{"type":"text","timestamp":1781756110530,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"id":"prt_ed8f0a6750010hQb5sBMVeePTL","messageID":"msg_ed8f0809d001l5LL0eJweTXKy6","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","type":"text","text":"SKILL ROUTING: User directed → deep-review. Binding `artifact_dir` directly to the provided lineage directory and constraining writes to that path.","time":{"start":1781756110453,"end":1781756110511},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ce26168c0f0e0bc016a3370ce712c8191b65b3382ac98c24e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756110785,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8lfPuwx0itilCFRPrm0gDInj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-review\n3: description: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\n5: argument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]\"\n6: version: 1.10.2.0\n7: ---\n8: <!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n9: \n10: <!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n11: \n12: # Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n13: \n14: Iterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n15: \n16: Runtime path resolution:\n17: - OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n18: - Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n19: - Codex runtime: `.codex/agents/*.toml`\n20: \n21: Convergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n22: \n23: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n24: \n25: ### When to Use This Skill\n26: \n27: Use this skill when:\n28: - Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\n29: - Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\n30: - Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\n31: - Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\n32: - Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\n33: - Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\n34: - Unattended or overnight audit sessions\n35: \n36: ### When NOT to Use\n37: \n38: - Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code-review` instead)\n39: - Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\n40: - Implementation tasks (use `sk-code` or `/speckit:implement`)\n41: - Quick one-file checks (use direct Grep/Read)\n42: - Fewer than 2 review dimensions needed (single-pass suffices)\n43: \n44: ### FORBIDDEN INVOCATION PATTERNS\n45: \n46: This skill is invoked EXCLUSIVELY through the `/deep:review` command. The command's YAML workflow owns state, dispatch, and convergence.\n47: \n48: **NEVER:**\n49: - Write a custom bash/shell dispatcher to parallelize iterations (ad-hoc shell fan-out)\n50: - Invoke cli-codex / cli-claude-code directly in a loop to simulate iterations\n51: - Manually write iteration prompts to `/tmp` and dispatch them via `copilot -p`\n52: - Dispatch the `@deep-review` LEAF agent via the Task tool for iteration loops (the agent is LEAF, a single iteration, and MUST be driven by the command's workflow)\n53: - Skip the state machine: `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-config.json`, `deltas/`, `prompts/`, `logs/`\n54: - Manage iteration state outside the resolved local review packet under `{spec_folder}/review/`\n55: \n56: **COMMAND-DRIVEN FAN-OUT IS SUPPORTED:** use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on `/deep:review`. The command's YAML `step_fanout_spawn` owns multi-lineage dispatch; `fanout-merge.cjs` applies strongest-restriction (any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL). This is not ad-hoc shell dispatch — it is the canonical fan-out path. Intra-lineage wave orchestration remains deferred.\n57: \n58: **ALWAYS:**\n59: - Invoke via `/deep:review :auto` or `/deep:review :confirm`\n60: - Let the command's YAML workflow own dispatch (auto: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`)\n61: - Let `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` be the SINGLE state writer\n62: - Require every iteration to produce BOTH the markdown narrative AND the JSONL delta (dispatch scripts must fail if either is missing)\n63: - Use `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` to locate the canonical review root\n64: \n65: ### Trigger Phrases\n66: \n67: - \"review code quality\" / \"audit this code\"\n68: - \"audit spec folder\" / \"validate spec completeness\"\n69: - \"release readiness check\" / \"pre-release review\"\n70: - \"find misalignments\" (between spec and implementation)\n71: - \"verify cross-references\" (across docs and code)\n72: - \"deep review\" / \"iterative review\" / \"review loop\"\n73: - \"quality audit\" / \"convergence detection\"\n74: \n75: ### Keyword Triggers\n76: \n77: `deep review`, `code audit`, `iterative review`, `review loop`, `release readiness`, `spec folder review`, `convergence detection`, `quality audit`, `find misalignments`, `verify cross-references`, `pre-release review`, `audit spec folder`\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n82: \n83: \n84: ### Resource Loading Levels\n85: \n86: | Level | When to Load | Resources |\n87: |-------|-------------|-----------|\n88: | ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` |\n89: | CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop protocol, convergence, state format, review contract |\n90: | ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full protocol docs, detailed specifications |\n91: \n92: ### Smart Router Pseudocode\n93: \n94: - Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n95: - Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards markdown paths, checks `inventory`, and uses `seen`.\n96: - Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - `get_routing_key()` derives the review phase from dispatch context.\n97: - Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` returns review disambiguation and missing phases return a \"no review resources\" notice.\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: from pathlib import Path\n101: \n102: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n103: RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n104: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"\n105: \n106: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n107:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"deep review\", \"review mode\", \"code audit\", \"iterative review\", \":review\", \"audit spec\"]},\n108:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"review iteration\", \"dimension review\", \"review findings\", \"P0\", \"P1\", \"P2\"]},\n109:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review convergence\", \"coverage gate\", \"verdict\", \"binary gate\", \"all dimensions\"]},\n110:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review report\", \"remediation\", \"verdict\", \"release readiness\", \"planning packet\"]},\n111: }\n112: \n113: NOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n114:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"audit code\": 2.0, \"review spec folder\": 1.8, \"release readiness\": 1.5, \"pre-release\": 1.5},\n115:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"review dimension\": 1.5, \"check correctness\": 1.4, \"check security\": 1.4, \"check alignment\": 1.4},\n116:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"all dimensions covered\": 1.6, \"coverage complete\": 1.5, \"stop review\": 1.4},\n117:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"review results\": 1.5, \"what to fix\": 1.4, \"ship decision\": 1.6, \"final report\": 1.5},\n118: }\n119: \n120: # RESOURCE_MAP: local markdown assets + local review-specific protocol docs\n121: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n122:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       [\n123:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n124:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n125:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n126:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n127:         \"assets/deep_review_strategy.md\",\n128:     ],\n129:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   [\n130:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n131:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n132:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n133:     ],\n134:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": [\n135:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n136:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n137:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n138:     ],\n139:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      [\n140:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n141:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n142:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n143:         \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\",\n144:     ],\n145: }\n146: \n147: LOADING_LEVELS = {\n148:     \"ALWAYS\":            [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n149:     \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all templates\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep review\", \"deep-review wave\", \"review artifact\", \"release-readiness audit\", \"convergence-tracked\", \"same session lineage\", \"P0\"],\n150:     \"ON_DEMAND\":         [\n151:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n152:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n153:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n154:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n155:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n156:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n157:     ],\n158: }\n159: \n160: PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP = {\n161:     \"init\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n162:     \"iteration\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n163:     \"stuck\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n164:     \"synthesis\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\", \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\"],\n165: }\n166: \n167: NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES = {\n168:     \"review_contract\": \"assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\",\n169: }\n170: \n171: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n172:     \"Confirm the review target or spec folder\",\n173:     \"Confirm the review phase\",\n174:     \"Provide one concrete file, diff range, or expected finding class\",\n175:     \"Confirm the verification command set before final review\",\n176: ]\n177: \n178: def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n179:     resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n180:     resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n181:     if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n182:         raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n183:     return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n184: \n185: def discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n186:     docs = []\n187:     for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n188:         if base.exists():\n189:             docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n190:     return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n191: \n192: def get_routing_key(dispatch_context) -> str:\n193:     phase = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"phase\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n194:     if phase:\n195:         return phase\n196:     text = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n197:     if \"recovery\" in text:\n198:         return \"stuck\"\n199:     if \"convergence\" in text or \"synthesis\" in text:\n200:         return \"synthesis\"\n201:     if \"iteration\" in text or \"dimension\" in text:\n202:         return \"iteration\"\n203:     return \"init\"\n204: \n205: def route_review_resources(task, dispatch_context):\n206:     inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n207:     routing_key = get_routing_key(dispatch_context)\n208:     scores = score_intents(task, INTENT_SIGNALS, NOISY_SYNONYMS)\n209:     intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n210: \n211:     loaded = []\n212:     seen = set()\n213: \n214:     def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n215:         guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n216:         if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n217:             load(guarded)\n218:             loaded.append(guarded)\n219:             seen.add(guarded)\n220: \n221:     for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n222:         load_if_available(relative_path)\n223: \n224:     if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n225:         return {\n226:             \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n227:             \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n228:             \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n229:             \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n230:             \"resources\": loaded,\n231:         }\n232: \n233:     phase_resources = PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP.get(routing_key, [])\n234:     if routing_key == \"unknown\" or not phase_resources:\n235:         return {\n236:             \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n237:             \"notice\": f\"No review resources found for routing key '{routing_key}'\",\n238:             \"resources\": loaded,\n239:         }\n240: \n241:     for intent in intents:\n242:         for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n243:             load_if_available(relative_path)\n244: \n245:     for relative_path in phase_resources:\n246:         load_if_available(relative_path)\n247: \n248:     task_text = str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n249:     if any(keyword in task_text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n250:         for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n251:             load_if_available(relative_path)\n252: \n253:     return {\n254:         \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n255:         \"intents\": intents,\n256:         \"resources\": loaded,\n257:         \"non_markdown_references\": NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES,\n258:     }\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ### Phase Detection\n262: \n263: Detect the current review phase from dispatch context to load appropriate resources:\n264: \n265: | Phase | Signal | Resources to Load |\n266: |-------|--------|-------------------|\n267: | Init | No JSONL exists in `review/` | Loop protocol, state format, state outputs, review contract |\n268: | Iteration | Dispatch context includes dimension + iteration number | Loop protocol, convergence, convergence signals, review contract |\n269: | Stuck | Dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY\" | Convergence, convergence signals, loop protocol, reducer registry |\n270: | Synthesis | Convergence triggered STOP | Review contract, state format, state outputs, reducer registry |\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n275: \n276: ### Resource Map Coverage Gate\n277: \n278: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep review treats it as a first-class audit input instead of optional prompt wiring.\n279: \n280: - Persist `resource_map_present: true` in `deep-review-config.json`.\n281: - Add a resource-map snapshot to `Known Context` so later iterations inherit the packet inventory baseline.\n282: - Promote `Resource Map Coverage` to a first-class audit angle alongside correctness, regression risk, test coverage, cross-runtime parity, observability, and docs-vs-code drift.\n283: - Reserve at least one loop iteration to cross-check `target_files` from `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md` against `resource-map.md`.\n284: - Treat that pass as mandatory coverage work, not an optional traceability extra.\n285: - Classify results into three buckets: entries touched, entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n286: - Findings emitted from that audit use the `resource-map-coverage` category.\n287: - Synthesis inserts `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` into `review-report.md` when the map was present at init.\n288: - Convergence also emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from review delta evidence unless the operator passes `--no-resource-map`.\n289: \n290: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` is absent at init:\n291: \n292: - Persist `resource_map_present: false`.\n293: - Log `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` in `Known Context`.\n294: - Skip the coverage-gate pass and omit the report section without failing the loop.\n295: \n296: ### Architecture\n297: \n298: `/deep:review` owns the loop. The YAML workflow initializes state, dispatches one LEAF review iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `review-report.md`, and saves continuity. The LEAF agent reads state, reviews one dimension, writes `iteration-NNN.md`, updates strategy, and appends JSONL.\n299: \n300: ### State Packet Location\n301: \n302: The review state packet always lives under the target spec's local `review/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/review/` directly. Child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/review/`. A `pt-NN` subfolder (`{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`) is allocated only when prior content already exists in `review/` for a non-matching target (continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n303: \n304: Example (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../006-continuity-refactor-gates/003-gate-c-writer-ready/` → `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/` (flat, no subfolder).\n305: \n306: Example (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/003-gate-c-writer-ready-pt-02/` (pt-NN allocated as a sibling to the prior content).\n307: \n308: Core artifacts: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, `.deep-review-pause`, `resource-map.md`, `review-report.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n309: \n310: ### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n311: \n312: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files, not memory. This solves context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n313: \n314: ### Data Flow\n315: \n316: Init creates config, strategy, and JSONL state. Each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches one dimension, records findings, and reduces state. Synthesis compiles the final report and saves continuity.\n317: \n318: ### Review Dimensions\n319: \n320: The four primary review dimensions (configured in `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml`):\n321: \n322: | Dimension | Focus | Key Questions |\n323: |-----------|-------|---------------|\n324: | **Correctness** | Logic, behavior, error handling | Does the code do what it claims? Are edge cases handled? |\n325: | **Security** | Vulnerabilities, exposure, trust boundaries | Are inputs validated? Are credentials exposed? |\n326: | **Spec-Alignment / Traceability** | Spec vs. implementation fidelity | Does code match spec.md? Are all planned items present? |\n327: | **Completeness / Maintainability** | Coverage, dead code, documentation | Are TODOs resolved? Is the code self-documenting? |\n328: \n329: ### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n330: \n331: Review mode is lineage-aware. Supported lifecycle modes are `new`, `resume`, and `restart`. Required lineage fields include `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, and `releaseReadinessState`. The reducer consumes the latest JSONL delta, the new iteration file, and prior reduced state, then emits finding registry, dashboard metrics, and strategy updates.\n332: \n333: ### Severity Classification\n334: \n335: | Severity | Criteria | Blocking |\n336: |----------|----------|---------|\n337: | **P0** | Correctness failure, security vulnerability, spec contradiction | Yes, blocks PASS verdict |\n338: | **P1** | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation | Conditional, triggers CONDITIONAL verdict |\n339: | **P2** | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps | No, PASS with advisories |\n340: \n341: ### Verdicts\n342: \n343: | Verdict | Condition |\n344: |---------|-----------|\n345: | **PASS** | No P0/P1 findings, P2 findings recorded as advisories (`hasAdvisories: true`) |\n346: | **CONDITIONAL** | P1 findings present, remediation plan included in report |\n347: | **FAIL** | Any P0 finding confirmed after adversarial self-check |\n348: \n349: ### Verdict Lock and Advisory Risk Score\n350: \n351: Always emit exactly one parseable verdict. A confirmed active P0 locks the verdict to `FAIL`; do not soften it to `CONDITIONAL`, `partial`, or any other phrasing. Truncated or partial iteration output is not a valid substitute for the final verdict line. Review narratives and JSONL details may include an optional advisory `riskScore` for relative risk calibration, but it never changes the `PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` mapping.\n352: \n353: ### Acceptance-Coverage Signal\n354: \n355: When the review target is a spec folder, deep review reflects the `AC_COVERAGE` validation signal in synthesis for Level 2+ folders only after both lifecycle conditions are true: `checklist.md` exists and `implementation-summary.md` is in-progress or later. Level 1 folders and fresh scaffolds are exempt. The signal is advisory while the validation rule remains INFO/default-off; it can add traceability context and planning-seed work, but it must not alter the exact iteration final-line contract below unless a later enforcement rollout explicitly changes severity.\n356: \n357: ### Iteration Final-Line Contract (MANDATORY)\n358: \n359: Every `iteration-NNN.md` MUST end with exactly one of the following plain-text lines as the **absolute final line** (no trailing whitespace, no variation):\n360: \n361: ```\n362: Review verdict: PASS\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ```\n366: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ```\n370: Review verdict: FAIL\n371: ```\n372: \n373: **Mapping rule:** PASS if no P0 or P1 findings in this iteration. CONDITIONAL if any P1 (but no P0) findings. FAIL if any P0 findings. P2-only findings → PASS.\n374: \n375: **VERDICT_LOCK:** Any confirmed active P0 forces the exact final line `Review verdict: FAIL`. Do not relabel that state as conditional, partial, mixed, or advisory.\n376: \n377: Downstream automation (including the synthesis phase and CI gate parser) parses this final line via exact string match, do not vary the format.\n378: \n379: ### Executor Selection Contract\n380: \n381: Executor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta. The full contract -- per-iteration invariants, failure modes, JSONL audit field, config surface and precedence, executor-invariant guarantees, and the four-value code-graph readiness TrustState surface -- lives in `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`.\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## 4. RULES\n386: \n387: ### ✅ ALWAYS\n388: \n389: 1. Read JSONL and strategy before review action.\n390: 2. Review one dimension per iteration and write findings to `iteration-NNN.md`.\n391: 3. Append JSONL with severity counts, finding detail, and `newInfoRatio`.\n392: 4. Cite every finding with `[SOURCE: file:line]`. Reject inference-only findings.\n393: 5. Re-read cited code before recording any P0.\n394: 6. Keep target files read-only.\n395: 7. Use `generate-context.js` for continuity saves. **Owner**: the YAML workflow (`deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) calls `generate-context.js` at the save phase. The reducer (`scripts/reduce-state.cjs`) does NOT call it directly. Operators should not invoke the reducer expecting continuity-save side effects.\n396: 8. Emit setup `BINDING:` lines before workflow output.\n397: 9. Refuse nested dispatch with: `REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.`\n398: \n399: ### ❌ NEVER\n400: \n401: 1. **Dispatch sub-agents**, `@deep-review` is LEAF-only. It cannot dispatch additional agents. When dispatch is requested, use the canonical REFUSE wording (ALWAYS rule 14).\n402: 2. **Hold findings in context**, Write everything to iteration files. Context is discarded after each dispatch.\n403: 3. **Exceed TCB**, Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle.\n404: 4. **Ask the user**, Autonomous execution. The agent makes best-judgment decisions without pausing.\n405: 5. **Skip convergence checks**, Every iteration must be evaluated against convergence criteria before the next dispatch.\n406: 6. **Modify config after init**, `deep-review-config.json` is read-only after initialization.\n407: 7. **Modify files under review**, The review loop is observation-only. No code changes during audit.\n408: 8. **Use WebFetch**, Review is code-only. No external resource fetching is permitted.\n409: 9. **Implement fixes during review**, Report findings only. Implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n410: \n411: ### Iteration Status Enum\n412: \n413: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight`\n414: \n415: - `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important finding that changes the verdict trajectory.\n416: \n417: ### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n418: \n419: 1. **3+ consecutive timeouts**, Infrastructure issue. Pause loop and report to user.\n420: 2. **State file corruption**, Cannot reconstruct iteration history from JSONL or iteration files.\n421: 3. **All dimensions covered with P0 findings remaining**, Human sign-off required before shipping.\n422: 4. **Security vulnerabilities discovered in production code**, Escalate immediately. Do not defer to report synthesis.\n423: 5. **All recovery tiers exhausted**, No automatic recovery path remaining in convergence protocol.\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ## 5. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n428: \n429: The router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/protocol/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`, `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md`, `assets/deep_review_strategy.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n430: \n431: Scripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n432: \n433: Detailed contracts: `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` (executor invariants, failure modes, config surface) and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` (two-tier content-hash dedup).\n434: \n435: Related skills: `deep-research` for investigation loops, `sk-code-review` for single-pass review doctrine, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state and continuity saves.\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n440: \n441: ### Loop Completion\n442: \n443: A review loop is considered complete when every item below holds:\n444: \n445: - The loop reached convergence (composite stop score above `compositeStopScore`, with required gates green) OR hit `maxIterations` without false-positive STOP.\n446: - Every configured review dimension has at least one full iteration of coverage recorded in `deep-review-state.jsonl` and reflected in `deep-review-strategy.md`.\n447: - Required traceability protocols (`spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`) executed at least once. Overlay protocols that apply to the target type ran or were explicitly marked N/A.\n448: - All canonical state files exist and parse cleanly: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, and one `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` per dispatched iteration.\n449: - `review/resource-map.md` was emitted from converged delta evidence unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag `--no-resource-map`).\n450: - `review/review-report.md` carries all 9 core sections (Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix) plus the conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present == true`.\n451: - Canonical continuity surfaces updated via `generate-context.js` (description.json, graph-metadata.json, indexed memory entries).\n452: \n453: ### Quality Gates\n454: \n455: Each gate is binary: pass or block. STOP cannot be legal until every gate passes.\n456: \n457: - **Config validity**: `deep-review-config.json` parses, names every required field, and lineage block matches the current run (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`).\n458: - **Strategy initialization**: `deep-review-strategy.md` carries the Files Under Review table, Cross-Reference Status grouped by core vs overlay, Known Context, and Review Boundaries.\n459: - **State consistency**: `deep-review-state.jsonl` opens with the config record and appends one iteration record per dispatched iteration. Reducer-owned fields in `deep-review-findings-registry.json` reconcile against JSONL totals.\n460: - **Iteration completeness**: every dispatched iteration produced both an `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` (non-empty, ending with the canonical `Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` line) AND a JSONL delta record with `findingDetails[]`, `findingsSummary`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n461: - **Severity coverage**: every reported finding carries `severity` in {P0, P1, P2}, `category`, `file:line` evidence, `finding_class`, and a `content_hash` for synthesis dedup.\n462: - **Advisory numeric score**: `riskScore` may appear in finding details as non-gating context only; verdict logic must ignore it.\n463: - **Adversarial replay**: every P0 finding survived adversarial self-check. Rejected P0s downgraded with rationale recorded in the iteration narrative.\n464: - **Coverage threshold**: `dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count` AND required traceability protocols covered, stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations.\n465: - **Acceptance coverage**: when the spec-folder lifecycle predicate is active, the final report records `AC_COVERAGE` status, covered/total, floor, and next action; default-off INFO output is advisory and does not by itself block STOP.\n466: - **Security-sensitive override**: when the run targets security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, or shared policy, the gates from `references/convergence/convergence.md` \"Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\" apply (`minStabilizationPasses=2`, closed-finding replay required, fix-completeness gate enforced).\n467: \n468: ### Validation Success\n469: \n470: The release-readiness handoff is valid when:\n471: \n472: - The final report records stop reason, iteration count, dimension coverage, severity counts (P0/P1/P2), verdict (PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL), and release-readiness state (`in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking`).\n473: - Verdict logic matches: PASS = no P0/P1 findings (P2 advisories permitted with `hasAdvisories: true`). CONDITIONAL = P1 findings present with remediation plan. FAIL = any P0 confirmed after adversarial self-check.\n474: - `resource-map.md` Phase-5 Augmentation section (if present) lists novel logic gaps with iteration source links, or explicitly records the empty-result case.\n475: - `skill_advisor.py \"run a deep review loop\" --threshold 0.8` still surfaces the skill after any graph-metadata edits.\n476: - `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` exits 0 on the target spec folder.\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n481: \n482: ### Framework Integration\n483: \n484: This skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or CODEX.md).\n485: \n486: Key integrations:\n487: - **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: deep review, code audit, iterative review)\n488: - **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3. The spec folder determines the `{spec_folder}/review/` state packet location\n489: - **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface. Canonical packet continuity is written via `generate-context.js`\n490: - **Command**: `/deep:review` is the primary invocation point\n491: \n492: ### Continuity Integration\n493: \n494: Recover context via `/speckit:resume` in the order `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During review, the agent writes iteration, strategy, and JSONL state. After synthesis, run `generate-context.js`.\n495: \n496: ### Code Graph Integration\n497: \n498: `code_graph_query + Grep` is available to `@deep-review` for semantic code search when Grep/Glob exact matching is insufficient. Use for:\n499: - Finding all usages of a pattern by concept/intent\n500: - Locating implementations when exact symbol names are unknown\n501: - Cross-referencing behavior across unfamiliar code paths\n\n(End of file - total 501 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\nargument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]\"\nversion: 1.10.2.0\n---\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n- Codex runtime: `.codex/agents/*.toml`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\nargument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]\"\nversion: 1.10.2.0\n---\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n- Codex runtime: `.codex/agents/*.toml`\n\nConvergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### When to Use This Skill\n\nUse this skill when:\n- Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\n- Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\n- Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\n- Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\n- Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\n- Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\n- Unattended or overnight audit sessions\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code-review` instead)\n- Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\n- Implementation tasks (use `sk-code` or `/speckit:implement`)\n- Quick one-file checks (use direct Grep/Read)\n- Fewer than 2 review dimensions needed (single-pass suffices)\n\n### FORBIDDEN INVOCATION PATTERNS\n\nThis skill is invoked EXCLUSIVELY through the `/deep:review` command. The command's YAML workflow owns state, dispatch, and convergence.\n\n**NEVER:**\n- Write a custom bash/shell dispatcher to parallelize iterations (ad-hoc shell fan-out)\n- Invoke cli-codex / cli-claude-code directly in a loop to simulate iterations\n- Manually write iteration prompts to `/tmp` and dispatch them via `copilot -p`\n- Dispatch the `@deep-review` LEAF agent via the Task tool for iteration loops (the agent is LEAF, a single iteration, and MUST be driven by the command's workflow)\n- Skip the state machine: `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-config.json`, `deltas/`, `prompts/`, `logs/`\n- Manage iteration state outside the resolved local review packet under `{spec_folder}/review/`\n\n**COMMAND-DRIVEN FAN-OUT IS SUPPORTED:** use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on `/deep:review`. The command's YAML `step_fanout_spawn` owns multi-lineage dispatch; `fanout-merge.cjs` applies strongest-restriction (any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL). This is not ad-hoc shell dispatch — it is the canonical fan-out path. Intra-lineage wave orchestration remains deferred.\n\n**ALWAYS:**\n- Invoke via `/deep:review :auto` or `/deep:review :confirm`\n- Let the command's YAML workflow own dispatch (auto: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`)\n- Let `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` be the SINGLE state writer\n- Require every iteration to produce BOTH the markdown narrative AND the JSONL delta (dispatch scripts must fail if either is missing)\n- Use `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` to locate the canonical review root\n\n### Trigger Phrases\n\n- \"review code quality\" / \"audit this code\"\n- \"audit spec folder\" / \"validate spec completeness\"\n- \"release readiness check\" / \"pre-release review\"\n- \"find misalignments\" (between spec and implementation)\n- \"verify cross-references\" (across docs and code)\n- \"deep review\" / \"iterative review\" / \"review loop\"\n- \"quality audit\" / \"convergence detection\"\n\n### Keyword Triggers\n\n`deep review`, `code audit`, `iterative review`, `review loop`, `release readiness`, `spec folder review`, `convergence detection`, `quality audit`, `find misalignments`, `verify cross-references`, `pre-release review`, `audit spec folder`\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level | When to Load | Resources |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|\n| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop protocol, convergence, state format, review contract |\n| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full protocol docs, detailed specifications |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards markdown paths, checks `inventory`, and uses `seen`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - `get_routing_key()` derives the review phase from dispatch context.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` returns review disambiguation and missing phases return a \"no review resources\" notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"deep review\", \"review mode\", \"code audit\", \"iterative review\", \":review\", \"audit spec\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"review iteration\", \"dimension review\", \"review findings\", \"P0\", \"P1\", \"P2\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review convergence\", \"coverage gate\", \"verdict\", \"binary gate\", \"all dimensions\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review report\", \"remediation\", \"verdict\", \"release readiness\", \"planning packet\"]},\n}\n\nNOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"audit code\": 2.0, \"review spec folder\": 1.8, \"release readiness\": 1.5, \"pre-release\": 1.5},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"review dimension\": 1.5, \"check correctness\": 1.4, \"check security\": 1.4, \"check alignment\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"all dimensions covered\": 1.6, \"coverage complete\": 1.5, \"stop review\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"review results\": 1.5, \"what to fix\": 1.4, \"ship decision\": 1.6, \"final report\": 1.5},\n}\n\n# RESOURCE_MAP: local markdown assets + local review-specific protocol docs\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_strategy.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": [\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      [\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\":            [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all templates\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep review\", \"deep-review wave\", \"review artifact\", \"release-readiness audit\", \"convergence-tracked\", \"same session lineage\", \"P0\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\":         [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nPHASE_RESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"init\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n    \"iteration\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n    \"stuck\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"synthesis\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\", \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\"],\n}\n\nNON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES = {\n    \"review_contract\": \"assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\",\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm the review target or spec folder\",\n    \"Confirm the review phase\",\n    \"Provide one concrete file, diff range, or expected finding class\",\n    \"Confirm the verification command set before final review\",\n]\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef get_routing_key(dispatch_context) -> str:\n    phase = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"phase\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n    if phase:\n        return phase\n    text = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if \"recovery\" in text:\n        return \"stuck\"\n    if \"convergence\" in text or \"synthesis\" in text:\n        return \"synthesis\"\n    if \"iteration\" in text or \"dimension\" in text:\n        return \"iteration\"\n    return \"init\"\n\ndef route_review_resources(task, dispatch_context):\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    routing_key = get_routing_key(dispatch_context)\n    scores = score_intents(task, INTENT_SIGNALS, NOISY_SYNONYMS)\n    intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n\n    for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    phase_resources = PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP.get(routing_key, [])\n    if routing_key == \"unknown\" or not phase_resources:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n            \"notice\": f\"No review resources found for routing key '{routing_key}'\",\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    for intent in intents:\n        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    for relative_path in phase_resources:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    task_text = str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if any(keyword in task_text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    return {\n        \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n        \"intents\": intents,\n        \"resources\": loaded,\n        \"non_markdown_references\": NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES,\n    }\n```\n\n### Phase Detection\n\nDetect the current review phase from dispatch context to load appropriate resources:\n\n| Phase | Signal | Resources to Load |\n|-------|--------|-------------------|\n| Init | No JSONL exists in `review/` | Loop protocol, state format, state outputs, review contract |\n| Iteration | Dispatch context includes dimension + iteration number | Loop protocol, convergence, convergence signals, review contract |\n| Stuck | Dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY\" | Convergence, convergence signals, loop protocol, reducer registry |\n| Synthesis | Convergence triggered STOP | Review contract, state format, state outputs, reducer registry |\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Resource Map Coverage Gate\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep review treats it as a first-class audit input instead of optional prompt wiring.\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: true` in `deep-review-config.json`.\n- Add a resource-map snapshot to `Known Context` so later iterations inherit the packet inventory baseline.\n- Promote `Resource Map Coverage` to a first-class audit angle alongside correctness, regression risk, test coverage, cross-runtime parity, observability, and docs-vs-code drift.\n- Reserve at least one loop iteration to cross-check `target_files` from `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md` against `resource-map.md`.\n- Treat that pass as mandatory coverage work, not an optional traceability extra.\n- Classify results into three buckets: entries touched, entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n- Findings emitted from that audit use the `resource-map-coverage` category.\n- Synthesis inserts `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` into `review-report.md` when the map was present at init.\n- Convergence also emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from review delta evidence unless the operator passes `--no-resource-map`.\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` is absent at init:\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: false`.\n- Log `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` in `Known Context`.\n- Skip the coverage-gate pass and omit the report section without failing the loop.\n\n### Architecture\n\n`/deep:review` owns the loop. The YAML workflow initializes state, dispatches one LEAF review iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `review-report.md`, and saves continuity. The LEAF agent reads state, reviews one dimension, writes `iteration-NNN.md`, updates strategy, and appends JSONL.\n\n### State Packet Location\n\nThe review state packet always lives under the target spec's local `review/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/review/` directly. Child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/review/`. A `pt-NN` subfolder (`{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`) is allocated only when prior content already exists in `review/` for a non-matching target (continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\nExample (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../006-continuity-refactor-gates/003-gate-c-writer-ready/` → `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/` (flat, no subfolder).\n\nExample (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/003-gate-c-writer-ready-pt-02/` (pt-NN allocated as a sibling to the prior content).\n\nCore artifacts: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, `.deep-review-pause`, `resource-map.md`, `review-report.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n\n### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files, not memory. This solves context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n\n### Data Flow\n\nInit creates config, strategy, and JSONL state. Each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches one dimension, records findings, and reduces state. Synthesis compiles the final report and saves continuity.\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\nThe four primary review dimensions (configured in `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml`):\n\n| Dimension | Focus | Key Questions |\n|-----------|-------|---------------|\n| **Correctness** | Logic, behavior, error handling | Does the code do what it claims? Are edge cases handled? |\n| **Security** | Vulnerabilities, exposure, trust boundaries | Are inputs validated? Are credentials exposed? |\n| **Spec-Alignment / Traceability** | Spec vs. implementation fidelity | Does code match spec.md? Are all planned items present? |\n| **Completeness / Maintainability** | Coverage, dead code, documentation | Are TODOs resolved? Is the code self-documenting? |\n\n### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n\nReview mode is lineage-aware. Supported lifecycle modes are `new`, `resume`, and `restart`. Required lineage fields include `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, and `releaseReadinessState`. The reducer consumes the latest JSONL delta, the new iteration file, and prior reduced state, then emits finding registry, dashboard metrics, and strategy updates.\n\n### Severity Classification\n\n| Severity | Criteria | Blocking |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| **P0** | Correctness failure, security vulnerability, spec contradiction | Yes, blocks PASS verdict |\n| **P1** | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation | Conditional, triggers CONDITIONAL verdict |\n| **P2** | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps | No, PASS with advisories |\n\n### Verdicts\n\n| Verdict | Condition |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **PASS** | No P0/P1 findings, P2 findings recorded as advisories (`hasAdvisories: true`) |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | P1 findings present, remediation plan included in report |\n| **FAIL** | Any P0 finding confirmed after adversarial self-check |\n\n### Verdict Lock and Advisory Risk Score\n\nAlways emit exactly one parseable verdict. A confirmed active P0 locks the verdict to `FAIL`; do not soften it to `CONDITIONAL`, `partial`, or any other phrasing. Truncated or partial iteration output is not a valid substitute for the final verdict line. Review narratives and JSONL details may include an optional advisory `riskScore` for relative risk calibration, but it never changes the `PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` mapping.\n\n### Acceptance-Coverage Signal\n\nWhen the review target is a spec folder, deep review reflects the `AC_COVERAGE` validation signal in synthesis for Level 2+ folders only after both lifecycle conditions are true: `checklist.md` exists and `implementation-summary.md` is in-progress or later. Level 1 folders and fresh scaffolds are exempt. The signal is advisory while the validation rule remains INFO/default-off; it can add traceability context and planning-seed work, but it must not alter the exact iteration final-line contract below unless a later enforcement rollout explicitly changes severity.\n\n### Iteration Final-Line Contract (MANDATORY)\n\nEvery `iteration-NNN.md` MUST end with exactly one of the following plain-text lines as the **absolute final line** (no trailing whitespace, no variation):\n\n```\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\n**Mapping rule:** PASS if no P0 or P1 findings in this iteration. CONDITIONAL if any P1 (but no P0) findings. FAIL if any P0 findings. P2-only findings → PASS.\n\n**VERDICT_LOCK:** Any confirmed active P0 forces the exact final line `Review verdict: FAIL`. Do not relabel that state as conditional, partial, mixed, or advisory.\n\nDownstream automation (including the synthesis phase and CI gate parser) parses this final line via exact string match, do not vary the format.\n\n### Executor Selection Contract\n\nExecutor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta. The full contract -- per-iteration invariants, failure modes, JSONL audit field, config surface and precedence, executor-invariant guarantees, and the four-value code-graph readiness TrustState surface -- lives in `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n\n1. Read JSONL and strategy before review action.\n2. Review one dimension per iteration and write findings to `iteration-NNN.md`.\n3. Append JSONL with severity counts, finding detail, and `newInfoRatio`.\n4. Cite every finding with `[SOURCE: file:line]`. Reject inference-only findings.\n5. Re-read cited code before recording any P0.\n6. Keep target files read-only.\n7. Use `generate-context.js` for continuity saves. **Owner**: the YAML workflow (`deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) calls `generate-context.js` at the save phase. The reducer (`scripts/reduce-state.cjs`) does NOT call it directly. Operators should not invoke the reducer expecting continuity-save side effects.\n8. Emit setup `BINDING:` lines before workflow output.\n9. Refuse nested dispatch with: `REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.`\n\n### ❌ NEVER\n\n1. **Dispatch sub-agents**, `@deep-review` is LEAF-only. It cannot dispatch additional agents. When dispatch is requested, use the canonical REFUSE wording (ALWAYS rule 14).\n2. **Hold findings in context**, Write everything to iteration files. Context is discarded after each dispatch.\n3. **Exceed TCB**, Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle.\n4. **Ask the user**, Autonomous execution. The agent makes best-judgment decisions without pausing.\n5. **Skip convergence checks**, Every iteration must be evaluated against convergence criteria before the next dispatch.\n6. **Modify config after init**, `deep-review-config.json` is read-only after initialization.\n7. **Modify files under review**, The review loop is observation-only. No code changes during audit.\n8. **Use WebFetch**, Review is code-only. No external resource fetching is permitted.\n9. **Implement fixes during review**, Report findings only. Implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n\n### Iteration Status Enum\n\n`complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight`\n\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important finding that changes the verdict trajectory.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. **3+ consecutive timeouts**, Infrastructure issue. Pause loop and report to user.\n2. **State file corruption**, Cannot reconstruct iteration history from JSONL or iteration files.\n3. **All dimensions covered with P0 findings remaining**, Human sign-off required before shipping.\n4. **Security vulnerabilities discovered in production code**, Escalate immediately. Do not defer to report synthesis.\n5. **All recovery tiers exhausted**, No automatic recovery path remaining in convergence protocol.\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/protocol/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`, `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md`, `assets/deep_review_strategy.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\nScripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n\nDetailed contracts: `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` (executor invariants, failure modes, config surface) and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` (two-tier content-hash dedup).\n\nRelated skills: `deep-research` for investigation loops, `sk-code-review` for single-pass review doctrine, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state and continuity saves.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Loop Completion\n\nA review loop is considered complete when every item below holds:\n\n- The loop reached convergence (composite stop score above `compositeStopScore`, with required gates green) OR hit `maxIterations` without false-positive STOP.\n- Every configured review dimension has at least one full iteration of coverage recorded in `deep-review-state.jsonl` and reflected in `deep-review-strategy.md`.\n- Required traceability protocols (`spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`) executed at least once. Overlay protocols that apply to the target type ran or were explicitly marked N/A.\n- All canonical state files exist and parse cleanly: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, and one `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` per dispatched iteration.\n- `review/resource-map.md` was emitted from converged delta evidence unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag `--no-resource-map`).\n- `review/review-report.md` carries all 9 core sections (Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix) plus the conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present == true`.\n- Canonical continuity surfaces updated via `generate-context.js` (description.json, graph-metadata.json, indexed memory entries).\n\n### Quality Gates\n\nEach gate is binary: pass or block. STOP cannot be legal until every gate passes.\n\n- **Config validity**: `deep-review-config.json` parses, names every required field, and lineage block matches the current run (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`).\n- **Strategy initialization**: `deep-review-strategy.md` carries the Files Under Review table, Cross-Reference Status grouped by core vs overlay, Known Context, and Review Boundaries.\n- **State consistency**: `deep-review-state.jsonl` opens with the config record and appends one iteration record per dispatched iteration. Reducer-owned fields in `deep-review-findings-registry.json` reconcile against JSONL totals.\n- **Iteration completeness**: every dispatched iteration produced both an `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` (non-empty, ending with the canonical `Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` line) AND a JSONL delta record with `findingDetails[]`, `findingsSummary`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n- **Severity coverage**: every reported finding carries `severity` in {P0, P1, P2}, `category`, `file:line` evidence, `finding_class`, and a `content_hash` for synthesis dedup.\n- **Advisory numeric score**: `riskScore` may appear in finding details as non-gating context only; verdict logic must ignore it.\n- **Adversarial replay**: every P0 finding survived adversarial self-check. Rejected P0s downgraded with rationale recorded in the iteration narrative.\n- **Coverage threshold**: `dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count` AND required traceability protocols covered, stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations.\n- **Acceptance coverage**: when the spec-folder lifecycle predicate is active, the final report records `AC_COVERAGE` status, covered/total, floor, and next action; default-off INFO output is advisory and does not by itself block STOP.\n- **Security-sensitive override**: when the run targets security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, or shared policy, the gates from `references/convergence/convergence.md` \"Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\" apply (`minStabilizationPasses=2`, closed-finding replay required, fix-completeness gate enforced).\n\n### Validation Success\n\nThe release-readiness handoff is valid when:\n\n- The final report records stop reason, iteration count, dimension coverage, severity counts (P0/P1/P2), verdict (PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL), and release-readiness state (`in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking`).\n- Verdict logic matches: PASS = no P0/P1 findings (P2 advisories permitted with `hasAdvisories: true`). CONDITIONAL = P1 findings present with remediation plan. FAIL = any P0 confirmed after adversarial self-check.\n- `resource-map.md` Phase-5 Augmentation section (if present) lists novel logic gaps with iteration source links, or explicitly records the empty-result case.\n- `skill_advisor.py \"run a deep review loop\" --threshold 0.8` still surfaces the skill after any graph-metadata edits.\n- `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` exits 0 on the target spec folder.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or CODEX.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: deep review, code audit, iterative review)\n- **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3. The spec folder determines the `{spec_folder}/review/` state packet location\n- **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface. Canonical packet continuity is written via `generate-context.js`\n- **Command**: `/deep:review` is the primary invocation point\n\n### Continuity Integration\n\nRecover context via `/speckit:resume` in the order `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During review, the agent writes iteration, strategy, and JSONL state. After synthesis, run `generate-context.js`.\n\n### Code Graph Integration\n\n`code_graph_query + Grep` is available to `@deep-review` for semantic code search when Grep/Glob exact matching is insufficient. Use for:\n- Finding all usages of a pattern by concept/intent\n- Locating implementations when exact symbol names are unknown\n- Cross-referencing behavior across unfamiliar code paths","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":501,"totalLines":501,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1781756110764,"end":1781756110782}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ce26168c0f0e0bc016a3370ce80308191a6be9ac974443bbc"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0a6b10017mVa3DGRr4LGee","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0809d001l5LL0eJweTXKy6"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781756111078,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"id":"prt_ed8f0a8e4001V0YDMuyTNagIMK","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"44912c82179a120422901c99fcb7ac64bfd56556","messageID":"msg_ed8f0809d001l5LL0eJweTXKy6","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":36894,"input":2740,"output":99,"reasoning":263,"cache":{"write":0,"read":33792}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781756112784,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"id":"prt_ed8f0af8f001dFMKhxbjMuS2JR","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","snapshot":"44912c82179a120422901c99fcb7ac64bfd56556","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1781756132669,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"id":"prt_ed8f0e371001I82ZUxkUe3dwQu","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","type":"text","text":"Reading the command-owned workflow and local protocol resources now so the lineage artifacts match the deep-review state contract rather than a hand-rolled layout.","time":{"start":1781756126065,"end":1781756132667},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370dddf888191a310695d8c98761b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756132725,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_i9b6i8CgyJViNoix8nUMBNLV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n5: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6: role: Deep Review Loop Manager\n7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\n8: action: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\n9: operating_mode:\n10:   workflow: iterative_loop\n11:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n12:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n13:   approvals: none\n14:   tracking: progressive_review_state\n15:   validation: convergence_detection\n16: \n17: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n18: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: operating_principles:\n21:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n22:   approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n23:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n24: \n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n27: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n28: user_inputs:\n29:   review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n30:   review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n31:   review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n32:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n33:   lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n34:   max_iterations: 7\n35:   convergence_threshold: 0.10\n36: \n37: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n38: # CONTEXT LOADING\n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: context_loading:\n41:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n42:   purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n43:   mcp_integration:\n44:     tool: memory_context\n45:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n46:     parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n47:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n48:   behavior:\n49:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n50:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n51: \n52: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n53: # SKILL REFERENCE\n54: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n55: skill_reference:\n56:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n57:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n58:   references:\n59:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n60:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n61:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n62:   templates:\n63:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n64:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n65: \n66: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n67: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n68: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n69: agent_config:\n70:   agent: deep-review\n71:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n72:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n73:   mode: subagent\n74:   model: opus\n75:   leaf_only: true\n76:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n77:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n78:   tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n79: \n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: # STATE FILE PATHS\n82: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n83: state_paths:\n84:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n85:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n86:   # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n87:   # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n88:   # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n89:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n90:   local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n91:   legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n92:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n93:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n94:   findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n95:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n96:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n97:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n98:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n99:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n100:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n101:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n102:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n103:   # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n104:   # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n105:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n106:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n107:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n108:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n109:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n110: \n111: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n112: # WORKFLOW\n113: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n114: workflow:\n115: \n116:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n117:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n118:     note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n119:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n120:     if_present:\n121:       bind:\n122:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n123:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n124:         artifact_subfolder: null\n125:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n126:     if_absent:\n127:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n128:       outputs:\n129:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n130:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n131:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n132:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n133: \n134:   step_fanout_spawn:\n135:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n136:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n137:     instructions: |\n138:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n139:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n140:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n141:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n142:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n143:     sub_steps:\n144:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n145:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n146:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n147:         command: |\n148:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n149:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n150:             --loop-type review \\\n151:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n152:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n153:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n154:         wait_for_completion: true\n155:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n156:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-review sub-agent\"\n157:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n158:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n159:         dispatch:\n160:           agent: deep-review\n161:           model: opus\n162:           context: |\n163:             Execute the deep-review loop with these parameters:\n164:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n165:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n166:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n167:               executor: native\n168:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n169:         wait_for_completion: true\n170: \n171:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n172:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n173:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n174:   phase_init:\n175:     purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n176:     steps:\n177: \n178:       step_preflight_contract:\n179:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n180:         verify:\n181:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n182:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n183:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n184:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n185:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n186: \n187:       step_create_directories:\n188:         action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n189:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n190: \n191:       step_detect_resource_map:\n192:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n193:         inspect:\n194:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n195:         classify:\n196:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n197:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n198:         outputs:\n199:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n200:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n201: \n202:       step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n203:         action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n204:         detect:\n205:           canonical_review_state:\n206:             - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n207:             - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n208:             - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n209:             - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n210:           legacy_review_state:\n211:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n212:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n213:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n214:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n215:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n216:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n217:             - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n218:             - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n219:           legacy_review_markers:\n220:             - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n221:             - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n222:         migrate_only:\n223:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n224:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n225:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n226:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n227:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n228:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n229:           - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n230:           - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n231:         on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n232:         on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n233:         on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n234:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n235: \n236:       step_acquire_lock:\n237:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n238:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n239:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n240:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n241:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n242:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n243:         on_halt:\n244:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n245:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n246:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n247:         on_cancel:\n248:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n249:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n250:         on_workflow_exit:\n251:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n252:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n253: \n254:       step_classify_session:\n255:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n256:         inspect:\n257:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n258:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n259:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n260:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n261:         classify:\n262:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n263:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n264:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n265:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n266:         outputs:\n267:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n268:         on_resume:\n269:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n270:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n271:           skip_to: phase_loop\n272:         on_restart:\n273:           action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n274:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n275:           set:\n276:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n277:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n278:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n279:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n280:           skip_to: step_create_config\n281:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n282:         on_completed_session:\n283:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n284:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n285:         on_invalid_state:\n286:           halt: true\n287:           message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n288:         on_fresh:\n289:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n290: \n291:       step_scope_discovery:\n292:         action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n293:         resolve:\n294:           spec-folder: |\n295:             1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n296:             2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n297:             3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n298:             4. Set scope = all discovered files\n299:           skill: |\n300:             1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n301:             2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n302:             3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n303:             4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n304:             5. Set scope = all discovered files\n305:           agent: |\n306:             1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n307:             2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n308:             3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n309:           track: |\n310:             1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n311:             2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n312:             3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n313:           files: |\n314:             1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n315:             2. Validate all files exist\n316:             3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n317:             4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n318:         outputs:\n319:           - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n320:           - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n321: \n322:       step_order_dimensions:\n323:         action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n324:         algorithm: |\n325:           1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n326:           2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n327:              correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n328:           3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n329:           4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n330:              - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n331:              - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n332:           5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n333:           6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n334:         outputs:\n335:           - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n336:           - inventory_pass: true\n337: \n338:       step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n339:         action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n340:         outputs:\n341:           - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n342:           - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n343:         normalize: |\n344:           Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n345:             - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n346:             - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n347:             - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n348:           Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n349: \n350:       step_create_config:\n351:         action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n352:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n353:         populate:\n354:           topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n355:           mode: \"review\"\n356:           sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n357:           parentSessionId: null\n358:           lineageMode: \"new\"\n359:           generation: 1\n360:           continuedFromRun: null\n361:           reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n362:           reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n363:           # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n364:           reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n365:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n366:           reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n367:           severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n368:           crossReference:\n369:             core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n370:             overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n371:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n372:           # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n373:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n374:           stuckThreshold: 2\n375:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n376:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n377:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n378:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n379:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n380:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n381:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n382:           status: \"initialized\"\n383:           releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n384:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n385:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n386: \n387:       step_create_state_log:\n388:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n389:         note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n390:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n391:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n392:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n393:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n394: \n395:       step_create_findings_registry:\n396:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n397:         content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n398:         output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n399: \n400:       step_create_strategy:\n401:         action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n402:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n403:         populate:\n404:           review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n405:           review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n406:           dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n407:           scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n408:           cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n409:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n410:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n411:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n412: \n413:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n414:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n415:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n416:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n417:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n418: \n419:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n420:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n421:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n422:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n423: \n424:       step_init_complete:\n425:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n426:         set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n427: \n428:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n429:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n430:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n431:   phase_loop:\n432:     purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n433:     repeat: true\n434:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n435:     steps:\n436: \n437:       step_read_state:\n438:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n439:         read:\n440:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n441:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n442:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n443:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n444:         extract:\n445:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n446:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n447:           - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n448:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n449:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n450:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n451:           - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n452:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n453:           - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n454:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n455:           - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n456:           - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n457:           - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n458:           - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n459:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n460:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n461:           - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n462:           - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n463:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n464:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n465:           - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n466:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n467:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n468:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n469:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n470: \n471:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n472:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n473:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n474:         if_exists:\n475:           set:\n476:             pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n477:             pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n478:             pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n479:           skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n480:         if_not_exists:\n481:           proceed: true\n482: \n483:       step_graph_convergence:\n484:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n485:         inspect:\n486:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n487:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n488:         transform: |\n489:           1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n490:           2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n491:           3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n492:           4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n493:           5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n494:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n495:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n496:         append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n497:         outputs:\n498:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n499:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n500:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n501:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n502:           - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n503: \n504:       step_check_convergence:\n505:         action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n506:         algorithm: |\n507:           0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n508:              claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n509:              If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n510:                candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n511:                stop_blocked = true\n512:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n513:                blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n514:                recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n515:                Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n516:           1. HARD STOPS:\n517:              a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n518:              b) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n519:              Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n520:           2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n521:              if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n522:           3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n523:                graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n524:                Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n525:                If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n526:           4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n527:                signals = []\n528:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n529:                   avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n530:                   stop if avg <= 0.08\n531:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n532:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n533:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n534:                c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n535:                   coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n536:                   stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n537:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n538:                if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n539:                if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n540:           5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n541:                a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n542:                b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n543:                c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n544:                d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n545:                e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n546:                f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n547:                g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n548:                h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n549:                i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n550:              if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n551:                decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n552:                stop_blocked = true\n553:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n554:                blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n555:                blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n556:                convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n557:                convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n558:                dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n559:                dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n560:                dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n561:                p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n562:                active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n563:                evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n564:                avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n565:                hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n566:                claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n567:                claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n568:                fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n569:                security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n570:                fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n571:                fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n572:                candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n573:                candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n574:                candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n575:                graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n576:                graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n577:                graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n578:                graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n579:                recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n580:           6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n581:                a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n582:                b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n583:                     decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n584:                     stop_blocked = true\n585:                     stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n586:                     # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n587:                     # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n588:                     # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n589:                     # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n590:                     blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n591:                     blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n592:                     graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n593:                     recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n594:                c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n595:                     decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n596:                     stop_blocked = false\n597:                     reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n598:                d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n599:         outputs:\n600:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n601:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n602:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n603:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n604:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n605:           - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n606:           - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n607:           - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n608:           - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n609:           - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n610:           - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n611:           - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n612:           - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n613:           - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n614:           - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n615:           - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n616:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n617:           - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n618:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n619:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n620:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n621:           - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n622:           - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n623:           - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n624:           - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n625:           - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n626:           - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n627:           - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n628:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n629:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n630:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n631:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n632:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n633: \n634:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-634. Use offset=635 to continue.)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md\n---\ndescription: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Context Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-context loop. This command verifies the orchestrating agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoints, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\nThis command is **general-agent based** and must pass the @general verification gate before setup routing continues. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n│\n├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate the deep-context loop (YAML workflow execution)\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n│   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n│\n├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-context loop and runs   │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:context [arguments]                                │ \n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n- Resolve `executor_pool` before persisting config and entering the YAML workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached command suffixes (`:auto` or `:confirm`). Canonical mode syntax is `/deep:context:auto` and `/deep:context:confirm`; keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n2. Treat scope text, `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, relevance/agreement flags, executor pool flags, and pre-bound setup answers as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If `:auto` is present, set `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` and resolve required setup inputs through the presentation contract's three-tier auto setup resolution before loading YAML.\n4. If `:confirm` is present, set `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt before loading YAML.\n5. If no mode suffix is present, set `execution_mode = ASK` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n6. Load the selected workflow asset only after `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, and `executor_pool` are bound.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, question text, and reply-format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display behavior.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layouts, workflow overview displays, convergence threshold semantics, runtime robustness/session classification displays, and memory/skill reference displays.\n- Success and failure result templates, output formats, and error-handling displays.\n- Example invocations, executor-pool explanation display, and next-step suggestion wording.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe YAML workflow runs iterative codebase-context gathering by seeding a `SLICE` frontier from the scope, dispatching every executor over the same focus as a parallel sweep, merging findings by `file:symbol` with agreement counts, and synthesizing a reuse-first Context Report under `context/`. Convergence uses deep-context's relevance-gated coverage saturation with agreement and relevance as blocking guards; do not transfer sibling defaults from deep-research or deep-review. Code graph tool IDs remain stable as `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context`; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n**Context path:** `/deep:context` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Research:** `/deep:research` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` -> (if issues) `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:","truncated":true,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n  lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n  max_iterations: 7\n  convergence_threshold: 0.10\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-review\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  mode: subagent\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n  # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n  # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n  # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n  legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n  findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n  # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n  # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-review sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-review\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-review loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n        action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n        detect:\n          canonical_review_state:\n            - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          legacy_review_state:\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n            - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n          legacy_review_markers:\n            - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n            - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n        migrate_only:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n        on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n        on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n        on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_scope_discovery:\n        action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n        resolve:\n          spec-folder: |\n            1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n            2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n            3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n            4. Set scope = all discovered files\n          skill: |\n            1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n            2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n            3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n            4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n            5. Set scope = all discovered files\n          agent: |\n            1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n            2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n            3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n          track: |\n            1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n            2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n            3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n          files: |\n            1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n            2. Validate all files exist\n            3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n            4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n        outputs:\n          - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n          - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n\n      step_order_dimensions:\n        action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n          2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n             correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n          3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n          4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n             - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n             - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n          5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n          6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n        outputs:\n          - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n          - inventory_pass: true\n\n      step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n        action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n        outputs:\n          - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n          - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n        normalize: |\n          Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n            - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n            - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n            - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n          Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n          mode: \"review\"\n          sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          parentSessionId: null\n          lineageMode: \"new\"\n          generation: 1\n          continuedFromRun: null\n          reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n          reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n          reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n          crossReference:\n            core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n            overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n        note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_findings_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n          review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n          scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n          - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n          - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n          - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n          - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          set:\n            pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n          skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n          2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n          3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n          4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n          5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n        append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n          - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n        algorithm: |\n          0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n             claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n             If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n               candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n               recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n               Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n          1. HARD STOPS:\n             a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n             b) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n             Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n          2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n             if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n               graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n               Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n               If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n          4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n               signals = []\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n                  stop if avg <= 0.08\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n                  coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n                  stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n               if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n          5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n               a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n               b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n               c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n               d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n               e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n               f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n               g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n               h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n               i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n             if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n               decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n               blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n               convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n               convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n               dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n               dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n               p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n               active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n               evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n               avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n               hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n               fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n               security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n               fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n                    blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n                    graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n                    recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n               c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n                    decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n                    stop_blocked = false\n                    reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n               d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n          - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n          - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n          - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n          - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n          - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n          - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n          - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n          - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n          - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n          - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n          - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n          - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":634,"totalLines":635,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781756132716,"end":1781756132723}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370e49cb481918b78ae9d9d7174a0"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0fd43001rjED6Fw3TchUVW","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756132745,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bwCaGe1urYzUXsdIv81cH5Sx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review quick reference\"\n6:   - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n7:   - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n8:   - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n9:   - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\n10: importance_tier: normal\n11: contextType: general\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Quick Reference\n15: \n16: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Use this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: - Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n29: - Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n30: - Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n31: - Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n32: \n33: ### Commands\n34: \n35: | Command | Description |\n36: |---------|-------------|\n37: | `/deep:review:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n38: | `/deep:review:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n39: | `/deep:review \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n40: \n41: ### Parameters\n42: \n43: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n44: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n45: | `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n46: | `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n47: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n48: | `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## 2. WHEN TO USE\n53: \n54: | Scenario | Use |\n55: |----------|-----|\n56: | Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:review` |\n57: | Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code-review` |\n58: | Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:review:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n59: | Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:review:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n60: | Deep technical investigation | `/deep:research` (different skill) |\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n65: \n66: ```\n67: /deep:review  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n68:     |                    |                      |\n69:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n70:     |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n71:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n72:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n73:     |                    |\n74:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n75:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n76:     |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n77:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 4. STATE FILES\n83: \n84: Review mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n85: \n86: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n87: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n88: | Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n89: | State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n90: | Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n91: | Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n92: | Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n93: | Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n94: | Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n95: | Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n96: \n97: ### Lifecycle Modes\n98: \n99: | Mode | Effect |\n100: |------|--------|\n101: | `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n102: | `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n103: | `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n104: | `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n109: \n110: | ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n111: |----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n112: | D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n113: | D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n114: | D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n115: | D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n120: \n121: | Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n122: |---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n123: | FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n124: | CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n125: | PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n126: \n127: ### Release Readiness\n128: \n129: `releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n130: \n131: | State | Meaning |\n132: |-------|---------|\n133: | `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n134: | `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n135: | `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n140: \n141: | Gate | Rule |\n142: |------|------|\n143: | Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n144: | Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n145: | Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n150: \n151: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n152: |--------|--------|-------------|\n153: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n154: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n155: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n156: \n157: **Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n158: \n159: **P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n164: \n165: Each @deep-review iteration:\n166: 1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n167: 2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n168: 3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n169: 4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n170: 5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n171: 6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n172: 7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n177: \n178: | # | Section | Purpose |\n179: |---|---------|---------|\n180: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n181: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n182: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n183: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n184: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n185: | 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n186: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n187: | 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n188: | 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n193: \n194: | Goal | Adjustment |\n195: |------|------------|\n196: | Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n197: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n198: | Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n199: | Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n204: \n205: | Problem | Fix |\n206: |---------|-----|\n207: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05 |\n208: | Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n209: | P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n210: | Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n211: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ## 13. RELATED\n216: \n217: | Resource | Purpose |\n218: |----------|---------|\n219: | `deep-research` | Investigation/research (not review) |\n220: | `sk-code-review` | Single-pass code review |\n221: | `@deep-review` | Single review iteration agent (LEAF) |\n222: | `@context` | Single-pass codebase search |\n223: | `generate-context.js` | Memory save script |\n224: \n225: For review-specific protocol documentation, see local `references/`:\n226: - `loop_protocol.md`, Review loop lifecycle (4 phases)\n227: - `../state/state_format.md`, Review state file schemas\n228: - `../convergence/convergence.md`, Review convergence algorithms\n\n(End of file - total 228 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review quick reference\"\n  - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n  - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n  - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review quick reference\"\n  - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n  - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n  - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nUse this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n- Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n- Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n- Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n\n### Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:review:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:review:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:review \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n\n---\n\n## 2. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:review` |\n| Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code-review` |\n| Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:review:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n| Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:review:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n| Deep technical investigation | `/deep:research` (different skill) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```\n/deep:review  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE FILES\n\nReview mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n| State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n| Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n| Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n| Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n| Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n| Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n\n### Lifecycle Modes\n\n| Mode | Effect |\n|------|--------|\n| `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n| `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n| `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n| `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n\n| ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n|----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n| D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n| D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n| D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n\n---\n\n## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n|---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n| FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n| CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n| PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n\n### Release Readiness\n\n`releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n\n| State | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n| `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n| `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n| Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n| Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n\n---\n\n## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n\n**Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n\n**P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n\n---\n\n## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-review iteration:\n1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n\n---\n\n## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n\n| # | Section | Purpose |\n|---|---------|---------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n| 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n| 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n| Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n\n---\n\n## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05 |\n| Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n| P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n| Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n\n---\n\n## 13. RELATED\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `deep-research` | Investigation/research (not review) |\n| `sk-code-review` | Single-pass code review |\n| `@deep-review` | Single review iteration agent (LEAF) |\n| `@context` | Single-pass codebase search |\n| `generate-context.js` | Memory save script |\n\nFor review-specific protocol documentation, see local `references/`:\n- `loop_protocol.md`, Review loop lifecycle (4 phases)\n- `../state/state_format.md`, Review state file schemas\n- `../convergence/convergence.md`, Review convergence algorithms","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":228,"totalLines":228,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1781756132733,"end":1781756132744}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370e49cc08191a192bd07e8a7d4fc"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0fd6d001tgGL3n2FdCz61y","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756132774,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_k5GrqT0nTUdgAGFos8jzCQXb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n6:   - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n7:   - \"review loop initialization\"\n8:   - \"review auto resume\"\n9:   - \"review synthesis phase\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\n15: \n16: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n29: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n30: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n31: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n32: \n33: ```\n34: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n35: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n36: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n37: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n38: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n39: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n40: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n41: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n42: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n43: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n44: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n45: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n46: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n47: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n48: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n50: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ### Core Innovation\n54: \n55: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n56: \n57: ### Key References\n58: \n59: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n60: |----------|------|---------|\n61: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n62: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n63: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n64: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n65: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n70: \n71: ### Purpose\n72: \n73: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n74: \n75: ### Steps\n76: \n77: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n78:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n79:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n80:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n81:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n82: \n83: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n84: \n85: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n86: \n87:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n88:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n89:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n90:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n91:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n92:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n93:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n94: \n95:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n96: \n97: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n98: \n99:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n100:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\n101:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n102:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n103:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n104:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n105: \n106:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n107: \n108: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n109: \n110:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n111:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n112:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n113:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n114:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n115:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n116:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n117:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n118: \n119:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n120: \n121: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n122: \n123: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n124: \n125: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n126: \n127: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n128:    - Topic (review target description)\n129:    - Review Dimensions checklist\n130:    - Files Under Review table\n131:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n132:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n133:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n134:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n135:    - Review Boundaries from config\n136: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n137:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n138:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n139: \n140: 10. **Validate review charter**:\n141:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n142:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n143:    - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n144: \n145: 11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n146: \n147: ### Outputs\n148: \n149: | File | Location | Purpose |\n150: |------|----------|---------|\n151: | Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n152: | State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n153: | Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n154: | Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n159: \n160: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n161: \n162: #### Step 1: Read State\n163: \n164: - Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n165: - Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n166: - Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n167: \n168: Reducer contract for every loop refresh:\n169: \n170: | Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n171: |--------------|-----------------|-------|\n172: | Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n173: | Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n174: | Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n175: \n176: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n177: \n178: Run `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n179: \n180: - Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n181: - Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n182: - Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n183:   - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n184:   - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n185:   - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n186:   - Required traceability protocols are covered\n187:   - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n188: - Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n189: \n190: If convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n191: \n192: - `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n193: - `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n194: - `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n195: \n196: The blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n197: \n198: Convergence signals and weights:\n199: \n200: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n201: |--------|--------|-------------|\n202: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n203: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n204: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n205: \n206: **P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n207: \n208: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n209: \n210: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n211: \n212: 1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n213: 2. If present:\n214:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n215:    - Halt the loop with message:\n216:      ```\n217:      Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n218:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n219:      ```\n220:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n221: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n222:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n223:    - Continue from step_read_state\n224: \n225: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n226: \n227: Normalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n228: \n229: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n230: \n231: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n232: \n233: ```\n234: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\n235: Iteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\n236: Target: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\n237: Dimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\n238: Findings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\n239: Traceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\n240: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n241: Provisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\n242: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n243: ```\n244: \n245: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n246: \n247: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n248: \n249: Dispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n250: \n251: ```\n252: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n253: \n254: Review Target: {config.reviewTarget}\n255: Review Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\n256: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n257: Focus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\n258: Focus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\n259: Remaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}\n260: Traceability Protocols:\n261:   - Core: {core_protocols}\n262:   - Overlay: {overlay_protocols}\n263: Active Findings: {findingsSummary}\n264: State Files:\n265:   - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\n266:   - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\n267:   - Registry: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\n268:   - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\n269: Output: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n270: CONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n271: CONSTRAINT: Target files are READ-ONLY -- never modify code under review\n272: ```\n273: \n274: #### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n275: \n276: Before dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n277: \n278: - `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-review` agent with model Opus.\n279: - `cli-codex` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `codex exec --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n280: - `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only). We override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n281: \n282: All branches share:\n283: 1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n284: 2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n285: 3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n286: \n287: Per-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n288: \n289: Cross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope. See the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n290: \n291: Failure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n292: \n293: **Agent constraints**:\n294: - `@deep-review` is LEAF-only: it cannot dispatch sub-agents\n295: - No WebFetch: review is code-only and read-only\n296: - Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle\n297: - Tools available: Read, Grep, Glob, Edit (state files only), code_graph_query + Grep\n298: \n299: #### Step 3a: Cross-Reference Protocol Execution\n300: \n301: During iterations focused on the Traceability dimension, the agent executes applicable cross-reference protocols. Each protocol produces a structured result appended to the JSONL `traceabilityChecks.results[]` array.\n302: \n303: | Protocol | Execution | Expected Output |\n304: |----------|-----------|-----------------|\n305: | `spec_code` | Compare normative claims in spec.md against shipped implementation | Pass/partial/fail per claim with file:line evidence |\n306: | `checklist_evidence` | Verify every `[x]` mark in checklist.md has supporting evidence | Pass/partial/fail per checked item |\n307: | `skill_agent` | Compare SKILL.md contracts against runtime agent definitions | Agreement/drift/disagreement per capability |\n308: | `agent_cross_runtime` | Compare agent definitions across runtimes (.opencode, .claude, .codex) | Parity/drift/divergence per runtime pair |\n309: | `feature_catalog_code` | Compare catalog claims against discoverable implementation | Match/stale/missing per feature |\n310: | `playbook_capability` | Validate playbook scenarios against executable reality | Executable/needs-update/impossible per scenario |\n311: \n312: Each protocol result includes:\n313: - `protocolId`: Protocol identifier\n314: - `status`: `pass`, `partial`, or `fail`\n315: - `gateClass`: `hard` or `advisory`\n316: - `applicable`: Whether the protocol applies to this target type\n317: - `counts`: `{ pass, partial, fail, skipped }`\n318: - `evidence`: Array of file:line citations\n319: - `findingRefs`: Array of finding IDs generated from this protocol\n320: - `summary`: Human-readable summary text\n321: \n322: #### Step 3b: Resource Map Coverage Audit\n323: \n324: When `config.resource_map_present == true`, at least one loop iteration MUST audit implementation-vs-resource-map coverage:\n325: \n326: 1. Read `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`\n327: 2. Read applied reports under `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md`\n328: 3. Cross-check `target_files` from the applied reports against resource-map entries\n329: 4. Classify outcomes into:\n330:    - entries touched\n331:    - entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`)\n332:    - implementation paths absent from the map\n333: 5. Emit any resulting findings with category `resource-map-coverage`\n334: \n335: When `config.resource_map_present == false`, skip this audit and rely on the `Known Context` note: `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate`.\n336: \n337: #### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n338: \n339: After agent completes:\n340: \n341: 1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n342: 2. Verify JSONL was appended with review iteration fields:\n343:    - `dimensions` (array of dimensions covered)\n344:    - `filesReviewed` (array of file paths)\n345:    - `findingsSummary` (cumulative P0/P1/P2 counts)\n346:    - `findingsNew` (this iteration's new findings)\n347:    - `traceabilityChecks` (protocol results if applicable)\n348: 3. Verify strategy.md was updated (dimension progress, findings count, protocol status)\n349: 4. Extract `newFindingsRatio` from JSONL record\n350: 5. Update stuck tracking using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`:\n351:    - Skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change)\n352:    - Reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress)\n353:    - Increment if `newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold`\n354:    - Reset otherwise\n355: \n356: #### Step 4a: Claim Adjudication\n357: \n358: Before the next convergence pass, the orchestrator adjudicates every new P0/P1 finding with a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. This step prevents false positives from inflating severity and distorting convergence, AND acts as a hard STOP gate: `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` appends a `claim_adjudication` event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree consults that event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`). A missing or failing packet vetoes STOP even when every other gate passes.\n359: \n360: Each new P0/P1 must carry a typed packet with the following required fields (see `../state/state_format.md` §9 for the full schema and a worked example):\n361: \n362: | Field | Type | Description |\n363: |-------|------|-------------|\n364: | `findingId` | string | Matches the finding ID in the iteration body |\n365: | `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes |\n366: | `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations (≥ 1) |\n367: | `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the orchestrator looked for contradicting evidence |\n368: | `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative explanation, even if rejected |\n369: | `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication |\n370: | `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Orchestrator confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n371: | `downgradeTrigger` | string | Concrete condition that would cause a future downgrade |\n372: | `transitions` | object[] | Optional, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n373: \n374: **Protocol**:\n375: \n376: 1. Re-read the cited evidence at the referenced file:line locations.\n377: 2. Seek counterevidence in adjacent code, docs, or prior iteration history.\n378: 3. Record an alternative explanation even if it is rejected.\n379: 4. Confirm or downgrade severity before the finding becomes convergence-visible.\n380: 5. Emit the typed packet inside the iteration file so `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` can parse it.\n381: \n382: **Failure semantics**: when any new P0/P1 finding is missing a packet or a required field, the workflow records `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. On the next loop, `step_check_convergence` step 0 (universal pre-check) routes STOP to `BLOCKED` with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet. Downgraded findings have their `finalSeverity` updated. The original severity is preserved in the iteration file for audit trail.\n383: \n384: #### Step 4b: Generate Dashboard\n385: \n386: Generate `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md` with review-specific sections:\n387: \n388: | Section | Content |\n389: |---------|---------|\n390: | Status | Provisional verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`/`PENDING`) and `hasAdvisories` flag |\n391: | Findings Summary | P0/P1/P2 counts with deltas from previous iteration |\n392: | Progress Table | Iteration number, focus dimension, `newFindingsRatio`, findings count, status |\n393: | Coverage | Files reviewed, dimensions completed, traceability protocol status |\n394: | Trend | Last 3 `newFindingsRatio` values with direction indicator (ascending/descending/flat) |\n395: | Active Risks | Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings |\n396: \n397: Dashboard behavior:\n398: - Auto-generated only -- never manually edited\n399: - Overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n400: - Non-blocking: if generation fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n401: - In **confirm mode**: displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate\n402: - In **auto mode**: written silently for post-hoc review\n403: \n404: #### Step 5: Loop Decision\n405: \n406: - If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n407: - If STUCK_RECOVERY: apply review-specific recovery strategies (see Section 3a), reset stuck count, continue\n408: - Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n409: \n410: ### Stuck Recovery (Review-Specific)\n411: \n412: **Threshold:** 2 consecutive no-progress iterations (`noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n413: \n414: | Failure Mode | Detection | Recovery Strategy |\n415: |-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n416: | Same dimension stuck | Last 2 iterations reviewed the same dimension with ratios `< 0.05` | **Change granularity**: if reviewing at file level, zoom into functions, if reviewing functions, zoom out to module level |\n417: | Traceability plateau | Required protocols remain partial while ratios stay `< 0.05` | **Protocol-first replay**: re-run the unresolved traceability protocol directly against the conflicting artifacts |\n418: | Low-value advisory churn | Last 2 iterations found only P2 work | **Escalate severity review**: explicitly search for P0/P1 patterns or downgrade unsupported severity claims |\n419: \n420: **Selection logic**:\n421: \n422: ```\n423: function selectReviewRecoveryStrategy(stuckIterations, state, config):\n424:   lastFocuses = [i.focus for i in stuckIterations[-2:]]\n425: \n426:   // Same dimension stuck? Change granularity\n427:   if len(set(lastFocuses)) <= 1:\n428:     return { strategy: \"change_granularity\", dimension: lastFocuses[0] }\n429: \n430:   // Required protocol plateau?\n431:   if hasRequiredProtocolPlateau(state.traceabilityChecks):\n432:     return { strategy: \"protocol_first_replay\" }\n433: \n434:   // Default: escalate severity\n435:   return { strategy: \"escalate_severity_review\" }\n436: ```\n437: \n438: **Recovery evaluation**:\n439: - If recovery iteration finds any new P0/P1 or materially advances required traceability coverage: recovery successful. Reset stuck count. Continue.\n440: - If recovery iteration finds only P2 or nothing: recovery failed. If all dimensions are already covered, exit to synthesis. Otherwise, move to the next unreviewed dimension.\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## 4. PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n445: \n446: ### Purpose\n447: \n448: Compile all iteration findings into the final `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md`. The synthesis phase owns the canonical review report output.\n449: \n450: ### Steps\n451: \n452: #### Step 1: Finding Registry Deduplication\n453: \n454: Consolidate findings across all iterations:\n455: \n456: 1. Read all iteration files: `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n457: 2. Group findings by file + line range + root cause\n458: 3. Merge duplicates, keeping the highest severity and all evidence\n459: 4. Assign final finding IDs: `F001`, `F002`, ...\n460: 5. Preserve the audit trail: note which iterations contributed to each merged finding\n461: \n462: #### Step 2: Severity Reconciliation\n463: \n464: Use adjudicated `finalSeverity` for any P0/P1 that was downgraded during claim adjudication (Step 4a of the iteration loop). The original severity from the iteration file is preserved in the audit appendix.\n465: \n466: #### Step 3: Replay Validation\n467: \n468: Recompute the convergence outcome from JSONL state before finalizing the report:\n469: \n470: 1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` and select review-mode iteration records in run order\n471: 2. Recompute `newFindingsRatio`, rolling-average votes, MAD votes, and coverage votes from stored JSONL fields only\n472: 3. Recompute `traceabilityChecks.summary` and confirm required protocol statuses match the recorded coverage vote\n473: 4. Re-run the evidence, scope, and coverage gates against stored findings and scope data\n474: 5. Compare the replayed decision and stop reason to the recorded synthesis event\n475: \n476: This synthesis-stage replay is a **full-history audit replay** over the stored JSONL state. It follows the same full-history replay discipline as the per-iteration reducer refresh above, but runs as an explicit pre-synthesis audit.\n477: \n478: Replay passes only when the recomputed decision, thresholds, and gate outcomes agree with the persisted result. If replay fails, log a warning in the audit appendix but proceed with synthesis.\n479: \n480: #### Step 4: Compile review-report.md\n481: \n482: Generate the 9 core review-report sections (defined in `review_mode_contract.yaml` under `outputs.reviewReport`) and insert `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` between `Traceability Status` and `Deferred Items` when `config.resource_map_present == true`:\n483: \n484: | # | Section | Purpose |\n485: |---|---------|---------|\n486: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` metadata |\n487: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n488: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduplicated active findings with evidence and final severity |\n489: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n490: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n491: | 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n492: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n493: | 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `config.resource_map_present == true`, reports touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n494: | 9 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n495: | 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, convergence evidence |\n496: \n497: #### Step 5: Verdict Determination\n498: \n499: Apply the verdict contract from `review_mode_contract.yaml`:\n500: \n501: | Verdict | Condition | Next Command |\n502: |---------|-----------|--------------|\n503: | **FAIL** | Active P0 remains OR any required binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n504: | **CONDITIONAL** | No active P0, but active P1 remains | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n505: | **PASS** | No active P0/P1 | `/create:changelog` |\n506: \n507: When `PASS` verdict is issued and active P2 findings remain, set `hasAdvisories = true` in the report metadata.\n508: \n509: #### Step 6: Finalize State\n510: \n511: 1. Update config status: Set `status: \"complete\"` in `deep-review-config.json`\n512: 2. Write final JSONL entry:\n513:    ```json\n514:    {\n515:      \"type\": \"event\",\n516:      \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\",\n517:      \"mode\": \"review\",\n518:      \"totalIterations\": N,\n519:      \"verdict\": \"PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL\",\n520:      \"activeP0\": N,\n521:      \"activeP1\": N,\n522:      \"activeP2\": N,\n523:      \"dimensionCoverage\": X,\n524:      \"stopReason\": \"...\",\n525:      \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n526:    }\n527:    ```\n528: \n529: ---\n530: \n531: ## 5. PHASE 4: SAVE\n532: \n533: ### Purpose\n534: \n535: Preserve review context to the memory system for future session recovery and cross-session continuity.\n536: \n537: ### Steps\n538: \n539: 1. **Compose context payload**: Create a structured JSON payload with the review summary, active findings, verdict, next action, and relevant artifacts. Use `specFolder` for the target packet and include curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` when available.\n540: \n541: 2. **Generate context**: Run the memory save script with structured JSON via `--stdin`, `--json`, or a session-scoped JSON file:\n542:    ```bash\n543:    node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --json '{\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"sessionSummary\":\"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict and findings.\"}' {spec_folder}\n544:    ```\n545: \n546: 3. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow.\n547: \n548: 4. **Verify**: Confirm the routed canonical spec document carries the review continuity update. Expected targets are `implementation-summary.md`, `decision-record.md`, or `handover.md`; standalone `memory/*.md` files are retired and should not be created.\n549: \n550: ### On Save Failure\n551: \n552: If memory save fails:\n553: - Preserve the current `review/` packet as backup (the disk state is the ground truth)\n554: - Log the error\n555: - The review results remain intact in `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md` regardless of memory save status\n556: \n557: ---\n558: \n559: ## 6. AUTO-RESUME PROTOCOL\n560: \n561: ### Purpose\n562: \n563: Enable review sessions to resume cleanly from prior state when interrupted by context compaction, process termination, or intentional pause.\n564: \n565: ### Resume Detection\n566: \n567: If state files already exist from a prior session:\n568: \n569: 1. **Verify agreement**: Confirm config, JSONL, findings registry, and strategy all exist and agree on target/spec folder\n570: 2. **Count progress**: Read JSONL, count iteration records, determine last completed iteration\n571: 3. **Read strategy**: Load current dimension progress, findings, and next focus from `deep-review-strategy.md`\n572: 4. **Set counter**: Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n573: 5. **Log resume**: Append the canonical resume event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The reducer requires every field below:\n574:    ```json\n575:    {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-24T14:05:00Z\"}\n576:    ```\n577: 6. **Continue**: Enter the iteration loop from step_read_state\n578: \n579: ### Lifecycle Branches (current release)\n580: \n581: The runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures. Until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n582: \n583: | Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n584: |------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n585: | `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n586: | `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n587: | `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `review/` tree moved under `review_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus non-null `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n588: \n589: **Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n590: \n591: ```json\n592: {\n593:   \"type\": \"event\",\n594:   \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n595:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n596:   \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n597:   \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n598:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n599:   \"generation\": <number>,\n600:   \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n601:   \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n602:   \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n603: }\n604: ```\n605: \n606: Every field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n607: \n608: ### State Validation on Resume\n609: \n610: | Condition | Classification | Action |\n611: |-----------|---------------|--------|\n612: | Config + JSONL + strategy all exist and agree | `resume` | Continue from last iteration + 1 |\n613: | All exist, config says `status: \"complete\"` | `completed-session` | Report completion, ask user if re-review desired |\n614: | Partial files or contradictions | `invalid-state` | Halt for repair, do not guess |\n615: | No files exist | `fresh` | Start new initialization |\n616: \n617: ### State Recovery Cascade\n618: \n619: When state files are missing or corrupted, apply this priority cascade:\n620: \n621: | Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n622: |----------|-----------|----------------|\n623: | 1 | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation |\n624: | 2 | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract dimensions, findings, coverage |\n625: | 3 | JSONL missing, iteration files exist | Scan `review/iterations/iteration-*.md`, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n626: | 4 | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase |\n627: | 5 | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n628: \n629: Each priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next.\n630: \n631: ---\n632: \n633: ## 7. PAUSE/RESUME\n634: \n635: ### Pause Sentinel Behavior\n636: \n637: The pause sentinel provides graceful loop suspension in autonomous mode without killing the process.\n638: \n639: ### Creating a Pause\n640: \n641: Create the sentinel file at any time:\n642: \n643: ```bash\n644: touch {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n645: ```\n646: \n647: The orchestrator checks for this file between iterations (Step 2a). When detected:\n648: - The current iteration is allowed to complete\n649: - The loop halts before dispatching the next iteration\n650: - A paused event is logged to JSONL\n651: - The user is notified with current state (iteration count, dimensions covered, findings)\n652: \n653: ### Resuming After Pause\n654: \n655: Delete the sentinel file and restart the workflow:\n656: \n657: ```bash\n658: rm {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n659: ```\n660: \n661: On the next invocation:\n662: - The auto-resume protocol (Section 6) detects the existing state\n663: - A resumed event is logged to JSONL\n664: - The loop continues from the next iteration\n665: \n666: ### Confirm Mode Approval Gates\n667: \n668: In confirm mode (`deep_review_confirm.yaml`), the workflow adds explicit approval gates instead of relying on the pause sentinel:\n669: \n670: | Gate Location | Behavior |\n671: |---------------|----------|\n672: | After initialization | Show config, strategy, and scope. Wait for approval |\n673: | After each iteration | Show iteration findings, dashboard, and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n674: | Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n675: | After synthesis | Show final review-report.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n676: \n677: ---\n678: \n679: ## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS, ERROR HANDLING, AND QUALITY GATES\n680: \n681: State-transition rules, error handling, and the review quality gates live in `loop_state_and_gates.md` for navigability.\n682: \n683: ---\n684: \n685: ## 11. RELATED RESOURCES\n686: \n687: ### Shared Protocol Documentation\n688: \n689: Protocol documents from `deep-research` are cross-referenced, not duplicated:\n690: \n691: | Document | Path | Purpose |\n692: |----------|------|---------|\n693: | Loop Protocol (research) | `../deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` | Research loop lifecycle (this file adapts Section 9) |\n694: | State Format | `../deep-research/references/state/state_format.md` | JSONL, strategy, and config schemas |\n695: | Convergence | `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` | `shouldContinue_review()` (Section 10), stuck recovery, quality guards |\n696: \n697: ### Review-Specific Resources\n698: \n699: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n700: |----------|------|---------|\n701: | Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n702: | Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n703: | Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n704: | Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n705: | Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n706: \n707: ### Workflow Files\n708: \n709: | Mode | Path |\n710: |------|------|\n711: | Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` |\n712: | Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` |\n713: \n714: ### Agent\n715: \n716: | Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n717: |-------|-------------|------------|\n718: | `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |\n719: \n720: Runtime paths:\n721: - OpenCode / Copilot: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md`\n722: - Claude: `.claude/agents/deep-review.md`\n723: - Codex: `.codex/agents/deep-review.toml`\n724: \n725: ---\n726: \n727: ## Executor Selection Contract\n728: \n729: Executor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta.\n730: \n731: ### Invariants\n732: \n733: Every executor path MUST satisfy:\n734: \n735: 1. Produce an iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}` (non-empty).\n736: 2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n737: 3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops. Max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n738: \n739: ### Failure Modes\n740: \n741: - Missing iteration file: `iteration_file_missing` from `post-dispatch-validate.ts`, emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event.\n742: - Empty iteration file: `iteration_file_empty`, same downstream.\n743: - JSONL not appended: `jsonl_not_appended`.\n744: - JSONL missing required fields: `jsonl_missing_fields`.\n745: - JSONL malformed: `jsonl_parse_error`.\n746: - 3 consecutive failures: existing `stuck_recovery` event (unchanged).\n747: \n748: ### JSONL Audit Field\n749: \n750: Non-native executor runs append an `executor` block with model and runtime settings to the iteration's JSONL record via `executor-audit.ts`. Native runs are recoverable from YAML alone.\n751: \n752: ### Template And Config Surface\n753: \n754: The executor-agnostic iteration prompt lives at `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, rendered by `prompt-pack.ts` before dispatch and either injected as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\n755: \n756: ### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\n757: \n758: - YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\n759: - `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\n760: - Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\n761: - The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\n762: \n763: ### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n764: \n765: On this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\n\n(End of file - total 765 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n  - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n  - \"review loop initialization\"\n  - \"review auto resume\"\n  - \"review synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n  - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n  - \"review loop initialization\"\n  - \"review auto resume\"\n  - \"review synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n- Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n- Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n- Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n│              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n│ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n│ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n│ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n│ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n│ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n│              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n└──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n### Core Innovation\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n\n### Key References\n\n| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n| Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n| Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\n\nSet up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n\n2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n\n3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n\n   | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n   |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n   | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n   | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n   | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n   | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n   | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n\n   Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n\n4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n\n   | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n   |----------|-----------|-----------|\n   | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n   | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n   | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n   | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n\n   Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n\n5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n\n   | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n   |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n   | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n   | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n   | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n   | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n   | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n   | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n\n   Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n\n6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n\n7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n\n8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n\n9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n   - Topic (review target description)\n   - Review Dimensions checklist\n   - Files Under Review table\n   - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n   - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n   - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n   - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n   - Review Boundaries from config\n9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n   - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n\n10. **Validate review charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n\n11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n\n### Outputs\n\n| File | Location | Purpose |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n| State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n| Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n| Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n\n- Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n- Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n- Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n\nReducer contract for every loop refresh:\n\n| Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n|--------------|-----------------|-------|\n| Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n| Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n| Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\n\nRun `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n\n- Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n- Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n- Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n  - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n  - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n  - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n  - Required traceability protocols are covered\n  - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n- Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n\nIf convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n- `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n- `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n\nThe blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n\nConvergence signals and weights:\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n\n**P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```\n     Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n\nNormalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\nIteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\nTarget: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\nDimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\nFindings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\nTraceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nProvisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n\nDispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n\n```\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nReview Target: {config.reviewTarget}\nReview Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\nFocus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\nRemaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}\nTraceability Protocols:\n  - Core: {core_protocols}\n  - Overlay: {overlay_protocols}\nActive Findings: {findingsSummary}\nState Files:\n  - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\n  - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\n  - Registry: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\n  - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\nOutput: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\nCONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\nCONSTRAINT: Target files are READ-ONLY -- never modify code under review\n```\n\n#### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n\nBefore dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n\n- `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-review` agent with model Opus.\n- `cli-codex` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `codex exec --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n- `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only). We override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n\nAll branches share:\n1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n\nPer-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n\nCross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope. See the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n\nFailure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n\n**Agent constraints**:\n- `@deep-review` is LEAF-only: it cannot dispatch sub-agents\n- No WebFetch: review is code-only and read-only\n- Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle\n- Tools available: Read, Grep, Glob, Edit (state files only), code_graph_query + Grep\n\n#### Step 3a: Cross-Reference Protocol Execution\n\nDuring iterations focused on the Traceability dimension, the agent executes applicable cross-reference protocols. Each protocol produces a structured result appended to the JSONL `traceabilityChecks.results[]` array.\n\n| Protocol | Execution | Expected Output |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| `spec_code` | Compare normative claims in spec.md against shipped implementation | Pass/partial/fail per claim with file:line evidence |\n| `checklist_evidence` | Verify every `[x]` mark in checklist.md has supporting evidence | Pass/partial/fail per checked item |\n| `skill_agent` | Compare SKILL.md contracts against runtime agent definitions | Agreement/drift/disagreement per capability |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | Compare agent definitions across runtimes (.opencode, .claude, .codex) | Parity/drift/divergence per runtime pair |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | Compare catalog claims against discoverable implementation | Match/stale/missing per feature |\n| `playbook_capability` | Validate playbook scenarios against executable reality | Executable/needs-update/impossible per scenario |\n\nEach protocol result includes:\n- `protocolId`: Protocol identifier\n- `status`: `pass`, `partial`, or `fail`\n- `gateClass`: `hard` or `advisory`\n- `applicable`: Whether the protocol applies to this target type\n- `counts`: `{ pass, partial, fail, skipped }`\n- `evidence`: Array of file:line citations\n- `findingRefs`: Array of finding IDs generated from this protocol\n- `summary`: Human-readable summary text\n\n#### Step 3b: Resource Map Coverage Audit\n\nWhen `config.resource_map_present == true`, at least one loop iteration MUST audit implementation-vs-resource-map coverage:\n\n1. Read `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`\n2. Read applied reports under `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md`\n3. Cross-check `target_files` from the applied reports against resource-map entries\n4. Classify outcomes into:\n   - entries touched\n   - entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`)\n   - implementation paths absent from the map\n5. Emit any resulting findings with category `resource-map-coverage`\n\nWhen `config.resource_map_present == false`, skip this audit and rely on the `Known Context` note: `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate`.\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n\nAfter agent completes:\n\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with review iteration fields:\n   - `dimensions` (array of dimensions covered)\n   - `filesReviewed` (array of file paths)\n   - `findingsSummary` (cumulative P0/P1/P2 counts)\n   - `findingsNew` (this iteration's new findings)\n   - `traceabilityChecks` (protocol results if applicable)\n3. Verify strategy.md was updated (dimension progress, findings count, protocol status)\n4. Extract `newFindingsRatio` from JSONL record\n5. Update stuck tracking using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`:\n   - Skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change)\n   - Reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress)\n   - Increment if `newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold`\n   - Reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Claim Adjudication\n\nBefore the next convergence pass, the orchestrator adjudicates every new P0/P1 finding with a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. This step prevents false positives from inflating severity and distorting convergence, AND acts as a hard STOP gate: `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` appends a `claim_adjudication` event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree consults that event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`). A missing or failing packet vetoes STOP even when every other gate passes.\n\nEach new P0/P1 must carry a typed packet with the following required fields (see `../state/state_format.md` §9 for the full schema and a worked example):\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `findingId` | string | Matches the finding ID in the iteration body |\n| `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes |\n| `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations (≥ 1) |\n| `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the orchestrator looked for contradicting evidence |\n| `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative explanation, even if rejected |\n| `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication |\n| `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Orchestrator confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n| `downgradeTrigger` | string | Concrete condition that would cause a future downgrade |\n| `transitions` | object[] | Optional, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n\n**Protocol**:\n\n1. Re-read the cited evidence at the referenced file:line locations.\n2. Seek counterevidence in adjacent code, docs, or prior iteration history.\n3. Record an alternative explanation even if it is rejected.\n4. Confirm or downgrade severity before the finding becomes convergence-visible.\n5. Emit the typed packet inside the iteration file so `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` can parse it.\n\n**Failure semantics**: when any new P0/P1 finding is missing a packet or a required field, the workflow records `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. On the next loop, `step_check_convergence` step 0 (universal pre-check) routes STOP to `BLOCKED` with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet. Downgraded findings have their `finalSeverity` updated. The original severity is preserved in the iteration file for audit trail.\n\n#### Step 4b: Generate Dashboard\n\nGenerate `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md` with review-specific sections:\n\n| Section | Content |\n|---------|---------|\n| Status | Provisional verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`/`PENDING`) and `hasAdvisories` flag |\n| Findings Summary | P0/P1/P2 counts with deltas from previous iteration |\n| Progress Table | Iteration number, focus dimension, `newFindingsRatio`, findings count, status |\n| Coverage | Files reviewed, dimensions completed, traceability protocol status |\n| Trend | Last 3 `newFindingsRatio` values with direction indicator (ascending/descending/flat) |\n| Active Risks | Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings |\n\nDashboard behavior:\n- Auto-generated only -- never manually edited\n- Overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n- Non-blocking: if generation fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n- In **confirm mode**: displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate\n- In **auto mode**: written silently for post-hoc review\n\n#### Step 5: Loop Decision\n\n- If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n- If STUCK_RECOVERY: apply review-specific recovery strategies (see Section 3a), reset stuck count, continue\n- Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n\n### Stuck Recovery (Review-Specific)\n\n**Threshold:** 2 consecutive no-progress iterations (`noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n\n| Failure Mode | Detection | Recovery Strategy |\n|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| Same dimension stuck | Last 2 iterations reviewed the same dimension with ratios `< 0.05` | **Change granularity**: if reviewing at file level, zoom into functions, if reviewing functions, zoom out to module level |\n| Traceability plateau | Required protocols remain partial while ratios stay `< 0.05` | **Protocol-first replay**: re-run the unresolved traceability protocol directly against the conflicting artifacts |\n| Low-value advisory churn | Last 2 iterations found only P2 work | **Escalate severity review**: explicitly search for P0/P1 patterns or downgrade unsupported severity claims |\n\n**Selection logic**:\n\n```\nfunction selectReviewRecoveryStrategy(stuckIterations, state, config):\n  lastFocuses = [i.focus for i in stuckIterations[-2:]]\n\n  // Same dimension stuck? Change granularity\n  if len(set(lastFocuses)) <= 1:\n    return { strategy: \"change_granularity\", dimension: lastFocuses[0] }\n\n  // Required protocol plateau?\n  if hasRequiredProtocolPlateau(state.traceabilityChecks):\n    return { strategy: \"protocol_first_replay\" }\n\n  // Default: escalate severity\n  return { strategy: \"escalate_severity_review\" }\n```\n\n**Recovery evaluation**:\n- If recovery iteration finds any new P0/P1 or materially advances required traceability coverage: recovery successful. Reset stuck count. Continue.\n- If recovery iteration finds only P2 or nothing: recovery failed. If all dimensions are already covered, exit to synthesis. Otherwise, move to the next unreviewed dimension.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\n\nCompile all iteration findings into the final `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md`. The synthesis phase owns the canonical review report output.\n\n### Steps\n\n#### Step 1: Finding Registry Deduplication\n\nConsolidate findings across all iterations:\n\n1. Read all iteration files: `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. Group findings by file + line range + root cause\n3. Merge duplicates, keeping the highest severity and all evidence\n4. Assign final finding IDs: `F001`, `F002`, ...\n5. Preserve the audit trail: note which iterations contributed to each merged finding\n\n#### Step 2: Severity Reconciliation\n\nUse adjudicated `finalSeverity` for any P0/P1 that was downgraded during claim adjudication (Step 4a of the iteration loop). The original severity from the iteration file is preserved in the audit appendix.\n\n#### Step 3: Replay Validation\n\nRecompute the convergence outcome from JSONL state before finalizing the report:\n\n1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` and select review-mode iteration records in run order\n2. Recompute `newFindingsRatio`, rolling-average votes, MAD votes, and coverage votes from stored JSONL fields only\n3. Recompute `traceabilityChecks.summary` and confirm required protocol statuses match the recorded coverage vote\n4. Re-run the evidence, scope, and coverage gates against stored findings and scope data\n5. Compare the replayed decision and stop reason to the recorded synthesis event\n\nThis synthesis-stage replay is a **full-history audit replay** over the stored JSONL state. It follows the same full-history replay discipline as the per-iteration reducer refresh above, but runs as an explicit pre-synthesis audit.\n\nReplay passes only when the recomputed decision, thresholds, and gate outcomes agree with the persisted result. If replay fails, log a warning in the audit appendix but proceed with synthesis.\n\n#### Step 4: Compile review-report.md\n\nGenerate the 9 core review-report sections (defined in `review_mode_contract.yaml` under `outputs.reviewReport`) and insert `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` between `Traceability Status` and `Deferred Items` when `config.resource_map_present == true`:\n\n| # | Section | Purpose |\n|---|---------|---------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` metadata |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduplicated active findings with evidence and final severity |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n| 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `config.resource_map_present == true`, reports touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n| 9 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n| 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, convergence evidence |\n\n#### Step 5: Verdict Determination\n\nApply the verdict contract from `review_mode_contract.yaml`:\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Next Command |\n|---------|-----------|--------------|\n| **FAIL** | Active P0 remains OR any required binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | No active P0, but active P1 remains | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n| **PASS** | No active P0/P1 | `/create:changelog` |\n\nWhen `PASS` verdict is issued and active P2 findings remain, set `hasAdvisories = true` in the report metadata.\n\n#### Step 6: Finalize State\n\n1. Update config status: Set `status: \"complete\"` in `deep-review-config.json`\n2. Write final JSONL entry:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"type\": \"event\",\n     \"event\": \"synthesis_complete\",\n     \"mode\": \"review\",\n     \"totalIterations\": N,\n     \"verdict\": \"PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL\",\n     \"activeP0\": N,\n     \"activeP1\": N,\n     \"activeP2\": N,\n     \"dimensionCoverage\": X,\n     \"stopReason\": \"...\",\n     \"timestamp\": \"...\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## 5. PHASE 4: SAVE\n\n### Purpose\n\nPreserve review context to the memory system for future session recovery and cross-session continuity.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Compose context payload**: Create a structured JSON payload with the review summary, active findings, verdict, next action, and relevant artifacts. Use `specFolder` for the target packet and include curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` when available.\n\n2. **Generate context**: Run the memory save script with structured JSON via `--stdin`, `--json`, or a session-scoped JSON file:\n   ```bash\n   node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --json '{\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"sessionSummary\":\"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict and findings.\"}' {spec_folder}\n   ```\n\n3. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow.\n\n4. **Verify**: Confirm the routed canonical spec document carries the review continuity update. Expected targets are `implementation-summary.md`, `decision-record.md`, or `handover.md`; standalone `memory/*.md` files are retired and should not be created.\n\n### On Save Failure\n\nIf memory save fails:\n- Preserve the current `review/` packet as backup (the disk state is the ground truth)\n- Log the error\n- The review results remain intact in `{artifact_dir}/review-report.md` regardless of memory save status\n\n---\n\n## 6. AUTO-RESUME PROTOCOL\n\n### Purpose\n\nEnable review sessions to resume cleanly from prior state when interrupted by context compaction, process termination, or intentional pause.\n\n### Resume Detection\n\nIf state files already exist from a prior session:\n\n1. **Verify agreement**: Confirm config, JSONL, findings registry, and strategy all exist and agree on target/spec folder\n2. **Count progress**: Read JSONL, count iteration records, determine last completed iteration\n3. **Read strategy**: Load current dimension progress, findings, and next focus from `deep-review-strategy.md`\n4. **Set counter**: Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n5. **Log resume**: Append the canonical resume event to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The reducer requires every field below:\n   ```json\n   {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-24T14:05:00Z\"}\n   ```\n6. **Continue**: Enter the iteration loop from step_read_state\n\n### Lifecycle Branches (current release)\n\nThe runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures. Until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n\n| Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n|------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n| `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n| `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n| `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `review/` tree moved under `review_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus non-null `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n\n**Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n  \"generation\": <number>,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n  \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n}\n```\n\nEvery field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n\n### State Validation on Resume\n\n| Condition | Classification | Action |\n|-----------|---------------|--------|\n| Config + JSONL + strategy all exist and agree | `resume` | Continue from last iteration + 1 |\n| All exist, config says `status: \"complete\"` | `completed-session` | Report completion, ask user if re-review desired |\n| Partial files or contradictions | `invalid-state` | Halt for repair, do not guess |\n| No files exist | `fresh` | Start new initialization |\n\n### State Recovery Cascade\n\nWhen state files are missing or corrupted, apply this priority cascade:\n\n| Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation |\n| 2 | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract dimensions, findings, coverage |\n| 3 | JSONL missing, iteration files exist | Scan `review/iterations/iteration-*.md`, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n| 4 | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase |\n| 5 | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n\nEach priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PAUSE/RESUME\n\n### Pause Sentinel Behavior\n\nThe pause sentinel provides graceful loop suspension in autonomous mode without killing the process.\n\n### Creating a Pause\n\nCreate the sentinel file at any time:\n\n```bash\ntouch {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n```\n\nThe orchestrator checks for this file between iterations (Step 2a). When detected:\n- The current iteration is allowed to complete\n- The loop halts before dispatching the next iteration\n- A paused event is logged to JSONL\n- The user is notified with current state (iteration count, dimensions covered, findings)\n\n### Resuming After Pause\n\nDelete the sentinel file and restart the workflow:\n\n```bash\nrm {artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\n```\n\nOn the next invocation:\n- The auto-resume protocol (Section 6) detects the existing state\n- A resumed event is logged to JSONL\n- The loop continues from the next iteration\n\n### Confirm Mode Approval Gates\n\nIn confirm mode (`deep_review_confirm.yaml`), the workflow adds explicit approval gates instead of relying on the pause sentinel:\n\n| Gate Location | Behavior |\n|---------------|----------|\n| After initialization | Show config, strategy, and scope. Wait for approval |\n| After each iteration | Show iteration findings, dashboard, and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n| Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n| After synthesis | Show final review-report.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS, ERROR HANDLING, AND QUALITY GATES\n\nState-transition rules, error handling, and the review quality gates live in `loop_state_and_gates.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## 11. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Shared Protocol Documentation\n\nProtocol documents from `deep-research` are cross-referenced, not duplicated:\n\n| Document | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Loop Protocol (research) | `../deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` | Research loop lifecycle (this file adapts Section 9) |\n| State Format | `../deep-research/references/state/state_format.md` | JSONL, strategy, and config schemas |\n| Convergence | `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` | `shouldContinue_review()` (Section 10), stuck recovery, quality guards |\n\n### Review-Specific Resources\n\n| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review Contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Single source of truth for dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Quick Reference | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` | One-page review cheat sheet |\n| Strategy Template | `assets/deep_review_strategy.md` | Template for review strategy files |\n| Config Template | `assets/deep_review_config.json` | Template for review config files |\n| Dashboard Template | `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md` | Template for auto-generated dashboard |\n\n### Workflow Files\n\n| Mode | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Auto (unattended) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm (step-by-step) | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` |\n\n### Agent\n\n| Agent | Path Pattern | Constraint |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| `@deep-review` | `{runtime_dir}/deep-review.{ext}` | LEAF-only, no sub-agents, no WebFetch, target files read-only |\n\nRuntime paths:\n- OpenCode / Copilot: `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md`\n- Claude: `.claude/agents/deep-review.md`\n- Codex: `.codex/agents/deep-review.toml`\n\n---\n\n## Executor Selection Contract\n\nExecutor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta.\n\n### Invariants\n\nEvery executor path MUST satisfy:\n\n1. Produce an iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}` (non-empty).\n2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops. Max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n\n### Failure Modes\n\n- Missing iteration file: `iteration_file_missing` from `post-dispatch-validate.ts`, emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event.\n- Empty iteration file: `iteration_file_empty`, same downstream.\n- JSONL not appended: `jsonl_not_appended`.\n- JSONL missing required fields: `jsonl_missing_fields`.\n- JSONL malformed: `jsonl_parse_error`.\n- 3 consecutive failures: existing `stuck_recovery` event (unchanged).\n\n### JSONL Audit Field\n\nNon-native executor runs append an `executor` block with model and runtime settings to the iteration's JSONL record via `executor-audit.ts`. Native runs are recoverable from YAML alone.\n\n### Template And Config Surface\n\nThe executor-agnostic iteration prompt lives at `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, rendered by `prompt-pack.ts` before dispatch and either injected as the agent's context (native) or piped to `codex exec` stdin (cli-codex). Config is in `assets/deep_review_config.json` under the `executor` key; schema in `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. CLI flag precedence: `--executor/--model/--reasoning-effort/--service-tier/--executor-timeout > config file > schema default`.\n\n### What Never Changes Regardless Of Executor Route\n\n- YAML owns state (`deep-review-state.jsonl`, strategy.md, registry, dashboard).\n- `reduce-state.cjs` is the single state writer.\n- Convergence detection, lifecycle events (new/resume/restart), the review dimensions pass, and stuck_recovery stay YAML-driven.\n- The `@deep-review` LEAF agent definition is untouched: it is the native executor, not the only one.\n\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n\nOn this skill surface, the live code-graph readiness contract only reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`. The values `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility and downstream schema stability, but the seven code-graph handlers and readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":765,"totalLines":765,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1781756132735,"end":1781756132745}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370e49cc88191baad2e325cf145d4"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0fd7e00146v1RZo6lG9JTf","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756132774,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MSS45l7yvYQIQG7U7lco9m0x","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review State Format\n3: description: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state format\"\n6:   - \"deep review config schema\"\n7:   - \"review severity weights\"\n8:   - \"file protection levels\"\n9:   - \"review iteration file structure\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review State Format\n15: \n16: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: The deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n23: \n24: | File | Format | Mutability |\n25: |------|--------|------------|\n26: | `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n27: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n28: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n29: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n30: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n31: | `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n32: | `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n33: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n34: \n35: ```text\n36: {artifact_dir}/\n37:   deep-review-config.json\n38:   deep-review-state.jsonl\n39:   deep-review-findings-registry.json\n40:   deep-review-strategy.md\n41:   deep-review-dashboard.md\n42:   .deep-review-pause\n43:   review-report.md\n44:   iterations/\n45:     iteration-001.md\n46:     iteration-002.md\n47:     ...\n48: ```\n49: \n50: `{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet).\n51: \n52: ### When to Use\n53: \n54: - Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n55: - Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n56: - Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n57: - Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n62: \n63: Created during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n64: \n65: ```json\n66: {\n67:   \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n68:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n69:   \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n70:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n71:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n72:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n73:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n74:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n75:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n76:   \"generation\": 1,\n77:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n78:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n79:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n80:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n81:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n82:   \"crossReference\": {\n83:     \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n84:     \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n85:   },\n86:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n87:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n88:   \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n89:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n90:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n91:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n92:   \"fileProtection\": {\n93:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n94:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n95:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n96:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n97:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n98:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n99:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n100:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n101:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n102:   },\n103:   \"reducer\": {\n104:     \"enabled\": true,\n105:     \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n106:     \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n107:     \"metrics\": [\n108:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n109:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n110:       \"openFindings\",\n111:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n112:       \"convergenceScore\"\n113:     ]\n114:   }\n115: }\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ### Field Reference\n119: \n120: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n121: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n122: | mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n123: | reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n124: | reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n125: | reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n126: | resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n127: | sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n128: | parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n129: | lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n130: | generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n131: | continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n132: | maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n133: | convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n134: | stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n135: | severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n136: | crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n137: | qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n138: | specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n139: | status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n140: | releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n141: | fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n142: | reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n143: \n144: ### File Protection Levels\n145: \n146: | Level | Meaning |\n147: |-------|---------|\n148: | immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n149: | append-only | New content added at end only |\n150: | mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n151: | write-once | Created once, never modified |\n152: | auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n153: | operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n154: \n155: ### Review Dimensions\n156: \n157: | Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n158: |-----------|----------|---------------------|\n159: | correctness | 1 | Yes |\n160: | security | 2 | Yes |\n161: | traceability | 3 | Yes |\n162: | maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n163: \n164: ### Severity Weights\n165: \n166: | Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n167: |----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n168: | P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n169: | P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n170: | P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## 3. STATE LOG\n175: \n176: The `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n181: \n182: Updated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n183: \n184: ### Required Sections\n185: \n186: | Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n187: |---------|-----------|---------|\n188: | topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n189: | review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n190: | completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n191: | running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n192: | what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n193: | what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n194: | exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n195: | ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n196: | next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n197: | known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n198: | cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n199: | files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n200: | review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n201: \n202: ### Mapping from Research Mode\n203: \n204: | Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n205: |---------------|-------------------|\n206: | review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n207: | completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n208: | running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n209: | cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n210: | files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n211: | review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n212: \n213: Sections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n214: \n215: ### Update Protocol\n216: \n217: 1. Read current strategy file\n218: 2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n219: 3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n220: 4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n221: 5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n222: 6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n227: \n228: Reducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n229: \n230: ```json\n231: {\n232:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n233:   \"generation\": 1,\n234:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n235:   \"openFindings\": [],\n236:   \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n237:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n238:   \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n239:   \"severityChanged\": [],\n240:   \"repeatedFindings\": [],\n241:   \"dimensionCoverage\": {\n242:     \"correctness\": true,\n243:     \"security\": true,\n244:     \"traceability\": false,\n245:     \"maintainability\": false\n246:   },\n247:   \"findingsBySeverity\": {\n248:     \"P0\": 0,\n249:     \"P1\": 1,\n250:     \"P2\": 2\n251:   },\n252:   \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n253:   \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n254:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n255:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n256:   \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n257:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n258:   \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n259: }\n260: ```\n261: \n262: This file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n263: \n264: ### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n265: \n266: | Field | Type | Description |\n267: |-------|------|-------------|\n268: | `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |\n269: | `persistentSameSeverity` | array | Findings observed in ≥2 iterations with NO severity transitions beyond initial discovery. REQ-018 split of the deprecated `repeatedFindings` bucket. |\n270: | `severityChanged` | array | Findings that went through at least one severity transition (P0↔P1↔P2) in their `transitions` history. |\n271: | `repeatedFindings` | array | **Deprecated.** Union of `persistentSameSeverity` and `severityChanged`. Retained for backward compatibility, new code should read the split arrays. |\n272: | `corruptionWarnings` | array | Per-line corruption reports from `parseJsonlDetailed()`: `{line, raw, error}`. Non-empty means the reducer detected malformed JSONL. |\n273: \n274: ### Default Values\n275: \n276: When no `graph_convergence` event has been recorded yet, defaults are `graphConvergenceScore: 0`, `graphDecision: null`, and `graphBlockers: []`.\n277: When no `blocked_stop` event has been recorded yet, `blockedStopHistory: []`.\n278: When JSONL parses cleanly, `corruptionWarnings: []`.\n279: \n280: ### Fail-Closed Semantics (REQ-015, REQ-016)\n281: \n282: - **Malformed JSONL**: The reducer CLI exits with code `2` and writes a warning to stderr when `corruptionWarnings.length > 0`. Pass `--lenient` (or `lenient:true` to `reduceReviewState`) to escape-hatch out and preserve the v1.2.0.0 fail-open behavior for legacy packets.\n283: - **Missing machine-owned anchors**: `replaceAnchorSection()` throws `Error('Missing machine-owned anchor \"<id>\" in deep-review strategy file.')` when the strategy file is present but lacks one of the required anchors. Pass `--create-missing-anchors` (or `createMissingAnchors:true`) to bootstrap empty strategy files by appending the missing anchor blocks.\n284: - **Dashboard surfaces**: `CORRUPTION WARNINGS` section lists detected lines. `BLOCKED STOPS` section lists `blockedStopHistory` entries. `GRAPH CONVERGENCE` section reports `graphConvergenceScore` / `graphDecision` / `graphBlockers`.\n285: - **Strategy next-focus override**: When the latest `blocked_stop` event timestamp is newer than the latest iteration timestamp, the reducer rewrites the strategy `next-focus` anchor to surface the blocking gates and recovery hint so operators see the blocker before choosing the next iteration direction.\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ## 6. ITERATION FILES (review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md)\n290: \n291: Write-once files. One per iteration, zero-padded 3-digit naming.\n292: \n293: ### Structure\n294: \n295: ```markdown\n296: # Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n297: \n298: ## Focus\n299: [Dimension(s), files, scope investigated]\n300: \n301: ## Scorecard\n302: - Dimensions covered: [list]\n303: - Files reviewed: [count]\n304: - New findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n305: - Refined findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n306: - New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n307: \n308: ## Findings\n309: \n310: ### P0, Blocker\n311: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n312: \n313: ### P1, Required\n314: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n315: \n316: ### P2, Suggestion\n317: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n318: \n319: ## Cross-Reference Results\n320: | Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n321: |----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n322: | spec_code | pass/partial/fail | hard | file:line | ... |\n323: \n324: ## Assessment\n325: - New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n326: - Dimensions addressed: [list]\n327: - Novelty justification: [breakdown]\n328: \n329: ## Ruled Out\n330: - [Approach]: [Why], [Evidence]\n331: \n332: ## Dead Ends\n333: - [Direction]: [Why]\n334: \n335: ## Recommended Next Focus\n336: [What to investigate next]\n337: ```\n338: \n339: Every finding must include: unique ID (`F001`...), severity (`P0`/`P1`/`P2`), concrete `file:line` evidence, and dimension tag.\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## 7. REVIEW REPORT (review/review-report.md)\n344: \n345: The review synthesis output contains 9 core sections plus a conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present` is true:\n346: \n347: | # | Section | Description |\n348: |---|---------|-------------|\n349: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` flag |\n350: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why result routes to planning or changelog |\n351: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence, severity, dimension |\n352: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Ordered lanes grouped by dependency or area |\n353: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec updates implied by findings |\n354: | 6 | Plan Seed | Initial remediation tasks from findings |\n355: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol outcomes and gaps |\n356: | 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` existed at init, contains touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n357: | 9 | Deferred Items | Advisory findings, blocked items, follow-up checks |\n358: | 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, convergence replay, audit detail |\n359: \n360: **Executive Summary** includes verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`), active finding counts, `hasAdvisories` boolean (PASS + P2 > 0), scope description, and convergence reason.\n361: \n362: **Planning Trigger** routes FAIL/CONDITIONAL to remediation planning, PASS to changelog creation.\n363: \n364: **Active Finding Registry** lists each active finding with findingId, severity, dimension, title, file:line evidence, first/last seen iteration, and status.\n365: \n366: **Remediation Workstreams** group related findings into ordered lanes with constituent finding IDs and execution order.\n367: \n368: **Spec Seed / Plan Seed** provide minimal spec updates and initial remediation tasks referencing finding IDs and target files.\n369: \n370: **Traceability Status** reports per-protocol pass/partial/fail with gating class and evidence.\n371: \n372: **Resource Map Coverage Gate** is emitted only when `resource_map_present` is true and MUST contain exactly three bullets: touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n373: \n374: **Deferred Items** captures advisory findings, blocked protocols, and future follow-up checks.\n375: \n376: **Audit Appendix** contains iteration table, convergence signal replay, file coverage matrix, and dimension breakdown.\n377: \n378: ---\n379: \n380: ## 8. DASHBOARD (review/deep-review-dashboard.md)\n381: \n382: Auto-generated summary. Never manually edited.\n383: \n384: - **Path**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n385: - **Generated from**: JSONL state log + strategy + findings registry\n386: - **Refresh**: Regenerated after every iteration\n387: - **Protection**: `auto-generated` in fileProtection\n388: \n389: ### Sections\n390: \n391: | Section | Source | Description |\n392: |---------|--------|-------------|\n393: | Findings Summary | JSONL | Active P0/P1/P2 counts, new vs refined |\n394: | Progress Table | JSONL | Run, status, focus, dimensions, ratio, duration |\n395: | Coverage | Strategy + JSONL | Dimension completion, file coverage, protocol status |\n396: | Trend | JSONL signals | Rolling average, composite stop score, trajectory |\n397: \n398: **Rules:** Sole inputs are JSONL + strategy. Overwrite entirely on refresh. Read-only for all agents.\n399: \n400: ---\n401: \n402: ## 9. CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n403: \n404: Every new P0/P1 finding must carry a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. The packet is parsed by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` in the review workflow and its pass/fail result is persisted as a `claim_adjudication` event in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree reads the latest event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`), a missing or failed packet vetoes STOP even if every other gate passes. Prose-only adjudication blocks are no longer accepted.\n405: \n406: ### Typed Packet Schema (required)\n407: \n408: Embed the packet inside the iteration file for each new P0/P1 finding. The orchestrator parses it after evaluation and persists the validation result.\n409: \n410: ```json\n411: {\n412:   \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n413:   \"claim\": \"Coverage-graph upsert identity is bare `id`, so cross-session collisions overwrite prior rows.\",\n414:   \"evidenceRefs\": [\n415:     \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154\",\n416:     \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302\"\n417:   ],\n418:   \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Grepped the module for compound-key upserts, checked migration scripts, and inspected session-isolation.vitest.ts for a collision regression, none found.\",\n419:   \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be intentional single-tenant design, but REQ-024 explicitly requires session isolation, so this is rejected.\",\n420:   \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n421:   \"confidence\": 0.86,\n422:   \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a composite primary key `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` lands and a collision regression covers the ID-reuse path, downgrade to P2 tech-debt.\",\n423:   \"transitions\": [\n424:     { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" }\n425:   ]\n426: }\n427: ```\n428: \n429: ### Required Fields\n430: \n431: | Field | Type | Description |\n432: |-------|------|-------------|\n433: | `findingId` | string | Must match the finding ID in the iteration body and registry |\n434: | `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes (one sentence, evidence-backed) |\n435: | `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations that substantiate the claim (at least one entry) |\n436: | `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the reviewer looked for contradicting evidence (commands, paths, docs), blank string is not acceptable |\n437: | `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative reading of the evidence, even if the reviewer rejects it |\n438: | `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication (may differ from the severity originally asserted) |\n439: | `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Reviewer confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n440: | `downgradeTrigger` | string | The concrete condition under which this finding should be downgraded in a future iteration |\n441: | `transitions` | object[] | Optional severity transition log, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n442: \n443: ### Validation Rules (enforced by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication`)\n444: \n445: 1. A packet MUST exist for every new P0/P1 finding introduced in this iteration. Carried-forward findings reuse the previous packet unless severity transitioned.\n446: 2. All required fields MUST be present and non-empty. `confidence` MUST be a number in `[0, 1]`.\n447: 3. Each `evidenceRefs` entry MUST contain a `:` separating the path from a line or range.\n448: 4. `finalSeverity` MUST match the severity the finding is registered under in the iteration's `Findings` section and in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`.\n449: 5. When any rule fails, the workflow appends `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` to the state log. The next `step_check_convergence` call reads that event and sets `claimAdjudicationGate` = `false`, producing a `blockedStop` event with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet.\n450: \n451: ### Severity Transition Rules\n452: \n453: - **P2 → P1**: confirmed exploitable impact or spec violation with direct evidence\n454: - **P1 → P0**: demonstrated data loss, security breach, or hard-gate failure\n455: - **Downgrade**: requires explicit counterevidence or a confirmed alternative explanation\n456: - Every transition is recorded in the packet's `transitions` array and mirrored into the finding registry's `transitions` field\n457: \n458: ---\n459: \n460: ## 10. FINDING REGISTRY\n461: \n462: Each finding is tracked with a unique identifier enabling deduplication, severity transitions, and status lifecycle.\n463: \n464: ### Schema\n465: \n466: ```json\n467: {\n468:   \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n469:   \"severity\": \"P1\",\n470:   \"category\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n471:   \"status\": \"active\",\n472:   \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n473:   \"title\": \"Applied target file missing from resource-map inventory\",\n474:   \"file\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\",\n475:   \"line\": 955,\n476:   \"firstSeen\": 2,\n477:   \"lastSeen\": 4,\n478:   \"transitions\": [\n479:     { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" },\n480:     { \"iteration\": 4, \"from\": \"P2\", \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Confirmed real coverage gap against applied target inventory\" }\n481:   ]\n482: }\n483: ```\n484: \n485: | Field | Type | Description |\n486: |-------|------|-------------|\n487: | findingId | string | Sequential unique ID: `F001`, `F002`, ... |\n488: | severity | `\"P0\"` / `\"P1\"` / `\"P2\"` | Current severity |\n489: | category | `\"correctness\"` / `\"security\"` / `\"traceability\"` / `\"maintainability\"` / `\"resource-map-coverage\"` | Primary audit category for the finding, `resource-map-coverage` is reserved for implementation-vs-map coverage gaps |\n490: | status | `\"active\"` / `\"resolved\"` / `\"deferred\"` / `\"disproved\"` | Current status |\n491: | dimension | string | Primary dimension: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability |\n492: | title | string | Short description |\n493: | file | string | File path |\n494: | line | number | Line number (approximate) |\n495: | firstSeen / lastSeen | number | Iteration where first discovered / last referenced |\n496: | transitions | array | Severity and status change history |\n497: \n498: ### Status Lifecycle\n499: \n500: ```text\n501: [discovered] --> active --> resolved    (fixed or confirmed non-issue)\n502:                   |\n503:                   +--> deferred    (advisory, below threshold)\n504:                   |\n505:                   +--> disproved   (counterevidence invalidated)\n506: ```\n507: \n508: | Status | Counts Toward Verdict |\n509: |--------|----------------------|\n510: | active | Yes |\n511: | resolved | No |\n512: | deferred | No (listed in Deferred Items) |\n513: | disproved | No |\n514: \n515: ### Deduplication\n516: \n517: Same file + line range + root cause as an existing finding = **refinement**, not new. The existing findingId is updated. Refinements count at half weight (`refinementMultiplier: 0.5`) and are tracked via `findingsRefined` in JSONL.\n518: \n519: ### Cross-Reference Protocols\n520: \n521: | Protocol | Level | Applies To | Gate |\n522: |----------|-------|------------|------|\n523: | spec_code | core | all types | hard |\n524: | checklist_evidence | core | all types | hard |\n525: | skill_agent | overlay | skill | advisory |\n526: | agent_cross_runtime | overlay | agent | advisory |\n527: | feature_catalog_code | overlay | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory |\n528: | playbook_capability | overlay | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory |\n529: \n530: Severity for `resource-map-coverage` findings is calibrated to the coverage-gate outcome:\n531: - `P2` when an untouched map entry is explicitly `expected-by-scope`\n532: - `P1` when an untouched or absent path represents a real coverage gap\n533: - `P0` only when the missing coverage masks a release-blocking correctness or security risk\n534: \n535: ### Quality Gates\n536: \n537: | Gate | Rule |\n538: |------|------|\n539: | Evidence | Every active finding backed by concrete file:line evidence |\n540: | Scope | Reviewed files and conclusions stay inside declared scope |\n541: | Coverage | Required dimensions and required protocols covered |\n542: \n543: All three gates must pass before STOP. Gate failure forces `verdict: \"FAIL\"` regardless of finding counts.\n\n(End of file - total 543 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state format\"\n  - \"deep review config schema\"\n  - \"review severity weights\"\n  - \"file protection levels\"\n  - \"review iteration file structure\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state format\"\n  - \"deep review config schema\"\n  - \"review severity weights\"\n  - \"file protection levels\"\n  - \"review iteration file structure\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n\n| File | Format | Mutability |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n| `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n| `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n\n```text\n{artifact_dir}/\n  deep-review-config.json\n  deep-review-state.jsonl\n  deep-review-findings-registry.json\n  deep-review-strategy.md\n  deep-review-dashboard.md\n  .deep-review-pause\n  review-report.md\n  iterations/\n    iteration-001.md\n    iteration-002.md\n    ...\n```\n\n`{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet).\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n- Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n- Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n- Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n\nCreated during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n    \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n    \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Field Reference\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n| reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n| reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n| reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n| resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n| sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n| parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n| lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n| generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n| continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n| maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n| convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n| stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n| crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n| qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n| specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n| status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n| releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n| fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n| reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n\n### File Protection Levels\n\n| Level | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n| append-only | New content added at end only |\n| mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n| write-once | Created once, never modified |\n| auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n| operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\n| Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|---------------------|\n| correctness | 1 | Yes |\n| security | 2 | Yes |\n| traceability | 3 | Yes |\n| maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n\n### Severity Weights\n\n| Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n|----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n| P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n| P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n| P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## 3. STATE LOG\n\nThe `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n\nUpdated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n\n### Required Sections\n\n| Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n| review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n| completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n| running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n| what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n| what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n| exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n| ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n| next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n| known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n| cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n| files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n| review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n\n### Mapping from Research Mode\n\n| Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n|---------------|-------------------|\n| review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n| completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n| running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n\nSections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n\n### Update Protocol\n\n1. Read current strategy file\n2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n\nReducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"openFindings\": [],\n  \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n  \"severityChanged\": [],\n  \"repeatedFindings\": [],\n  \"dimensionCoverage\": {\n    \"correctness\": true,\n    \"security\": true,\n    \"traceability\": false,\n    \"maintainability\": false\n  },\n  \"findingsBySeverity\": {\n    \"P0\": 0,\n    \"P1\": 1,\n    \"P2\": 2\n  },\n  \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n  \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n  \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n}\n```\n\nThis file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n\n### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |\n| `persistentSameSeverity` | array | Findings observed in ≥2 iterations with NO severity transitions beyond initial discovery. REQ-018 split of the deprecated `repeatedFindings` bucket. |\n| `severityChanged` | array | Findings that went through at least one severity transition (P0↔P1↔P2) in their `transitions` history. |\n| `repeatedFindings` | array | **Deprecated.** Union of `persistentSameSeverity` and `severityChanged`. Retained for backward compatibility, new code should read the split arrays. |\n| `corruptionWarnings` | array | Per-line corruption reports from `parseJsonlDetailed()`: `{line, raw, error}`. Non-empty means the reducer detected malformed JSONL. |\n\n### Default Values\n\nWhen no `graph_convergence` event has been recorded yet, defaults are `graphConvergenceScore: 0`, `graphDecision: null`, and `graphBlockers: []`.\nWhen no `blocked_stop` event has been recorded yet, `blockedStopHistory: []`.\nWhen JSONL parses cleanly, `corruptionWarnings: []`.\n\n### Fail-Closed Semantics (REQ-015, REQ-016)\n\n- **Malformed JSONL**: The reducer CLI exits with code `2` and writes a warning to stderr when `corruptionWarnings.length > 0`. Pass `--lenient` (or `lenient:true` to `reduceReviewState`) to escape-hatch out and preserve the v1.2.0.0 fail-open behavior for legacy packets.\n- **Missing machine-owned anchors**: `replaceAnchorSection()` throws `Error('Missing machine-owned anchor \"<id>\" in deep-review strategy file.')` when the strategy file is present but lacks one of the required anchors. Pass `--create-missing-anchors` (or `createMissingAnchors:true`) to bootstrap empty strategy files by appending the missing anchor blocks.\n- **Dashboard surfaces**: `CORRUPTION WARNINGS` section lists detected lines. `BLOCKED STOPS` section lists `blockedStopHistory` entries. `GRAPH CONVERGENCE` section reports `graphConvergenceScore` / `graphDecision` / `graphBlockers`.\n- **Strategy next-focus override**: When the latest `blocked_stop` event timestamp is newer than the latest iteration timestamp, the reducer rewrites the strategy `next-focus` anchor to surface the blocking gates and recovery hint so operators see the blocker before choosing the next iteration direction.\n\n---\n\n## 6. ITERATION FILES (review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md)\n\nWrite-once files. One per iteration, zero-padded 3-digit naming.\n\n### Structure\n\n```markdown\n# Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n\n## Focus\n[Dimension(s), files, scope investigated]\n\n## Scorecard\n- Dimensions covered: [list]\n- Files reviewed: [count]\n- New findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n- Refined findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n- New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0, Blocker\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n### P1, Required\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n### P2, Suggestion\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n## Cross-Reference Results\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n| spec_code | pass/partial/fail | hard | file:line | ... |\n\n## Assessment\n- New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n- Dimensions addressed: [list]\n- Novelty justification: [breakdown]\n\n## Ruled Out\n- [Approach]: [Why], [Evidence]\n\n## Dead Ends\n- [Direction]: [Why]\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n[What to investigate next]\n```\n\nEvery finding must include: unique ID (`F001`...), severity (`P0`/`P1`/`P2`), concrete `file:line` evidence, and dimension tag.\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW REPORT (review/review-report.md)\n\nThe review synthesis output contains 9 core sections plus a conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present` is true:\n\n| # | Section | Description |\n|---|---------|-------------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` flag |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why result routes to planning or changelog |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence, severity, dimension |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Ordered lanes grouped by dependency or area |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec updates implied by findings |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Initial remediation tasks from findings |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol outcomes and gaps |\n| 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` existed at init, contains touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n| 9 | Deferred Items | Advisory findings, blocked items, follow-up checks |\n| 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, convergence replay, audit detail |\n\n**Executive Summary** includes verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`), active finding counts, `hasAdvisories` boolean (PASS + P2 > 0), scope description, and convergence reason.\n\n**Planning Trigger** routes FAIL/CONDITIONAL to remediation planning, PASS to changelog creation.\n\n**Active Finding Registry** lists each active finding with findingId, severity, dimension, title, file:line evidence, first/last seen iteration, and status.\n\n**Remediation Workstreams** group related findings into ordered lanes with constituent finding IDs and execution order.\n\n**Spec Seed / Plan Seed** provide minimal spec updates and initial remediation tasks referencing finding IDs and target files.\n\n**Traceability Status** reports per-protocol pass/partial/fail with gating class and evidence.\n\n**Resource Map Coverage Gate** is emitted only when `resource_map_present` is true and MUST contain exactly three bullets: touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n\n**Deferred Items** captures advisory findings, blocked protocols, and future follow-up checks.\n\n**Audit Appendix** contains iteration table, convergence signal replay, file coverage matrix, and dimension breakdown.\n\n---\n\n## 8. DASHBOARD (review/deep-review-dashboard.md)\n\nAuto-generated summary. Never manually edited.\n\n- **Path**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated from**: JSONL state log + strategy + findings registry\n- **Refresh**: Regenerated after every iteration\n- **Protection**: `auto-generated` in fileProtection\n\n### Sections\n\n| Section | Source | Description |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| Findings Summary | JSONL | Active P0/P1/P2 counts, new vs refined |\n| Progress Table | JSONL | Run, status, focus, dimensions, ratio, duration |\n| Coverage | Strategy + JSONL | Dimension completion, file coverage, protocol status |\n| Trend | JSONL signals | Rolling average, composite stop score, trajectory |\n\n**Rules:** Sole inputs are JSONL + strategy. Overwrite entirely on refresh. Read-only for all agents.\n\n---\n\n## 9. CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n\nEvery new P0/P1 finding must carry a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. The packet is parsed by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` in the review workflow and its pass/fail result is persisted as a `claim_adjudication` event in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree reads the latest event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`), a missing or failed packet vetoes STOP even if every other gate passes. Prose-only adjudication blocks are no longer accepted.\n\n### Typed Packet Schema (required)\n\nEmbed the packet inside the iteration file for each new P0/P1 finding. The orchestrator parses it after evaluation and persists the validation result.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n  \"claim\": \"Coverage-graph upsert identity is bare `id`, so cross-session collisions overwrite prior rows.\",\n  \"evidenceRefs\": [\n    \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154\",\n    \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302\"\n  ],\n  \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Grepped the module for compound-key upserts, checked migration scripts, and inspected session-isolation.vitest.ts for a collision regression, none found.\",\n  \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be intentional single-tenant design, but REQ-024 explicitly requires session isolation, so this is rejected.\",\n  \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.86,\n  \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a composite primary key `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` lands and a collision regression covers the ID-reuse path, downgrade to P2 tech-debt.\",\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Required Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `findingId` | string | Must match the finding ID in the iteration body and registry |\n| `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes (one sentence, evidence-backed) |\n| `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations that substantiate the claim (at least one entry) |\n| `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the reviewer looked for contradicting evidence (commands, paths, docs), blank string is not acceptable |\n| `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative reading of the evidence, even if the reviewer rejects it |\n| `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication (may differ from the severity originally asserted) |\n| `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Reviewer confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n| `downgradeTrigger` | string | The concrete condition under which this finding should be downgraded in a future iteration |\n| `transitions` | object[] | Optional severity transition log, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n\n### Validation Rules (enforced by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication`)\n\n1. A packet MUST exist for every new P0/P1 finding introduced in this iteration. Carried-forward findings reuse the previous packet unless severity transitioned.\n2. All required fields MUST be present and non-empty. `confidence` MUST be a number in `[0, 1]`.\n3. Each `evidenceRefs` entry MUST contain a `:` separating the path from a line or range.\n4. `finalSeverity` MUST match the severity the finding is registered under in the iteration's `Findings` section and in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`.\n5. When any rule fails, the workflow appends `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` to the state log. The next `step_check_convergence` call reads that event and sets `claimAdjudicationGate` = `false`, producing a `blockedStop` event with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet.\n\n### Severity Transition Rules\n\n- **P2 → P1**: confirmed exploitable impact or spec violation with direct evidence\n- **P1 → P0**: demonstrated data loss, security breach, or hard-gate failure\n- **Downgrade**: requires explicit counterevidence or a confirmed alternative explanation\n- Every transition is recorded in the packet's `transitions` array and mirrored into the finding registry's `transitions` field\n\n---\n\n## 10. FINDING REGISTRY\n\nEach finding is tracked with a unique identifier enabling deduplication, severity transitions, and status lifecycle.\n\n### Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n  \"severity\": \"P1\",\n  \"category\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n  \"status\": \"active\",\n  \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n  \"title\": \"Applied target file missing from resource-map inventory\",\n  \"file\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\",\n  \"line\": 955,\n  \"firstSeen\": 2,\n  \"lastSeen\": 4,\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" },\n    { \"iteration\": 4, \"from\": \"P2\", \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Confirmed real coverage gap against applied target inventory\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| findingId | string | Sequential unique ID: `F001`, `F002`, ... |\n| severity | `\"P0\"` / `\"P1\"` / `\"P2\"` | Current severity |\n| category | `\"correctness\"` / `\"security\"` / `\"traceability\"` / `\"maintainability\"` / `\"resource-map-coverage\"` | Primary audit category for the finding, `resource-map-coverage` is reserved for implementation-vs-map coverage gaps |\n| status | `\"active\"` / `\"resolved\"` / `\"deferred\"` / `\"disproved\"` | Current status |\n| dimension | string | Primary dimension: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability |\n| title | string | Short description |\n| file | string | File path |\n| line | number | Line number (approximate) |\n| firstSeen / lastSeen | number | Iteration where first discovered / last referenced |\n| transitions | array | Severity and status change history |\n\n### Status Lifecycle\n\n```text\n[discovered] --> active --> resolved    (fixed or confirmed non-issue)\n                  |\n                  +--> deferred    (advisory, below threshold)\n                  |\n                  +--> disproved   (counterevidence invalidated)\n```\n\n| Status | Counts Toward Verdict |\n|--------|----------------------|\n| active | Yes |\n| resolved | No |\n| deferred | No (listed in Deferred Items) |\n| disproved | No |\n\n### Deduplication\n\nSame file + line range + root cause as an existing finding = **refinement**, not new. The existing findingId is updated. Refinements count at half weight (`refinementMultiplier: 0.5`) and are tracked via `findingsRefined` in JSONL.\n\n### Cross-Reference Protocols\n\n| Protocol | Level | Applies To | Gate |\n|----------|-------|------------|------|\n| spec_code | core | all types | hard |\n| checklist_evidence | core | all types | hard |\n| skill_agent | overlay | skill | advisory |\n| agent_cross_runtime | overlay | agent | advisory |\n| feature_catalog_code | overlay | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory |\n| playbook_capability | overlay | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory |\n\nSeverity for `resource-map-coverage` findings is calibrated to the coverage-gate outcome:\n- `P2` when an untouched map entry is explicitly `expected-by-scope`\n- `P1` when an untouched or absent path represents a real coverage gap\n- `P0` only when the missing coverage masks a release-blocking correctness or security risk\n\n### Quality Gates\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding backed by concrete file:line evidence |\n| Scope | Reviewed files and conclusions stay inside declared scope |\n| Coverage | Required dimensions and required protocols covered |\n\nAll three gates must pass before STOP. Gate failure forces `verdict: \"FAIL\"` regardless of finding counts.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":543,"totalLines":543,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1781756132740,"end":1781756132771}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370e49cd0819197936ff2af9665d6"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0fd80001dI1O1tfqDoZbEv","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756132783,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_YOsghrGLQeW3tyPwr2ralAZQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state outputs\"\n6:   - \"review packet outputs\"\n7:   - \"review dashboard output\"\n8:   - \"review report output\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review State Outputs\n14: \n15: This reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: Deep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. PACKET FILES\n26: \n27: | File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n28: |------|-------|------------|---------|\n29: | `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n30: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n31: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n32: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n33: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n34: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n35: | `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n36: | `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n41: \n42: Each iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n43: \n44: ```text\n45: Review verdict: PASS\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ```text\n49: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ```text\n53: Review verdict: FAIL\n54: ```\n55: \n56: The line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 4. DASHBOARD\n61: \n62: The dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n63: \n64: - Current iteration and next focus.\n65: - Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n66: - Dimension coverage.\n67: - Convergence trend.\n68: - Gate blockers.\n69: - Provisional verdict.\n70: \n71: If dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 5. FINAL REPORT\n76: \n77: `review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n78: \n79: - Executive summary.\n80: - Planning trigger.\n81: - Active finding registry.\n82: - Remediation workstreams.\n83: - Spec seed.\n84: - Plan seed.\n85: - Traceability status.\n86: - Deferred items.\n87: - Audit appendix.\n88: - Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n93: \n94: - `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n95: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n96: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET FILES\n\n| File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n|------|-------|------------|---------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n| `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n| `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n\nEach iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n\n```text\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\nThe line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DASHBOARD\n\nThe dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n\n- Current iteration and next focus.\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Dimension coverage.\n- Convergence trend.\n- Gate blockers.\n- Provisional verdict.\n\nIf dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINAL REPORT\n\n`review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n\n- Executive summary.\n- Planning trigger.\n- Active finding registry.\n- Remediation workstreams.\n- Spec seed.\n- Plan seed.\n- Traceability status.\n- Deferred items.\n- Audit appendix.\n- Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":96,"totalLines":96,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1781756132760,"end":1781756132779}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370e49cd88191b7dcb65b18211682"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0fd85001k7eJIeQevhMH09","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756132783,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2uHOdux8JMVsSRxjK3Ge1ekn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Convergence\n3: description: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"review convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n7:   - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n8:   - \"review stuck detection\"\n9:   - \"composite convergence vote\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Convergence\n15: \n16: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Convergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n25: \n26: | Outcome | Meaning |\n27: |---------|---------|\n28: | **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n29: | **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n30: | **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n31: \n32: Convergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n33: \n34: Release-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n35: - `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n36: - `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n37: - `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n38: \n39: When the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n40: \n41: ### When to Use\n42: \n43: - Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n44: - Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n45: - Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n46: - Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n47: \n48: ### Key Defaults\n49: \n50: | Setting | Value | Purpose |\n51: |---------|-------|---------|\n52: | `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n53: | `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n54: | `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n55: | `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n56: | `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n57: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n58: | `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n59: \n60: ### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n61: \n62: `convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n63: \n64: **Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n65: \n66: | Skill | Default | Signal |\n67: |---|---|---|\n68: | `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n69: | `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n70: | `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n71: \n72: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n73: \n74: ### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n75: \n76: > **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n77: \n78: For review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n79: \n80: | Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n81: |---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n82: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n83: | `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n84: | `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n85: \n86: When implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n87: \n88: ### Shared Stop Contract\n89: \n90: Every terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n91: \n92: #### stopReason Enum\n93: \n94: | `stopReason` | Meaning |\n95: |--------------|---------|\n96: | `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n97: | `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n98: | `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n99: | `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n100: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n101: | `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n102: | `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n103: \n104: #### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n105: \n106: `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n107: \n108: ```json\n109: {\n110:   \"type\": \"event\",\n111:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n112:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n113:   \"run\": 5,\n114:   \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n115:   \"gateResults\": {\n116:     \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n117:     \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n118:       \"pass\": false,\n119:       \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n120:       \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n121:     },\n122:     \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n123:     \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n124:     \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n125:     \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n126:     \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n127:     \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n128:     \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n129:   },\n130:   \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n131:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n132:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n133:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n134:   \"generation\": 1\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: - `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n139: - `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n140: - `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n141: - `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n142: - When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n143: \n144: ### Decision Priority\n145: \n146: Checks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n147: \n148: 1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n149: 2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n150: 3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n151: 4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n152: 5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n153: 6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## 2. HARD STOPS\n158: \n159: Hard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n160: \n161: ### Max Iterations Reached\n162: \n163: ```\n164: if len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n165:   return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: The loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n169: \n170: ### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n171: \n172: ```\n173: if coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n174:   if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n175:     if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n176:       return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: Triggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n184: \n185: Identifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n186: \n187: ```\n188: function countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n189:   count = 0\n190:   for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n191:     if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n192:     if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n193:     if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n194:       count += 1\n195:     else:\n196:       break\n197:   return count\n198: ```\n199: \n200: **Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n201: \n202: **Status exclusions:**\n203: - `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n204: - `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n205: \n206: When `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n207: \n208: The recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n213: \n214: Three independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n215: \n216: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n217: |--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n218: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n219: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n220: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n221: \n222: ### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n223: \n224: Averages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n225: \n226: ```\n227: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n228:   recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n229:   avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n230:   rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n234: \n235: Robust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n236: \n237: ```\n238: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n239:   allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n240:   med = median(allRatios)\n241:   mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n242:   noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n243:   madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n247: \n248: Highest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n249: \n250: ```\n251: dimensionStop =\n252:   dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n253:   AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n254:   AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n255: ```\n256: \n257: The latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n258: \n259: ### Weighted Vote\n260: \n261: ```\n262: stopScore = sum(s.weight * (1 if s.stop else 0) for s in signals) / totalWeight\n263: if stopScore >= 0.60:   // proceed to quality gate evaluation\n264: ```\n265: \n266: Weights are redistributed across active signals only. If only 2 signals have enough data, their weights are normalized to sum to 1.0.\n267: \n268: ### Semantic Convergence Signals\n269: \n270: Two additional signals provide deeper semantic analysis of review iteration quality. These signals are ADDITIONAL to the 3-signal composite vote above and participate in the legal-stop gate evaluation rather than the composite stop-score.\n271: \n272: #### semanticNovelty (0.0-1.0)\n273: \n274: Measures how much genuinely new review insight each iteration contributes beyond surface-level overlap with prior findings. Unlike `newFindingsRatio` (which is severity-weighted), `semanticNovelty` evaluates the conceptual novelty of findings independent of severity weighting.\n275: \n276: | Value | Meaning |\n277: |-------|---------|\n278: | 0.8-1.0 | Iteration uncovered substantially new defect patterns, architectural concerns, or review angles |\n279: | 0.4-0.7 | Mix of new review insights and restatements of prior findings |\n280: | 0.1-0.3 | Mostly refinements or rewordings of previously identified issues |\n281: | 0.0 | No semantically novel findings detected |\n282: \n283: Computation:\n284: ```\n285: function computeSemanticNovelty_review(currentFindings, priorCumulativeFindings):\n286:   newPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings) - extractDefectPatterns(priorCumulativeFindings)\n287:   totalPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings)\n288:   if len(totalPatterns) == 0: return 0.0\n289:   return len(newPatterns) / len(totalPatterns)\n290: ```\n291: \n292: When `semanticNovelty` drops below 0.15 for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations, it provides strong supporting evidence for a legal STOP decision. This signal catches cases where `newFindingsRatio` stays moderate (due to severity weighting of refinements) but the review has exhausted genuinely new defect categories.\n293: \n294: #### findingStability (0.0-1.0)\n295: \n296: Measures how stable the cumulative finding set is across iterations. A high stability score means the finding registry is not materially changing between iterations -- findings are not being added, upgraded, downgraded, or invalidated at a significant rate.\n297: \n298: | Value | Meaning |\n299: |-------|---------|\n300: | 0.9-1.0 | Finding set is highly stable, minimal churn between iterations |\n301: | 0.6-0.8 | Moderate stability, some findings still evolving |\n302: | 0.3-0.5 | Active churn, findings being added, merged, or reclassified frequently |\n303: | 0.0-0.2 | Highly unstable, the review is still in early discovery |\n304: \n305: Computation:\n306: ```\n307: function computeFindingStability(currentRegistry, priorRegistry):\n308:   if priorRegistry is null: return 0.0  // first iteration\n309:   unchangedFindings = count(f for f in currentRegistry\n310:     if f.id in priorRegistry and f.severity == priorRegistry[f.id].severity\n311:     and f.status == priorRegistry[f.id].status)\n312:   totalFindings = max(len(currentRegistry), len(priorRegistry))\n313:   if totalFindings == 0: return 1.0\n314:   return unchangedFindings / totalFindings\n315: ```\n316: \n317: Convergence behavior:\n318: - `findingStability >= 0.85` supports STOP: the finding set has stabilized and further iterations are unlikely to materially change the review outcome.\n319: - `findingStability < 0.50` prevents STOP: the finding set is still in flux and the review has not reached a stable assessment.\n320: \n321: #### Integration with Legal-Stop Gate Bundle\n322: \n323: The two semantic signals integrate with the existing 5-gate legal-stop bundle (Section 6):\n324: \n325: 1. **findingStability gate** (existing): The existing `findingStability` gate already evaluates rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio. The new `semanticNovelty` signal adds a sub-check:\n326:    - `semanticNoveltyPlateau`: `semanticNovelty < 0.15` for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations\n327:    - When this sub-check fails while the existing churn signals pass, the gate records the mismatch as a diagnostic note but does not independently block STOP.\n328: \n329: 2. **findingStability signal** (new): The `findingStability` metric (0.0-1.0) is surfaced alongside the existing convergence signals. It supports the `findingStability` gate evaluation by providing a registry-level stability measure that complements the ratio-based churn signals.\n330: \n331: The gate passes only when both the existing churn-based checks AND the semantic stability checks agree. When a semantic check fails, the persisted `blocked_stop.gateResults.findingStability` payload includes the semantic signal values.\n332: \n333: #### Stop-Decision Trace\n334: \n335: The stop-decision event includes which semantic signals supported or prevented STOP:\n336: \n337: ```json\n338: {\n339:   \"type\": \"event\",\n340:   \"event\": \"stop_decision\",\n341:   \"semanticSignals\": {\n342:     \"semanticNovelty\": { \"value\": 0.06, \"consecutiveLow\": 3, \"supportsStop\": true },\n343:     \"findingStability\": { \"value\": 0.92, \"supportsStop\": true }\n344:   },\n345:   \"semanticVerdict\": \"all_support_stop\",\n346:   ...\n347: }\n348: ```\n349: \n350: | `semanticVerdict` | Meaning |\n351: |-------------------|---------|\n352: | `all_support_stop` | Both semantic signals support stopping |\n353: | `mixed` | One signal supports stop, the other does not |\n354: | `all_prevent_stop` | Both semantic signals indicate more work is needed |\n355: | `insufficient_data` | Not enough iterations to compute semantic signals |\n356: \n357: ### Graceful Degradation\n358: \n359: | Iterations Completed | Active Signals | Behavior |\n360: |---------------------|----------------|----------|\n361: | 1 | Novelty ratio only (weight 1.0) | Very unlikely to stop without later confirmation from rolling churn signals |\n362: | 2 | Rolling avg + novelty ratio | Two-signal vote, reweighted |\n363: | 3+ | All three signals | Full composite, most reliable |\n364: \n365: Semantic convergence signals (`semanticNovelty`, `findingStability`) require at least 2 evidence iterations to produce meaningful values. They are omitted from legal-stop evaluation when insufficient data exists.\n366: \n367: ---\n368: \n369: ## 5. SEVERITY-WEIGHTED RATIO\n370: \n371: The review loop uses `newFindingsRatio` instead of `newInfoRatio`. It weights findings by severity so that critical discoveries count far more than minor suggestions.\n372: \n373: ### Severity Weights\n374: \n375: | Severity | Weight | Description |\n376: |----------|--------|-------------|\n377: | **P0** (Blocker) | 10.0 | Correctness failures, security vulnerabilities, spec contradictions |\n378: | **P1** (Required) | 5.0 | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation |\n379: | **P2** (Suggestion) | 1.0 | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps |\n380: \n381: ### Computation\n382: \n383: ```\n384: SEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 }\n385: refinementMultiplier = 0.5\n386: \n387: weightedNew       = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in fully_new_findings)\n388: weightedRefinement = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] * 0.5 for f in refinement_findings)\n389: weightedTotal     = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in all_findings_this_iteration)\n390: \n391: newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal\n392: ```\n393: \n394: - `fully_new_findings` -- findings not present in any prior iteration (new findingId).\n395: - `refinement_findings` -- findings that refine or upgrade an existing finding (same root cause, new evidence or severity change).\n396: - `refinementMultiplier = 0.5` -- refinements count at half weight.\n397: \n398: ### P0 Override Rule\n399: \n400: ```\n401: if ANY new P0 found this iteration:\n402:   newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)\n403: \n404: if total_findings == 0:\n405:   newFindingsRatio = 0.0\n406: ```\n407: \n408: A new critical finding always signals significant remaining work. The 0.50 floor prevents premature convergence when critical issues are still being discovered.\n409: \n410: ---\n411: \n412: ## 6. LEGAL-STOP GATE BUNDLE\n413: \n414: > **GATE MODEL, two naming conventions mapped to one authoritative set.** The authoritative producer is `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`, which emits **9 gates** with the `Gate` suffix: `convergenceGate` / `dimensionCoverageGate` / `p0ResolutionGate` / `evidenceDensityGate` / `hotspotSaturationGate` / `claimAdjudicationGate` / `fixCompletenessReplayGate` / `candidateCoverageGate` / `graphlessFallbackGate`. The §Section-1 event shape (lines 98-119) mirrors this set verbatim and the reducer reads those names verbatim, so treat the event shape as authoritative when writing or reading JSONL state. The §6 table below is the high-level conceptual model and uses descriptive names WITHOUT the `Gate` suffix where one reads more naturally (for example `findingStability` maps to `convergenceGate`); each row carries its event-shape name so the mapping is explicit. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. The gate-model drift cluster (LG-0013, LG-0016, LG-0031, LG-0032) was reconciled in `006-gate-model-reconciliation`.\n415: \n416: Deep review treats STOP as legal only when the full review-specific gate bundle passes together. Convergence math may request STOP, but the workflow must still evaluate these 9 gates and persist a blocked-stop event when any gate fails.\n417: \n418: | Gate (§6 conceptual) | Event-shape name (§Section-1) | Rule | Fail Action |\n419: |------|------|------|-------------|\n420: | **findingStability** | `convergenceGate` | Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio must all indicate low-yield review churn | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n421: | **dimensionCoverage** | `dimensionCoverageGate` | Every configured review dimension must have been examined at least once, with required traceability coverage stabilized | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n422: | **p0Resolution** | `p0ResolutionGate` | No unresolved P0 findings may remain active at stop time | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n423: | **evidenceDensity** | `evidenceDensityGate` | Evidence density across active findings must meet the configured threshold | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n424: | **hotspotSaturation** | `hotspotSaturationGate` | Review hotspots must be revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n425: | (no §6 counterpart) | `claimAdjudicationGate` | Each new P0/P1 finding must carry a typed adjudication packet, missing or failing packets veto STOP | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n426: | **fixCompletenessReplay** | `fixCompletenessReplayGate` | Security-sensitive fix reruns must replay previously closed P0/P1 gates and validate producer/consumer/matrix coverage from the remediation packet | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n427: | **candidateCoverage** (v2 rollout) | `candidateCoverageGate` | Search debt must be cleared and every required bug class must have candidate coverage before STOP, passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n428: | **graphlessFallback** (v2 rollout) | `graphlessFallbackGate` | When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes must carry cited fallback ledger rows, passes trivially when the graph is available | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n429: \n430: ### Gate Evaluation\n431: \n432: ```\n433: function buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage):\n434:   gateResults = {\n435:     findingStability: {\n436:       pass: rollingStop and madStop and state.latestNoveltyRatio <= config.convergenceThreshold,\n437:       detail: \"Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio are all below stop thresholds.\"\n438:     },\n439:     dimensionCoverage: {\n440:       pass: everyConfiguredDimensionExaminedAtLeastOnce(coverage, config.reviewDimensions) and\n441:             coverage.requiredProtocolsCovered and\n442:             coverage.stabilizationPasses >= 1,\n443:       detail: \"All configured review dimensions have been examined, required traceability protocols are covered, and stabilization has aged enough to stop.\"\n444:     },\n445:     p0Resolution: {\n446:       pass: countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"]) == 0 and state.claimAdjudicationPassed != false,\n447:       detail: \"No unresolved P0 findings remain and blocker adjudication is complete.\"\n448:     },\n449:     evidenceDensity: {\n450:       pass: computeEvidenceDensity(state.activeFindings) >= config.evidenceDensityThreshold,\n451:       detail: \"Evidence density meets the configured threshold for active findings.\"\n452:     },\n453:     hotspotSaturation: {\n454:       pass: computeHotspotSaturation(state.hotspots) >= config.hotspotSaturationThreshold,\n455:       detail: \"Priority hotspots received enough revisits to satisfy saturation.\"\n456:     },\n457:     fixCompletenessReplay: {\n458:       pass: not isSecuritySensitiveFixRerun(state, config) or allRequiredReplayRowsPass(state.reviewReport),\n459:       detail: \"Security-sensitive fix reruns include closed-gate replay evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage before STOP.\"\n460:     },\n461:     candidateCoverage: {\n462:       pass: not isReviewDepthV2Active(state, config) or (searchDebtCleared(state) and allRequiredBugClassesCovered(state)),\n463:       detail: \"Search debt is cleared and every required bug class has candidate coverage. Passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive.\"\n464:     },\n465:     graphlessFallback: {\n466:       pass: state.searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode == \"graph_available\" or allRequiredBugClassesHaveFallbackRows(state),\n467:       detail: \"When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes carry cited fallback ledger rows. Passes trivially when the graph is available.\"\n468:     }\n469:   }\n470: \n471:   blockedBy = [name for name, result in gateResults.items() if not result.pass]\n472:   return {\n473:     pass: len(blockedBy) == 0,\n474:     blockedBy,\n475:     gateResults\n476:   }\n477: ```\n478: \n479: When convergence math returns STOP, invoke `buildReviewLegalStop()`. If it returns `pass: false`, persist a first-class `blocked_stop` event with the failing `blockedBy` gates, the full `gateResults` bundle, a `recoveryStrategy`, and the normal run/timestamp/session lineage fields before overriding the decision to CONTINUE.\n480: \n481: ### Blocked-Stop Recovery Strategy\n482: \n483: | Failed Gate | Recovery Strategy |\n484: |-------------|-------------------|\n485: | `findingStability` | Revisit the noisiest recent dimension and reduce novelty by closing obvious follow-up loops before re-checking STOP. |\n486: | `dimensionCoverage` | Schedule the next uncovered review dimension immediately. |\n487: | `p0Resolution` | Re-open the active blocker path and verify whether the P0 is real, downgraded, or still unresolved. |\n488: | `evidenceDensity` | Re-read weakly supported findings and add concrete `file:line` citations before they count toward a stop decision. |\n489: | `hotspotSaturation` | Revisit undersampled hotspots or adjacent call sites until the saturation heuristic passes. |\n490: | `fixCompletenessReplay` | Replay prior active or remediated P0/P1 gates, then record producer, consumer, and matrix coverage evidence before re-checking STOP. |\n491: | `candidateCoverage` | Clear outstanding search debt and run candidate discovery for the missing bug classes before re-checking STOP. |\n492: | `graphlessFallback` | Add cited fallback ledger rows for the required bug classes, or restore graph availability, before re-checking STOP. |\n493: \n494: ### Legacy Stop-Reason Mapping\n495: \n496: Use this table when replaying old packets or translating older prose/docs into the shared stop contract.\n497: \n498: | Legacy label | New `stopReason` | Mapping note |\n499: |--------------|------------------|--------------|\n500: | `all_dimensions_clean` | `converged` | Legacy review-specific terminal label, now expressed by the shared enum. |\n501: | `composite_converged` | `converged` | Legacy convergence-math wording now rolls into shared terminal success. |\n502: | `all dimensions clean` | `converged` | Old operator-facing prose for the same successful stop. |\n503: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` | Legacy machine label for the hard iteration cap. |\n504: | `max iterations` | `maxIterationsReached` | Old operator-facing hard-stop wording. |\n505: | `pause sentinel detected` | `userPaused` | Sentinel pause is now a shared user-directed stop reason. |\n506: | `guard_override` | `blockedStop` | Legacy continue override when a stop vote failed legal gates. |\n507: | `quality guard failed` | `blockedStop` | Older prose for the same blocked-stop outcome. |\n508: | `P0 override blocks convergence` | `blockedStop` | Legacy review wording for a stop attempt that was not legal to finalize. |\n509: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy recovery trigger label. |\n510: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy terminal wording for the same recovery path family. |\n511: | `manual halt` | `manualStop` | Operator-directed halt outside normal pause sentinel flow. |\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ## 7. PROVISIONAL VERDICT\n516: \n517: The provisional verdict is determined from active findings at the time the loop stops. It appears in both the convergence report and the final `review-report.md`.\n518: \n519: | Verdict | Condition | Meaning |\n520: |---------|-----------|---------|\n521: | **FAIL** | `activeP0 > 0` OR any legal-stop gate fails at terminal stop time | Does not meet quality standards. Blocks release. |\n522: | **CONDITIONAL** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 > 0` | Meets threshold but has required fixes before release. |\n523: | **PASS** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 == 0` | Shippable. Set `hasAdvisories: true` when `activeP2 > 0`. |\n524: \n525: ### Determination\n526: \n527: ```\n528: function determineVerdict(state, gateResult):\n529:   activeP0 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"])\n530:   activeP1 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P1\"])\n531:   activeP2 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P2\"])\n532: \n533:   if activeP0 > 0 or not gateResult.passed:\n534:     return { verdict: \"FAIL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n535:   if activeP1 > 0:\n536:     return { verdict: \"CONDITIONAL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n537: \n538:   hasAdvisories = activeP2 > 0\n539:   return { verdict: \"PASS\", hasAdvisories, nextCommand: \"/create:changelog\" }\n540: ```\n541: \n542: ### Post-Verdict Routing\n543: \n544: | Verdict | Next Step |\n545: |---------|-----------|\n546: | FAIL | `/speckit:plan` -- create remediation plan from findings |\n547: | CONDITIONAL | `/speckit:plan` -- create fix plan for P1 findings |\n548: | PASS | `/create:changelog` -- record the clean audit |\n549: \n550: ---\n551: \n552: ## 8. RECOVERY, REPORTING, AND GRAPH-AWARE CONVERGENCE\n553: \n554: Stuck-recovery strategies, the convergence report format, and graph-aware review convergence live in `convergence_recovery.md` for navigability.\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ## OPTIMIZER-TUNABLE THRESHOLDS\n559: \n560: The following convergence thresholds are managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). Changes to these fields are proposed through the optimizer's advisory-only promotion gate and reviewed by humans before adoption.\n561: \n562: ### Tunable Fields (Optimizer-Managed)\n563: \n564: | Field | Default | Range | Description |\n565: |-------|---------|-------|-------------|\n566: | `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | 0.01-0.20 | General convergence sensitivity |\n567: | `stuckThreshold` | 2 | 1-5 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n568: | `maxIterations` | 7 | 3-20 | Hard iteration ceiling |\n569: | `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | 0.40-0.80 | Weighted stop score needed before guard evaluation |\n570: \n571: ### Locked Fields (Not Optimizer-Tunable)\n572: \n573: The following fields are runtime contracts and MUST NOT be modified by the optimizer:\n574: \n575: - `stopReason` enum values and semantics\n576: - `blocked_stop` event structure and gate names\n577: - Lineage fields (`sessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`)\n578: - Reducer configuration and file protection policies\n579: - Review dimensions (`reviewDimensions`) and product mode (`mode`)\n580: \n581: ### Canonical Manifest\n582: \n583: The authoritative registry of tunable vs locked fields is maintained at:\n584: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n\n(End of file - total 584 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nConvergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n\n| Outcome | Meaning |\n|---------|---------|\n| **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n| **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n| **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n\nConvergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n\nRelease-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n- `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n- `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n- `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n\nWhen the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n- Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n- Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n- Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n\n### Key Defaults\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n| `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n| `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n| `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n| `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n| `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n\n### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n\n`convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n\n**Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n\n| Skill | Default | Signal |\n|---|---|---|\n| `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n| `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n| `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n\n### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n\n> **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n\nFor review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n\n| Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n|---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n| `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n| `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n\nWhen implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n\n### Shared Stop Contract\n\nEvery terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n\n#### stopReason Enum\n\n| `stopReason` | Meaning |\n|--------------|---------|\n| `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n| `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n| `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n| `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n| `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n\n#### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n\n`step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n  \"gateResults\": {\n    \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n    \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n      \"pass\": false,\n      \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n      \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n    },\n    \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n    \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n    \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n    \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n    \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n    \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n    \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n  },\n  \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1\n}\n```\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n- `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n- `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n- `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n- When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n\n### Decision Priority\n\nChecks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n\n1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HARD STOPS\n\nHard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n\n### Max Iterations Reached\n\n```\nif len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n  return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n```\n\nThe loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n\n### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n\n```\nif coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n  if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n    if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n      return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n```\n\nTriggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n\n---\n\n## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n\nIdentifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n\n```\nfunction countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n  count = 0\n  for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n    if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n    if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n    if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n      count += 1\n    else:\n      break\n  return count\n```\n\n**Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n\n**Status exclusions:**\n- `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n- `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n\nWhen `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n\nThe recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n\n---\n\n## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n\nThree independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n\n### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n\nAverages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n  recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n  avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n  rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n```\n\n### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n\nRobust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n  allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n  med = median(allRatios)\n  mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n  noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n  madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n```\n\n### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n\nHighest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n\n```\ndimensionStop =\n  dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n  AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n  AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n```\n\nThe latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n\n### Weighted Vote\n\n```\nstopScore = sum(s.weight * (1 if s.stop else 0) for s in signals) / totalWeight\nif stopScore >= 0.60:   // proceed to quality gate evaluation\n```\n\nWeights are redistributed across active signals only. If only 2 signals have enough data, their weights are normalized to sum to 1.0.\n\n### Semantic Convergence Signals\n\nTwo additional signals provide deeper semantic analysis of review iteration quality. These signals are ADDITIONAL to the 3-signal composite vote above and participate in the legal-stop gate evaluation rather than the composite stop-score.\n\n#### semanticNovelty (0.0-1.0)\n\nMeasures how much genuinely new review insight each iteration contributes beyond surface-level overlap with prior findings. Unlike `newFindingsRatio` (which is severity-weighted), `semanticNovelty` evaluates the conceptual novelty of findings independent of severity weighting.\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| 0.8-1.0 | Iteration uncovered substantially new defect patterns, architectural concerns, or review angles |\n| 0.4-0.7 | Mix of new review insights and restatements of prior findings |\n| 0.1-0.3 | Mostly refinements or rewordings of previously identified issues |\n| 0.0 | No semantically novel findings detected |\n\nComputation:\n```\nfunction computeSemanticNovelty_review(currentFindings, priorCumulativeFindings):\n  newPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings) - extractDefectPatterns(priorCumulativeFindings)\n  totalPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings)\n  if len(totalPatterns) == 0: return 0.0\n  return len(newPatterns) / len(totalPatterns)\n```\n\nWhen `semanticNovelty` drops below 0.15 for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations, it provides strong supporting evidence for a legal STOP decision. This signal catches cases where `newFindingsRatio` stays moderate (due to severity weighting of refinements) but the review has exhausted genuinely new defect categories.\n\n#### findingStability (0.0-1.0)\n\nMeasures how stable the cumulative finding set is across iterations. A high stability score means the finding registry is not materially changing between iterations -- findings are not being added, upgraded, downgraded, or invalidated at a significant rate.\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| 0.9-1.0 | Finding set is highly stable, minimal churn between iterations |\n| 0.6-0.8 | Moderate stability, some findings still evolving |\n| 0.3-0.5 | Active churn, findings being added, merged, or reclassified frequently |\n| 0.0-0.2 | Highly unstable, the review is still in early discovery |\n\nComputation:\n```\nfunction computeFindingStability(currentRegistry, priorRegistry):\n  if priorRegistry is null: return 0.0  // first iteration\n  unchangedFindings = count(f for f in currentRegistry\n    if f.id in priorRegistry and f.severity == priorRegistry[f.id].severity\n    and f.status == priorRegistry[f.id].status)\n  totalFindings = max(len(currentRegistry), len(priorRegistry))\n  if totalFindings == 0: return 1.0\n  return unchangedFindings / totalFindings\n```\n\nConvergence behavior:\n- `findingStability >= 0.85` supports STOP: the finding set has stabilized and further iterations are unlikely to materially change the review outcome.\n- `findingStability < 0.50` prevents STOP: the finding set is still in flux and the review has not reached a stable assessment.\n\n#### Integration with Legal-Stop Gate Bundle\n\nThe two semantic signals integrate with the existing 5-gate legal-stop bundle (Section 6):\n\n1. **findingStability gate** (existing): The existing `findingStability` gate already evaluates rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio. The new `semanticNovelty` signal adds a sub-check:\n   - `semanticNoveltyPlateau`: `semanticNovelty < 0.15` for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations\n   - When this sub-check fails while the existing churn signals pass, the gate records the mismatch as a diagnostic note but does not independently block STOP.\n\n2. **findingStability signal** (new): The `findingStability` metric (0.0-1.0) is surfaced alongside the existing convergence signals. It supports the `findingStability` gate evaluation by providing a registry-level stability measure that complements the ratio-based churn signals.\n\nThe gate passes only when both the existing churn-based checks AND the semantic stability checks agree. When a semantic check fails, the persisted `blocked_stop.gateResults.findingStability` payload includes the semantic signal values.\n\n#### Stop-Decision Trace\n\nThe stop-decision event includes which semantic signals supported or prevented STOP:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stop_decision\",\n  \"semanticSignals\": {\n    \"semanticNovelty\": { \"value\": 0.06, \"consecutiveLow\": 3, \"supportsStop\": true },\n    \"findingStability\": { \"value\": 0.92, \"supportsStop\": true }\n  },\n  \"semanticVerdict\": \"all_support_stop\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n| `semanticVerdict` | Meaning |\n|-------------------|---------|\n| `all_support_stop` | Both semantic signals support stopping |\n| `mixed` | One signal supports stop, the other does not |\n| `all_prevent_stop` | Both semantic signals indicate more work is needed |\n| `insufficient_data` | Not enough iterations to compute semantic signals |\n\n### Graceful Degradation\n\n| Iterations Completed | Active Signals | Behavior |\n|---------------------|----------------|----------|\n| 1 | Novelty ratio only (weight 1.0) | Very unlikely to stop without later confirmation from rolling churn signals |\n| 2 | Rolling avg + novelty ratio | Two-signal vote, reweighted |\n| 3+ | All three signals | Full composite, most reliable |\n\nSemantic convergence signals (`semanticNovelty`, `findingStability`) require at least 2 evidence iterations to produce meaningful values. They are omitted from legal-stop evaluation when insufficient data exists.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SEVERITY-WEIGHTED RATIO\n\nThe review loop uses `newFindingsRatio` instead of `newInfoRatio`. It weights findings by severity so that critical discoveries count far more than minor suggestions.\n\n### Severity Weights\n\n| Severity | Weight | Description |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| **P0** (Blocker) | 10.0 | Correctness failures, security vulnerabilities, spec contradictions |\n| **P1** (Required) | 5.0 | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation |\n| **P2** (Suggestion) | 1.0 | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps |\n\n### Computation\n\n```\nSEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 }\nrefinementMultiplier = 0.5\n\nweightedNew       = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in fully_new_findings)\nweightedRefinement = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] * 0.5 for f in refinement_findings)\nweightedTotal     = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in all_findings_this_iteration)\n\nnewFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal\n```\n\n- `fully_new_findings` -- findings not present in any prior iteration (new findingId).\n- `refinement_findings` -- findings that refine or upgrade an existing finding (same root cause, new evidence or severity change).\n- `refinementMultiplier = 0.5` -- refinements count at half weight.\n\n### P0 Override Rule\n\n```\nif ANY new P0 found this iteration:\n  newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)\n\nif total_findings == 0:\n  newFindingsRatio = 0.0\n```\n\nA new critical finding always signals significant remaining work. The 0.50 floor prevents premature convergence when critical issues are still being discovered.\n\n---\n\n## 6. LEGAL-STOP GATE BUNDLE\n\n> **GATE MODEL, two naming conventions mapped to one authoritative set.** The authoritative producer is `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`, which emits **9 gates** with the `Gate` suffix: `convergenceGate` / `dimensionCoverageGate` / `p0ResolutionGate` / `evidenceDensityGate` / `hotspotSaturationGate` / `claimAdjudicationGate` / `fixCompletenessReplayGate` / `candidateCoverageGate` / `graphlessFallbackGate`. The §Section-1 event shape (lines 98-119) mirrors this set verbatim and the reducer reads those names verbatim, so treat the event shape as authoritative when writing or reading JSONL state. The §6 table below is the high-level conceptual model and uses descriptive names WITHOUT the `Gate` suffix where one reads more naturally (for example `findingStability` maps to `convergenceGate`); each row carries its event-shape name so the mapping is explicit. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. The gate-model drift cluster (LG-0013, LG-0016, LG-0031, LG-0032) was reconciled in `006-gate-model-reconciliation`.\n\nDeep review treats STOP as legal only when the full review-specific gate bundle passes together. Convergence math may request STOP, but the workflow must still evaluate these 9 gates and persist a blocked-stop event when any gate fails.\n\n| Gate (§6 conceptual) | Event-shape name (§Section-1) | Rule | Fail Action |\n|------|------|------|-------------|\n| **findingStability** | `convergenceGate` | Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio must all indicate low-yield review churn | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **dimensionCoverage** | `dimensionCoverageGate` | Every configured review dimension must have been examined at least once, with required traceability coverage stabilized | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **p0Resolution** | `p0ResolutionGate` | No unresolved P0 findings may remain active at stop time | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **evidenceDensity** | `evidenceDensityGate` | Evidence density across active findings must meet the configured threshold | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **hotspotSaturation** | `hotspotSaturationGate` | Review hotspots must be revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| (no §6 counterpart) | `claimAdjudicationGate` | Each new P0/P1 finding must carry a typed adjudication packet, missing or failing packets veto STOP | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **fixCompletenessReplay** | `fixCompletenessReplayGate` | Security-sensitive fix reruns must replay previously closed P0/P1 gates and validate producer/consumer/matrix coverage from the remediation packet | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **candidateCoverage** (v2 rollout) | `candidateCoverageGate` | Search debt must be cleared and every required bug class must have candidate coverage before STOP, passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **graphlessFallback** (v2 rollout) | `graphlessFallbackGate` | When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes must carry cited fallback ledger rows, passes trivially when the graph is available | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n\n### Gate Evaluation\n\n```\nfunction buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage):\n  gateResults = {\n    findingStability: {\n      pass: rollingStop and madStop and state.latestNoveltyRatio <= config.convergenceThreshold,\n      detail: \"Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio are all below stop thresholds.\"\n    },\n    dimensionCoverage: {\n      pass: everyConfiguredDimensionExaminedAtLeastOnce(coverage, config.reviewDimensions) and\n            coverage.requiredProtocolsCovered and\n            coverage.stabilizationPasses >= 1,\n      detail: \"All configured review dimensions have been examined, required traceability protocols are covered, and stabilization has aged enough to stop.\"\n    },\n    p0Resolution: {\n      pass: countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"]) == 0 and state.claimAdjudicationPassed != false,\n      detail: \"No unresolved P0 findings remain and blocker adjudication is complete.\"\n    },\n    evidenceDensity: {\n      pass: computeEvidenceDensity(state.activeFindings) >= config.evidenceDensityThreshold,\n      detail: \"Evidence density meets the configured threshold for active findings.\"\n    },\n    hotspotSaturation: {\n      pass: computeHotspotSaturation(state.hotspots) >= config.hotspotSaturationThreshold,\n      detail: \"Priority hotspots received enough revisits to satisfy saturation.\"\n    },\n    fixCompletenessReplay: {\n      pass: not isSecuritySensitiveFixRerun(state, config) or allRequiredReplayRowsPass(state.reviewReport),\n      detail: \"Security-sensitive fix reruns include closed-gate replay evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage before STOP.\"\n    },\n    candidateCoverage: {\n      pass: not isReviewDepthV2Active(state, config) or (searchDebtCleared(state) and allRequiredBugClassesCovered(state)),\n      detail: \"Search debt is cleared and every required bug class has candidate coverage. Passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive.\"\n    },\n    graphlessFallback: {\n      pass: state.searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode == \"graph_available\" or allRequiredBugClassesHaveFallbackRows(state),\n      detail: \"When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes carry cited fallback ledger rows. Passes trivially when the graph is available.\"\n    }\n  }\n\n  blockedBy = [name for name, result in gateResults.items() if not result.pass]\n  return {\n    pass: len(blockedBy) == 0,\n    blockedBy,\n    gateResults\n  }\n```\n\nWhen convergence math returns STOP, invoke `buildReviewLegalStop()`. If it returns `pass: false`, persist a first-class `blocked_stop` event with the failing `blockedBy` gates, the full `gateResults` bundle, a `recoveryStrategy`, and the normal run/timestamp/session lineage fields before overriding the decision to CONTINUE.\n\n### Blocked-Stop Recovery Strategy\n\n| Failed Gate | Recovery Strategy |\n|-------------|-------------------|\n| `findingStability` | Revisit the noisiest recent dimension and reduce novelty by closing obvious follow-up loops before re-checking STOP. |\n| `dimensionCoverage` | Schedule the next uncovered review dimension immediately. |\n| `p0Resolution` | Re-open the active blocker path and verify whether the P0 is real, downgraded, or still unresolved. |\n| `evidenceDensity` | Re-read weakly supported findings and add concrete `file:line` citations before they count toward a stop decision. |\n| `hotspotSaturation` | Revisit undersampled hotspots or adjacent call sites until the saturation heuristic passes. |\n| `fixCompletenessReplay` | Replay prior active or remediated P0/P1 gates, then record producer, consumer, and matrix coverage evidence before re-checking STOP. |\n| `candidateCoverage` | Clear outstanding search debt and run candidate discovery for the missing bug classes before re-checking STOP. |\n| `graphlessFallback` | Add cited fallback ledger rows for the required bug classes, or restore graph availability, before re-checking STOP. |\n\n### Legacy Stop-Reason Mapping\n\nUse this table when replaying old packets or translating older prose/docs into the shared stop contract.\n\n| Legacy label | New `stopReason` | Mapping note |\n|--------------|------------------|--------------|\n| `all_dimensions_clean` | `converged` | Legacy review-specific terminal label, now expressed by the shared enum. |\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` | Legacy convergence-math wording now rolls into shared terminal success. |\n| `all dimensions clean` | `converged` | Old operator-facing prose for the same successful stop. |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` | Legacy machine label for the hard iteration cap. |\n| `max iterations` | `maxIterationsReached` | Old operator-facing hard-stop wording. |\n| `pause sentinel detected` | `userPaused` | Sentinel pause is now a shared user-directed stop reason. |\n| `guard_override` | `blockedStop` | Legacy continue override when a stop vote failed legal gates. |\n| `quality guard failed` | `blockedStop` | Older prose for the same blocked-stop outcome. |\n| `P0 override blocks convergence` | `blockedStop` | Legacy review wording for a stop attempt that was not legal to finalize. |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy recovery trigger label. |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy terminal wording for the same recovery path family. |\n| `manual halt` | `manualStop` | Operator-directed halt outside normal pause sentinel flow. |\n\n---\n\n## 7. PROVISIONAL VERDICT\n\nThe provisional verdict is determined from active findings at the time the loop stops. It appears in both the convergence report and the final `review-report.md`.\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Meaning |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| **FAIL** | `activeP0 > 0` OR any legal-stop gate fails at terminal stop time | Does not meet quality standards. Blocks release. |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 > 0` | Meets threshold but has required fixes before release. |\n| **PASS** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 == 0` | Shippable. Set `hasAdvisories: true` when `activeP2 > 0`. |\n\n### Determination\n\n```\nfunction determineVerdict(state, gateResult):\n  activeP0 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"])\n  activeP1 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P1\"])\n  activeP2 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P2\"])\n\n  if activeP0 > 0 or not gateResult.passed:\n    return { verdict: \"FAIL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n  if activeP1 > 0:\n    return { verdict: \"CONDITIONAL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n\n  hasAdvisories = activeP2 > 0\n  return { verdict: \"PASS\", hasAdvisories, nextCommand: \"/create:changelog\" }\n```\n\n### Post-Verdict Routing\n\n| Verdict | Next Step |\n|---------|-----------|\n| FAIL | `/speckit:plan` -- create remediation plan from findings |\n| CONDITIONAL | `/speckit:plan` -- create fix plan for P1 findings |\n| PASS | `/create:changelog` -- record the clean audit |\n\n---\n\n## 8. RECOVERY, REPORTING, AND GRAPH-AWARE CONVERGENCE\n\nStuck-recovery strategies, the convergence report format, and graph-aware review convergence live in `convergence_recovery.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## OPTIMIZER-TUNABLE THRESHOLDS\n\nThe following convergence thresholds are managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). Changes to these fields are proposed through the optimizer's advisory-only promotion gate and reviewed by humans before adoption.\n\n### Tunable Fields (Optimizer-Managed)\n\n| Field | Default | Range | Description |\n|-------|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | 0.01-0.20 | General convergence sensitivity |\n| `stuckThreshold` | 2 | 1-5 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| `maxIterations` | 7 | 3-20 | Hard iteration ceiling |\n| `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | 0.40-0.80 | Weighted stop score needed before guard evaluation |\n\n### Locked Fields (Not Optimizer-Tunable)\n\nThe following fields are runtime contracts and MUST NOT be modified by the optimizer:\n\n- `stopReason` enum values and semantics\n- `blocked_stop` event structure and gate names\n- Lineage fields (`sessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`)\n- Reducer configuration and file protection policies\n- Review dimensions (`reviewDimensions`) and product mode (`mode`)\n\n### Canonical Manifest\n\nThe authoritative registry of tunable vs locked fields is maintained at:\n`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":584,"totalLines":584,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1781756132766,"end":1781756132780}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370e49cdc819182ed850ef71cb54c"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0fd9b001dbHs3TdsI0Anyd","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756132783,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ywowfKHmXoR6lXrQdWNGFQfn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review Convergence Signals\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for severity-weighted stop signals, P0 overrides, quality gates, and graph-aware blocked-stop checks.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review convergence signals\"\n6:   - \"review stop signals\"\n7:   - \"severity weighted convergence\"\n8:   - \"review blocked stop\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Convergence Signals\n14: \n15: This reference names the live stop signals. Use `references/convergence/convergence.md` as the hub when you need algorithms, examples, and sibling threshold notes.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: Deep-review convergence is a release-readiness decision. The loop stops only when severity-weighted findings stabilize, dimension coverage is complete, quality gates pass, and no P0 override is active.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. SIGNALS\n26: \n27: | Signal | Meaning | Blocks STOP When |\n28: |--------|---------|------------------|\n29: | Severity-weighted new findings | Weighted P0/P1/P2 discovery ratio for the latest iteration | Above the configured threshold |\n30: | Rolling stop average | Stabilized trend across recent iterations | Still above the stop band |\n31: | Dimension coverage | Required review dimensions and traceability overlays covered | Any required dimension is missing |\n32: | Quality-gate bundle | Evidence, scope, coverage, P0, density, hotspot, claim, candidate, graphless gates | Any required gate fails |\n33: | Graph-aware blind spot check | Coverage graph sees unresolved structural gaps | Graph blockers remain active |\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 3. P0 OVERRIDE\n38: \n39: Any new P0 forces at least one more iteration. The override exists because a new blocker changes the release verdict, even if the rest of the stop math appears stable.\n40: \n41: P0 handling requires:\n42: \n43: - File and line evidence.\n44: - Adversarial self-check.\n45: - Active registry update.\n46: - Replay in synthesis before PASS is legal.\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 4. LEGAL STOP\n51: \n52: STOP is legal only when all of these are true:\n53: \n54: 1. New findings are below threshold.\n55: 2. Rolling trend is stable.\n56: 3. All required dimensions are covered.\n57: 4. The quality-gate bundle passes.\n58: 5. No unresolved P0 remains.\n59: 6. Graph-aware blockers are absent or explicitly unavailable with fallback evidence.\n60: \n61: If any item fails, the workflow emits `blocked_stop` and continues or routes to recovery.\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## 5. SIBLING CONTRAST\n66: \n67: Do not carry thresholds across deep skills:\n68: \n69: | Skill | Primary Signal | Default Threshold |\n70: |-------|----------------|-------------------|\n71: | `deep-review` | Severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 new findings | `0.10` |\n72: | `deep-research` | Novelty/newInfoRatio over research knowledge | `0.05` |\n73: | `deep-ai-council` | Planning agreement with critique blocker check | Council-specific, not interchangeable |\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n78: \n79: - `references/convergence/convergence.md` for the full stop contract.\n80: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` for dashboard and report fields that display convergence.\n81: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer-owned gate state.\n\n(End of file - total 81 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review Convergence Signals\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for severity-weighted stop signals, P0 overrides, quality gates, and graph-aware blocked-stop checks.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review convergence signals\"\n  - \"review stop signals\"\n  - \"severity weighted convergence\"\n  - \"review blocked stop\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence Signals\n\nThis reference names the live stop signals. Use `references/convergence/convergence.md` as the hub when you need algorithms, examples, and sibling threshold notes.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review Convergence Signals\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for severity-weighted stop signals, P0 overrides, quality gates, and graph-aware blocked-stop checks.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review convergence signals\"\n  - \"review stop signals\"\n  - \"severity weighted convergence\"\n  - \"review blocked stop\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence Signals\n\nThis reference names the live stop signals. Use `references/convergence/convergence.md` as the hub when you need algorithms, examples, and sibling threshold notes.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review convergence is a release-readiness decision. The loop stops only when severity-weighted findings stabilize, dimension coverage is complete, quality gates pass, and no P0 override is active.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SIGNALS\n\n| Signal | Meaning | Blocks STOP When |\n|--------|---------|------------------|\n| Severity-weighted new findings | Weighted P0/P1/P2 discovery ratio for the latest iteration | Above the configured threshold |\n| Rolling stop average | Stabilized trend across recent iterations | Still above the stop band |\n| Dimension coverage | Required review dimensions and traceability overlays covered | Any required dimension is missing |\n| Quality-gate bundle | Evidence, scope, coverage, P0, density, hotspot, claim, candidate, graphless gates | Any required gate fails |\n| Graph-aware blind spot check | Coverage graph sees unresolved structural gaps | Graph blockers remain active |\n\n---\n\n## 3. P0 OVERRIDE\n\nAny new P0 forces at least one more iteration. The override exists because a new blocker changes the release verdict, even if the rest of the stop math appears stable.\n\nP0 handling requires:\n\n- File and line evidence.\n- Adversarial self-check.\n- Active registry update.\n- Replay in synthesis before PASS is legal.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP\n\nSTOP is legal only when all of these are true:\n\n1. New findings are below threshold.\n2. Rolling trend is stable.\n3. All required dimensions are covered.\n4. The quality-gate bundle passes.\n5. No unresolved P0 remains.\n6. Graph-aware blockers are absent or explicitly unavailable with fallback evidence.\n\nIf any item fails, the workflow emits `blocked_stop` and continues or routes to recovery.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SIBLING CONTRAST\n\nDo not carry thresholds across deep skills:\n\n| Skill | Primary Signal | Default Threshold |\n|-------|----------------|-------------------|\n| `deep-review` | Severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 new findings | `0.10` |\n| `deep-research` | Novelty/newInfoRatio over research knowledge | `0.05` |\n| `deep-ai-council` | Planning agreement with critique blocker check | Council-specific, not interchangeable |\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/convergence/convergence.md` for the full stop contract.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` for dashboard and report fields that display convergence.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer-owned gate state.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":81,"totalLines":81,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","time":{"start":1781756132768,"end":1781756132781}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370e49ce08191b86ee15465ebd85e"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0fd9f001sw0mB4UVmjzbdT","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756132783,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_liHWIKVHaptoijutTXWTAUrG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"review findings registry\"\n7:   - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n8:   - \"review state reconstruction\"\n9: importance_tier: important\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n14: \n15: The reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: The reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. OWNERSHIP\n26: \n27: | Surface | Writer | Rule |\n28: |---------|--------|------|\n29: | JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n30: | Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n31: | Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n32: | Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n33: | Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n34: | Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n35: \n36: No agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n41: \n42: The registry groups findings into:\n43: \n44: - Active findings.\n45: - Resolved findings.\n46: - Repeated findings.\n47: - Blocked or disputed findings.\n48: - Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n49: \n50: Each active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n55: \n56: The reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n57: \n58: Recovery order:\n59: \n60: 1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n61: 2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n62: 3. Re-run the reducer.\n63: 4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n68: \n69: When derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n70: \n71: 1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n72: 2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n73: 3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n74: 4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n75: \n76: If JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n81: \n82: The reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n83: \n84: ### Two-Tier Match\n85: \n86: 1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n87:    - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n88:    - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n89:    - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n90:    - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n91: 2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n92: \n93: ### Synthesis Behavior\n94: \n95: When the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n96: \n97: ### Emission Requirement\n98: \n99: Every finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n104: \n105: - `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n106: - `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n107: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n108: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.\n\n(End of file - total 108 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNERSHIP\n\n| Surface | Writer | Rule |\n|---------|--------|------|\n| JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n| Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n| Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n| Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n| Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n| Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n\nNo agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe registry groups findings into:\n\n- Active findings.\n- Resolved findings.\n- Repeated findings.\n- Blocked or disputed findings.\n- Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n\nEach active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n\nThe reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n\nRecovery order:\n\n1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n3. Re-run the reducer.\n4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n\nWhen derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n\n1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n\nIf JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n\nThe reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n\n### Two-Tier Match\n\n1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n   - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n   - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n   - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n   - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n\n### Synthesis Behavior\n\nWhen the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n\n### Emission Requirement\n\nEvery finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n- `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":108,"totalLines":108,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1781756132769,"end":1781756132782}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07dc21605f43bb7d016a3370e49ce881918262d1c546b885fc"}},"id":"prt_ed8f0fda0001hJTE13NBOgwxRF","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781756133076,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"id":"prt_ed8f0fed2001TkwHij40yl631i","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"6649e8feac8ceae8794dcaa3aa38541c03152281","messageID":"msg_ed8f0a9e0001bbcCy0Nii3NH83","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":45997,"input":8604,"output":525,"reasoning":516,"cache":{"write":0,"read":36352}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781756135018,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"id":"prt_ed8f10669001ZSH505S8c5y0kK","messageID":"msg_ed8f0ffd8001D0nocr51mE1aSp","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","snapshot":"6649e8feac8ceae8794dcaa3aa38541c03152281","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756138789,"sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_50rZyJzK5Z9oQcAHZVNl9mxE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":635,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n635:         action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n636:         if_blocked:\n637:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n638:           log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n639:         if_not_blocked:\n640:           proceed: true\n641: \n642:       step_handle_convergence:\n643:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n644:         if_stop:\n645:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n646:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n647:         if_blocked:\n648:           log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n649:         if_stuck_recovery:\n650:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n651:           recovery_strategies:\n652:             - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n653:             - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n654:             - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n655:           pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n656:           set:\n657:             next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n658:             pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n659:             pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n660:             pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n661:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n662:         if_continue:\n663:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n664: \n665:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n666:         action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n667:         if_pending_pause_event:\n668:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n669:           message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n670:           reset:\n671:             pending_stop_event: null\n672:             pending_stop_reason: null\n673:             pending_stop_detail: null\n674:           halt: true\n675:         if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n676:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n677:           reset:\n678:             pending_stop_event: null\n679:             pending_stop_reason: null\n680:             pending_stop_detail: null\n681:         if_no_pending_event:\n682:           proceed: true\n683: \n684:       step_generate_state_summary:\n685:         action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n686:         generate: |\n687:           STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n688:           Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n689:           Dimension: {next_dimension}\n690:           Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n691:           Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n692:           Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n693:           {resource_map_prompt_line}\n694:           Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n695:           Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n696:           Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n697:           Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n698: \n699:       step_marker_scan:\n700:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n701:         algorithm: |\n702:           if current_iteration > 1:\n703:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n704:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n705:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n706:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n707:                 log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n708:                 halt with exit code 2\n709:         note: |\n710:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n711:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n712:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n713:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n714: \n715:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n716:         action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n717:         resolve_executor:\n718:           source: \"config.executor\"\n719:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n720:         pre_dispatch:\n721:           generate_summary: |\n722:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n723:             Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n724:             Dimension: {next_dimension}\n725:             Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n726:             Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n727:             Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n728:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n729:             Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n730:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n731:             Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n732:             Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n733:           render_prompt_pack:\n734:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n735:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n736:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n737:             variables:\n738:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n739:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n740:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n741:               next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n742:               review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n743:               review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n744:               p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n745:               p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n746:               p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n747:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n748:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n749:               state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n750:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n751:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n752:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n753:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n754:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n755:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n756:           args:\n757:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n758:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n759:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n760:         branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n761:         if_native:\n762:           dispatch:\n763:             agent: deep-review\n764:             model: opus\n765:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n766:           wait_for_completion: true\n767:         if_cli_codex:\n768:           command: |\n769:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n770:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n771: \n772:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n773:             import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n774: \n775:             const executor = {\n776:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n777:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n778:               configDir: '{config.executor.configDir}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.configDir}',\n779:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n780:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n781:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n782:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n783:             };\n784: \n785:             process.exit(await runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync({\n786:               command: 'codex',\n787:               args: [\n788:                 'exec',\n789:                 '--model',\n790:                 executor.model,\n791:                 '-c',\n792:                 `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n793:                 '-c',\n794:                 `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n795:                 '-c',\n796:                 'approval_policy=never',\n797:                 '--sandbox',\n798:                 resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n799:                 '-',\n800:               ],\n801:               cwd: '{repo_root}',\n802:               timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n803:               stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n804:               executor,\n805:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n806:               input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n807:             }));\n808:             EOF\n809:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n810:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n811:           wait_for_completion: true\n812:         if_cli_copilot:\n813:           command: |\n814:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n815:             import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n816:             import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n817: \n818:             import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n819: \n820:             const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n821:             const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n822: \n823:             // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n824:             // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n825:             // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n826:             // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n827:             // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n828:             // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n829:             // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n830:             const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n831:             const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n832: \n833:             const baseArgs = [\n834:               '-p',\n835:               prompt,\n836:               '--model',\n837:               '{config.executor.model}',\n838:               '--allow-all-tools',\n839:               '--no-ask-user',\n840:             ];\n841: \n842:             const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n843:               promptPath,\n844:               prompt,\n845:               targetAuthority,\n846:               baseArgv: baseArgs,\n847:             });\n848: \n849:             // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n850:             // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n851:             // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n852:             // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n853:             // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n854:             if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n855:               writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n856:             }\n857: \n858:             const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n859:               cwd: '{repo_root}',\n860:               stdio: 'inherit',\n861:               timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n862:             });\n863:             process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n864:             EOF\n865:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n866:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n867:           wait_for_completion: true\n868:           notes:\n869:             - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n870:             - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n871:             - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n872:             - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n873:             - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n874:             - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n875:         if_cli_claude_code:\n876:           command: |\n877:             if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n878:             claude \\\n879:               -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n880:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n881:               --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n882:               --output-format text \\\n883:               {optional_effort_flag}\n884:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n885:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n886:           wait_for_completion: true\n887:           render_hint:\n888:             optional_claude_config_dir: |\n889:               If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n890:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n891:             optional_effort_flag: |\n892:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n893:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n894:           notes:\n895:             - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n896:             - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n897:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n898:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n899:         if_cli_opencode:\n900:           command: |\n901:             opencode run \\\n902:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n903:               --format json \\\n904:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n905:               --pure \\\n906:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n907:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n908:               \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n909:               </dev/null\n910:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n911:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n912:           wait_for_completion: true\n913:           render_hint:\n914:             optional_variant_flag: |\n915:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n916:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n917:           notes:\n918:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n919:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n920:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n921:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n922:             - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n923:         post_dispatch_validate:\n924:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n925:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n926:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n927:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n928:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n929:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n930:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n931:           failure_reasons:\n932:             - iteration_file_missing\n933:             - iteration_file_empty\n934:             - jsonl_not_appended\n935:             - jsonl_missing_fields\n936:             - jsonl_parse_error\n937:             - jsonl_wrong_type\n938:             - delta_file_missing\n939:             - delta_file_empty\n940:             - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n941:             - executor_missing\n942:             - dispatch_failure_logged\n943:             - v2_missing_ledger\n944:             - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n945:             - v2_broken_linked_finding\n946:             - v2_shallow_finding_details\n947:             - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n948:             - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n949:           warning_surface:\n950:             source: \"result.warnings\"\n951:             action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n952:             severity: \"advisory\"\n953:             event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n954:             note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n955:           on_failure:\n956:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n957:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n958:         record_executor_audit:\n959:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n960:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n961:           field: \"executor\"\n962:           value:\n963:             kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n964:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n965:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n966:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n967: \n968:       step_evaluate_results:\n969:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n970:         verify:\n971:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n972:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n973:           - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n974:         extract:\n975:           - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n976:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n977:           - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n978:           - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n979:           - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n980:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n981:           - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n982:           - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n983:         on_missing_outputs:\n984:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n985:           # <!-- F-010-B5-03 -->\n986:           # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n987:           # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n988:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n989: \n990:       step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n991:         action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n992:         verify:\n993:           - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n994:           - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n995:           - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n996:         on_pass:\n997:           set:\n998:             claim_adjudication_passed: true\n999:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1000:           log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n1001:         on_fail:\n1002:           action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n1003:           set:\n1004:             claim_adjudication_passed: false\n1005:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1006:           log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n1007: \n1008:       step_reduce_review_state:\n1009:         action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n1010:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1011:         read:\n1012:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1013:           - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1014:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1015:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1016:         write:\n1017:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1018:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1019:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1020:         failure_modes:\n1021:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1022:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1023:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1024:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1025:         note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n1026: \n1027:       step_graph_upsert:\n1028:         action: \"Transform the latest iteration graphEvents delta into review graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n1029:         read:\n1030:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1031:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1032:         transform: |\n1033:           1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n1034:           2. If graphEvents is absent or empty, set graph_nodes_json = [] and graph_edges_json = [] and skip the upsert.\n1035:           3. For each graph event without relation/source/target, normalize type = uppercase(event.type || event.nodeKind || event.type) and keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n1036:           4. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } using the event label (or id fallback) and review metadata for run/current focus.\n1037:           5. For each graph event with relation + source + target, normalize relation = uppercase(event.relation) and keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n1038:           6. Emit edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata } and deduplicate the batch by id.\n1039:           7. Discard malformed or unknown graph events instead of failing the review iteration.\n1040:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n1041:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Upsert only the latest iteration graph delta.\"\n1042:         outputs:\n1043:           - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph nodes for the latest iteration\"\n1044:           - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph edges for the latest iteration\"\n1045:         skip_conditions:\n1046:           - \"Latest iteration record has no graphEvents array\"\n1047: \n1048:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1049:         action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n1050:         read:\n1051:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1052:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1053:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1054:         content: |\n1055:           # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n1056: \n1057:           Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n1058: \n1059:           ## Status\n1060:           - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n1061:           - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n1062:           - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n1063:           - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n1064:           - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n1065: \n1066:           ## Findings Summary\n1067:           | Severity | Count | Trend |\n1068:           |----------|------:|-------|\n1069:           | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n1070:           | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n1071:           | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n1072: \n1073:           ## Dimension Coverage\n1074:           | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n1075:           |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n1076:           | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n1077: \n1078:           ## Traceability Coverage\n1079:           | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n1080:           |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n1081:           | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n1082: \n1083:           ## Progress\n1084:           | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n1085:           |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n1086:           | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n1087: \n1088:           ## Trend\n1089:           - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n1090:           - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1091:           - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n1092: \n1093:           ## Next Focus\n1094:           {next_dimension}\n1095:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1096:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1097: \n1098:       step_update_tracking:\n1099:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1100:         set:\n1101:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1102:           p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1103:           p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1104:           p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1105:           stuck_count: |\n1106:             if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n1107:             if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n1108:             if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n1109:             else: 0\n1110:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1111: \n1112:       step_loop_decision:\n1113:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1114:         goto: step_read_state\n1115: \n1116:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1117:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1118:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1119:   phase_synthesis:\n1120:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n1121:     steps:\n1122: \n1123:       step_fanout_merge:\n1124:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n1125:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1126:         command: |\n1127:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1128:             --loop-type review \\\n1129:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1130:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1131:         wait_for_completion: true\n1132:         bind_from_output:\n1133:           p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n1134:           p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n1135:           p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n1136: \n1137:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1138:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1139:         read:\n1140:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1141:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1142:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1143:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1144:         extract:\n1145:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1146:           - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1147:           - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1148:           - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1149:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n1150:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n1151:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n1152:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n1153:           - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1154: \n1155:       # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n1156:       # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n1157:       # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n1158:       # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n1159:       # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n1160:       step_derive_verdict:\n1161:         action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n1162:         algorithm: |\n1163:           if p0_count > 0:\n1164:             verdict = \"FAIL\"\n1165:           elif p1_count > 0:\n1166:             verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n1167:           else:\n1168:             verdict = \"PASS\"\n1169:           has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n1170:           ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n1171:         outputs:\n1172:           - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n1173:           - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n1174:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n1175:         contract: |\n1176:           Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n1177:           Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n1178: \n1179:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1180:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1181:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1182:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1183: \n1184:       step_build_finding_registry:\n1185:         action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n1186:         algorithm: |\n1187:           1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n1188:           2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n1189:              content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n1190:              Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n1191:           3. Two-tier dedup:\n1192:              PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n1193:                - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n1194:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1195:              FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n1196:                - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n1197:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1198:           4. Track finding lifecycle:\n1199:              - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n1200:              - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n1201:              - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n1202:           5. Resolve contradictions:\n1203:              - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n1204:              - Determine final severity and status\n1205:           6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n1206:         outputs:\n1207:           - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n1208:           - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n1209:           - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n1210:           - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n1211: \n1212:       step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n1213:         action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n1214:         algorithm: |\n1215:           For each active P0/P1 finding:\n1216:             1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n1217:             2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n1218:             3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n1219:           Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n1220: \n1221:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1222:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1223:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1224:         read:\n1225:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1226:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1227:         write:\n1228:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1229:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1230: \n1231:       step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n1232:         action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n1233:         note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n1234: \n1235:       step_compile_review_report:\n1236:         action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n1237:         instructions: |\n1238:           Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n1239: \n1240:           1. **Executive Summary**\n1241:              - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n1242:              - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n1243:              - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n1244:              - Review scope summary\n1245: \n1246:           2. **Planning Trigger**\n1247:              - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n1248:              - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n1249:              - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n1250:              - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n1251: \n1252:           3. **Active Finding Registry**\n1253:              - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n1254:              - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n1255: \n1256:           4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n1257:              - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n1258: \n1259:           5. **Spec Seed**\n1260:              - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n1261: \n1262:           6. **Plan Seed**\n1263:              - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n1264: \n1265:            7. **Traceability Status**\n1266:               - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n1267:               - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n1268:               - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n1269: \n1270:           If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n1271:              - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n1272:              - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n1273:              - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n1274: \n1275:           8. **Deferred Items**\n1276:              - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n1277: \n1278:           9. **Search Ledger**\n1279:              - Always include this section before the appendix.\n1280:              - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n1281:              - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n1282:              - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n1283: \n1284:           10. **Audit Appendix**\n1285:              - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n1286:              - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n1287: \n1288:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n1289:         output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n1290: \n1291:       step_convergence_report:\n1292:         action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n1293:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"activeP0\":{active_p0},\"activeP1\":{active_p1},\"activeP2\":{active_p2},\"dimensionCoverage\":{dimension_coverage},\"verdict\":\"{verdict}\",\"releaseReadinessState\":\"{release_readiness_state}\",\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1294:         note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n1295: \n1296:       step_update_config_status:\n1297:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1298:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1299:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1300: \n1301:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n1302:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n1303:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n1304:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n1305:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n1306: \n1307:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1308:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1309:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1310:   phase_save:\n1311:     purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n1312:     steps:\n1313: \n1314:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1315:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1316:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1317:         requirements:\n1318:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n1319:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n1320:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n1321:         example_payload: |\n1322:           {\n1323:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n1324:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n1325:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n1326:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n1327:             \"exchanges\": [],\n1328:             \"toolCalls\": []\n1329:           }\n1330: \n1331:       step_generate_context:\n1332:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1333:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1334:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1335: \n1336:       step_index_memory:\n1337:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1338:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1339:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1340:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1341: \n1342:       step_verify_save:\n1343:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1344:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1345:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1346: \n1347:       step_release_lock:\n1348:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1349:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1350:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1351: \n1352:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1353:   # COMPLETION\n1354:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1355:   completion:\n1356:     message: |\n1357:       Deep review complete.\n1358:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1359:       Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n1360:       Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n1361: \n1362:       Artifacts:\n1363:         - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1364:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n1365:         - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n1366:         - Memory context saved\n1367: \n1368:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1369:     next_steps:\n1370:       - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n1371:       - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n1372:       - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n1373:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1374: \n1375: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1376: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1377: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1378: error_recovery:\n1379:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1380:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1381:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1382:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n1383: \n1384: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1385: # RULES\n1386: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1387: rules:\n1388:   ALWAYS:\n1389:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1390:     - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n1391:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1392:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1393:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1394:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1395:     - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n1396:     - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n1397:     - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n1398:   NEVER:\n1399:     - skip_convergence_check\n1400:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1401:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1402:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1403:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1404:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1405:     - modify_files_under_review\n1406:     - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n1407: \n1408: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1409: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n1410: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1411: reference_only_appendix:\n1412:   checkpoint_commit:\n1413:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1414:     commands:\n1415:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n1416:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n1417:   severity_weights:\n1418:     note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n1419:     weights:\n1420:       P0: 10.0\n1421:       P1: 5.0\n1422:       P2: 1.0\n1423:     p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n1424:     clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) → newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n1425:   review_dimensions:\n1426:     note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n1427:     dimensions:\n1428:       - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n1429:       - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n1430:       - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n1431:       - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n1432:   cross_reference_protocols:\n1433:     note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n1434:     core_protocols:\n1435:       - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n1436:       - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n1437:     overlay_protocols:\n1438:       - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n1439:       - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".codex/.opencode/.agents\" }\n1440:       - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 635-1440. Use offset=1441 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n            - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n            - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n          pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n          set:\n            next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n            pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n        if_pending_pause_event:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n          halt: true\n        if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n        if_no_pending_event:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_generate_state_summary:\n        action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n        generate: |\n          STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n          Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          Dimension: {next_dimension}\n          Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n          Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n          Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n          {resource_map_prompt_line}\n          Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n          Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n          Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n              review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n              review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n              p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n              p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n              p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-review\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: '{config.executor.configDir}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.configDir}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n\n            process.exit(await runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync({\n              command: 'codex',\n              args: [\n                'exec',\n                '--model',\n                executor.model,\n                '-c',\n                `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n                '-c',\n                `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n                '-c',\n                'approval_policy=never',\n                '--sandbox',\n                resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n                '-',\n              ],\n              cwd: '{repo_root}',\n              timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n              stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n              executor,\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n            }));\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_copilot:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n            const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n\n            // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n            // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n            // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n            // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n            // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n            // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n            // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n            const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n            const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n\n            const baseArgs = [\n              '-p',\n              prompt,\n              '--model',\n              '{config.executor.model}',\n              '--allow-all-tools',\n              '--no-ask-user',\n            ];\n\n            const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n              promptPath,\n              prompt,\n              targetAuthority,\n              baseArgv: baseArgs,\n            });\n\n            // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n            // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n            // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n            // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n            // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n            if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n              writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n            }\n\n            const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n              cwd: '{repo_root}',\n              stdio: 'inherit',\n              timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n            });\n            process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n            - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n            - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n            - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n            - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n            - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n            claude \\\n              -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n              --output-format text \\\n              {optional_effort_flag}\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_claude_config_dir: |\n              If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n            optional_effort_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n            - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n            - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          failure_reasons:\n            - iteration_file_missing\n            - iteration_file_empty\n            - jsonl_not_appended\n            - jsonl_missing_fields\n            - jsonl_parse_error\n            - jsonl_wrong_type\n            - delta_file_missing\n            - delta_file_empty\n            - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n            - executor_missing\n            - dispatch_failure_logged\n            - v2_missing_ledger\n            - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n            - v2_broken_linked_finding\n            - v2_shallow_finding_details\n            - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n            - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n          warning_surface:\n            source: \"result.warnings\"\n            action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n            severity: \"advisory\"\n            event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n        extract:\n          - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n          - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-03 -->\n          # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n          # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n\n      step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n        action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n        verify:\n          - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n          - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n          - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n        on_pass:\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: true\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n        on_fail:\n          action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: false\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n\n      step_reduce_review_state:\n        action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n        note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Transform the latest iteration graphEvents delta into review graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n          2. If graphEvents is absent or empty, set graph_nodes_json = [] and graph_edges_json = [] and skip the upsert.\n          3. For each graph event without relation/source/target, normalize type = uppercase(event.type || event.nodeKind || event.type) and keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n          4. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } using the event label (or id fallback) and review metadata for run/current focus.\n          5. For each graph event with relation + source + target, normalize relation = uppercase(event.relation) and keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n          6. Emit edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata } and deduplicate the batch by id.\n          7. Discard malformed or unknown graph events instead of failing the review iteration.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Upsert only the latest iteration graph delta.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph nodes for the latest iteration\"\n          - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph edges for the latest iteration\"\n        skip_conditions:\n          - \"Latest iteration record has no graphEvents array\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        content: |\n          # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n          Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n\n          ## Status\n          - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n          - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n          - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n          - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n\n          ## Findings Summary\n          | Severity | Count | Trend |\n          |----------|------:|-------|\n          | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n          | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n          | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n\n          ## Dimension Coverage\n          | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n          |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n          | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n\n          ## Traceability Coverage\n          | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n          |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n          | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n\n          ## Progress\n          | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n          |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n          | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n          ## Trend\n          - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n          - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n\n          ## Next Focus\n          {next_dimension}\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          stuck_count: |\n            if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n            if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n            if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n            else: 0\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n        bind_from_output:\n          p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n          p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n          p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n      # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n      # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n      # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n      # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n      step_derive_verdict:\n        action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if p0_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"FAIL\"\n          elif p1_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n          else:\n            verdict = \"PASS\"\n          has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n          ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n        outputs:\n          - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n          - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n        contract: |\n          Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n          Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_build_finding_registry:\n        action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n          2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n             content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n             Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n          3. Two-tier dedup:\n             PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n               - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n             FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n               - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n          4. Track finding lifecycle:\n             - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n             - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n             - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n          5. Resolve contradictions:\n             - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n             - Determine final severity and status\n          6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n        outputs:\n          - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n          - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n          - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n          - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n\n      step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n        action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          For each active P0/P1 finding:\n            1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n            2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n            3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n          Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n        action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n        note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n\n      step_compile_review_report:\n        action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n        instructions: |\n          Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n\n          1. **Executive Summary**\n             - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n             - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n             - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n             - Review scope summary\n\n          2. **Planning Trigger**\n             - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n             - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n             - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n             - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n\n          3. **Active Finding Registry**\n             - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n             - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n\n          4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n             - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n\n          5. **Spec Seed**\n             - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n\n          6. **Plan Seed**\n             - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n\n           7. **Traceability Status**\n              - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n              - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n              - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n\n          If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n             - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n             - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n             - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n\n          8. **Deferred Items**\n             - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n\n          9. **Search Ledger**\n             - Always include this section before the appendix.\n             - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n             - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n             - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n\n          10. **Audit Appendix**\n             - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n             - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"activeP0\":{active_p0},\"activeP1\":{active_p1},\"activeP2\":{active_p2},\"dimensionCoverage\":{dimension_coverage},\"verdict\":\"{verdict}\",\"releaseReadinessState\":\"{release_readiness_state}\",\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n        note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep review complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n      Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n        - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n      - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n      - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n    - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n    - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n    - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n    - modify_files_under_review\n    - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  severity_weights:\n    note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n    weights:\n      P0: 10.0\n      P1: 5.0\n      P2: 1.0\n    p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n    clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) → newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n  review_dimensions:\n    note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n    dimensions:\n      - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n      - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n      - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n      - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n  cross_reference_protocols:\n    note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n    core_protocols:\n      - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n      - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n    overlay_protocols:\n      - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n      - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".codex/.opencode/.agents\" }\n      - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }","lineStart":635,"lineEnd":1440,"totalLines":1441,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781756138779,"end":1781756138787}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a1ba3ea8f7bbf5016a3370ea6f4c8191bc17bb5e80369ae3"}},"id":"prt_ed8f113d50014ikLsEFuUhhrGD","sessionID":"ses_1270ff7ffffeghChHIr0qZoieH","messageID":"msg_ed8f0ffd8001D0nocr51mE1aSp"}}
